Appendix 0 1993-2004 United Nations Office in Burundi (UNOB)

UNOB was established on 25 October 1993 at the request of the Security Council to facilitate the restoration of constitutional rule in Burundi. This step was undertaken following the coup d'état on 21 October 1993.

UNOB was replaced by a peacekeeping operation, the United Nations Operation in Burundi (ONUB) in May 2004.

1993 SRSG Ahmedou Ould-Abdallah, appointed for Burundi

Secretary-General, Boutros Boutros-Ghali offered his good offices to Burundi in November 1993, appointed Ahmedou Ould-Abdallah as his Special Envoy and established UNOB (the United Nations Office in Burundi, which reported to the UN Department of Political Affairs, DPA)

1995.11.01 I have the honour to inform you that I have decided to appoint Mr. Aziz Hasbi as my new Special Representative in Burundi. Mr. Hasbi will be taking up his responsibilities in the coming days. Mr. Hasbi, formerly the Permanent Representative of Morocco to the United Nations and later Minister of Administrative Affairs, will be replacing Mr. Ahmedou Ould Abdallah, who, until his departure from Burundi last month, had served as my Special Representative there for over two years.

Abdallah resigned in September 1995. Three months of deliberation rations were necessary to find a candidate acceptable to all parties in conflict. Finally, Marc Faguy, a Canadian diplomat, was appointed on December 22nd. Boutros-Ghali had proposed the appointment of Aziz Hasbi. However, the former Moroccan ambassador to the UN was vetoed by Bujumbura and the appointment had to be cancelled

1995-1997 SRSG Marc Faguy appointed

19951222 Secretary-General Boutros Boutros-Ghali today appointed Marc Faguy, of Canada, as his Special Representative for Burundi in replacement of Ahmedou Ould Abdallah of Mauritania, who resumed his functions at Headquarters in October after a two-year tour of duty in Bujumbura.

Mr. Abdallah held office until October 1995. Mr. Marc Faguy, Canadian, who succeeded him, served from January 1996 to February 1997. Mr. Cheikh Tidiane Sy, of Senegalese nationality, is the current Director

upgrade the level of the United Nations Office in Burundi by appointing Mr. Cheikh Tidiane Sy, the current head of the Office, as SG’s Representative in Burundi

Current Head of Mission: Ambassador Berhanu Dinka (Ethiopia) was appointed Special Representative of the Secretary General (SRSG) for Burundi on July 23, 2002. Born on 4 June 1935 in the province of Wollega in Ethiopia, Mr. Dinka was educated in Ethiopia and in the United States.  He holds degrees in politics and economics.

Norbert Holl resigned as head of UNSMA on December 29, 1997.

1997 on 29 July, I appointed Mr. Lakhdar Brahimi as my Special Envoy on a short mission to consult interested and relevant countries and parties, as well as the Organization of the Islamic Conference, and to present a comprehensive review of the United Nations peacemaking activities in Afghanistan. Mr. Brahimi started his mission on 15 August.

Lakhdar Brahimi resigned as UN special envoy to Afghanistan on October 31, 1999.

亚洲

阿富汗 Afghanistan

阿富汗原为不列颠保护领，1919年独立。1923年4月颁布宪法，实行宪政，组织Advisory Council of State。1928年8月成立大支尔格会议，称作National Council。1931年10月宪法规定建立两院制议会，Council of State (Majlis-i-Shora-Milli)和Chamber of Notables (Majlis-i-Ayan)。1964年10月宪法同样规定了两院，Parliament (Shura) 由House of the People（Wolesi Jirga）和House of Elders（Meshrano Jirga）组成。1973年7月政变废除君主制，建立共和政府。1977年2月宪法规定建立House of Nationals （Meli Jirga），但1978年4月的塔拉基政变使之流产。1979年12月苏联入侵，大支尔格会议被解散，此后长期陷入战乱。根据1987年11月大支尔格会议通过的宪法，建立了两院制议会National Assembly (Meli Shura)，包括Senate (Sena)和House of Representatives (Wolasi Jirgah)。1992年以来也不复工作，直至2001年塔利班被推翻。2002年起政局始渐趋稳定，6月召集紧急支尔格大会，选举产生以卡尔扎伊为总统的阿富汗伊斯兰过渡政府；2003年12月召开制宪支尔格大会，制定并通过新宪法。根据阿宪法，国民议会（National Assembly）是国家最高立法机关，由人民院（下院）House of the People（Wolesi Jirga）和长老院（上院）House of Elders（Meshrano Jirga），2005年9月举行首次选举。根据新宪法，大支尔格会议是阿富汗人民意愿的最高体现，由一会上下两院医院、各省议会议长组成，会议不定期举行。除前述2002年月组织过渡政府、2003年12月制宪大会外，2010年6月召开和平支尔格大会，呼吁塔利班等参与政治和解进程；2011年11月召开大支尔格会议，讨论阿富汗同美国商签战略伙伴关系文件；2019年4月召开和平大支尔格会议，讨论同塔利班和谈问题。2021年8月塔利班重新掌权。

1923.04.09

The first constitution of Afghanistan establishs Advisory Council of State

1928.08.

A loya jirga (assembly of the people) is held at Paghman, Council of State is replaced by a National Assembly

1931.10.31

The new constitution provides two chambers parliament, National Council (Shura-i-Milli) and House of Nobles (Majlis-i-Ayan)

1964.09.09-19

A Loya Jirga called by King Mohammed Zahir Shah to approve a new constitution

1964.10.01

The new constitution provides The Shura (Parliament) to bo consisted of two houses, Wolesi Jirgah (House of the People) and Meshrano Jirgah (House of the Elders)

1973.07.17

The monarchy (and constitution) is abolished after the coup

1977.01.30-02.15

A Loya Jirga is called to compose and approve the new constitution

1977.02.24

The newly proclaimed constitution provides a single chamber parliament, the House of Nationals (Meli Jirga)

1978.04.27

The 1977 Constitution is abolished after the coup

1980.04.21

The Revolutionary Council ratified the Basic Principles of the Democratic Republic of Afghanistan

1985.04.23-25

A Loya Jirga is called to ratify the new constitution

1987.11.29-30

A new Loya Jirga is called to ratify a new constitution, The Meli Shura (National Assembly) is the highest legislative organ and it consists of two houses, the Wolasi Jirgah (House of Representative) and the Sena (Senate)

2001.12.05

Bonn Agreement is passed intended to re-create the State of Afghanistan

2002.10.05

Under the Bonn Agreement the Afghan Constitution Drafting Commission is established to draft a new constitution, President Karzai appoints the members and selects vice president Nematullah Shahrani as commission chairman. There is a drafting committee established on 11.03 and is replaced by review committee on 2003.05.07, still chaired by Shahrani.

2003.12.14-2004.01.04

Loya Jirga is held to consider and endorse the new constitution

2004.01.26

The new constitution is officially signed by President Hamid Karzai. The National Assembly of Afghanistan consists of two houses: the Wolesi Jirga (House of the People) and the Meshrano Jirga (House of Elders).

巴基斯坦 Pakistan

巴基斯坦原为印度一部分，1947年独立，实行宪政。首次制宪议会（Constituent Assembly）于1947年8月10日召开，8月11日真纳当选制宪议会主席，8月14日与英属印度末任总督蒙巴顿勋爵举行正式交接仪式。尽管制宪议会于1954年就准备好宪法草案，但是1954年10月24日议会被总督解散，并于1955年5月28日选举产生了第二届制宪议会。此次议会终于1956年2月29日通过宪法，并于3月23日正式实施，建立一院制议会（National Assembly）。首次选举应于1959年举行，然而总统米尔扎于1958年10月7日宣布废除宪法，解散议会并实行军事管制。新总统阿尤布汗于1960年2月17日组建宪法委员会（Constitution Commission），1962年3月1日实行新宪法，国民议会因此得以恢复。1969年再次实行军事管制法，议会再次被解散。根据法令，1970年12月重新举行了议会选举，但是由于印巴战争以及东巴分离，迟至1972年4月14日才举行首次会议，此时的国家总统已是阿里·布托。议会的任务是制定新宪法，1973年4月获得批准，同年8月14日实行。依据1973年宪法，建立两院制议会，国民议会（National Assembly）和参议院（Senate）。1977年7月在经历一次选举危机以后，军队接管政权，议会再次被终止。1981年12月24日，齐亚·哈克总统下令组建联邦咨询委员会（Federal Council (Majlis-e-Shoora)），从而恢复了部分的政治活力。在此基础上，1985年2月举行了议会选举，3月20日议会恢复活动。1999年10月12日穆沙拉夫将军发动军事政变，推翻民选政府，并于14日宣布宪法暂时无效，中止国民议会和参议院等多项法令。2001年6月20日，穆沙拉夫就任总统，同时颁布法令，正式解散被中止的议会。2002年8月穆沙拉夫颁布“法律框架令（Legal Framework Order）”，宣布恢复1973年宪法。同年10月和2003年2月，国民议会和参议院相继举行了选举，得以恢复。

1947.07.26 A notification was issued in the Gazette of India in which the first Constituent Assembly of Pakistan was given shape

1947.08.10 The first session of the first Constituent Assembly of Pakistan was held.

1947.08.11 Muhammad Ali Jinnah was elected unanimously as the President of the Constituent Assembly of Pakistan and the National Flag was formally approved by the Assembly.

1947.08.15 Muhammad Ali Jinnah was sworn in as the first Governor General of Pakistan.

1948.09.11 Muhammad Ali Jinnah died.

1948.12.14 Moulvi Tamizuddin Khan was elected new President of the Constituent Assembly.

1954.10.24 Governor General Malik Ghulam Muhammad dissolved Constituent Assembly of Pakistan.

1955.05.28 The second Constituent Assembly reconstituted.

1956.02.29 The Constitution was passed by the Constituent Assembly, assent was given on it by the Governor General on 2nd March 1956

1956.03.23 The constitution was promulgated, with unicameral legislative.

1958.10.07 martial law was imposed

1960.02.17 President Ayub Khan appointed a Constitution Commission with former Chief Justice Muhammad Shahabuddin as Chairman

1962.03.01 The new constitution was promulgated by president and finally came into effect on June 8 1963. The National Assembly is restored.

1962.03.28 General elections under the new Constitution were held

1962.06.08 The first session of the third National Assembly was held

1969.03.25 President Yahya Khan posed martial law again.

1971.12.20 Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto took over as the President of Pakistan as well as the first civil Chief Martial Law Administrator

1972.04.14 The first session of the National Assembly, due to the delay caused by the separation of East Pakistan, was held

1972.04.17 An Interim Constitution was adopted by the National Assembly, which provided for a Presidential form of Government. The Assembly also formed a Constitution Committee to prepare a draft of the permanent constitution of Pakistan. Mahmud Ali Kasuri was the elected chairman of the committee.

1972.04.21 Martial law was lifted and Zulfi kar All Bhutto was sworn in as President under an interim Constitution approved four days ago by the National Assembly

1973.04.10 A bill to provide a constitution for the Islamic Republic of Pakistan was passed in the assembly, and it was endorsed by the acting President Zulfikar Ali Bhutto on April 12, 1973

1973.04.14 The constitution was promulgated. On the same day, Mr. Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto took oath as the Prime Minister, while Mr. Fazal Illahi Choudhary took oath as the President of Pakistan.

1977.07.05 General Zia staged a military coup and suspended the constitution.

1981.12.24 A Federal Council (Majlis-e-Shoora) was constituted by the President, members nominated by the President

1982.01.11 The first session of this Federal Council was held, Khwaja Muhammad Safdar from Sialkot was nominated as its Chairman

1985.02.25 general elections were held for the National and Provincial Assemblies

1985.03.02 the revival of Constitution Order (P.O.14 of 1985) was issued

1985.03.20 The first session of the National Assembly was held

1999.10.12 General Musharraf staged a military coup and Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif is ousted.

1999.10.14 General Musharraf suspended the constitution, suspended the Senate, National and Provincial Assemblies, Chairman and Deputy Chairman Senate, Speaker, Deputy Speaker National and Provincial Assemblies and dismissed the Federal and Provincial governments, and he converted the orders of suspension of legislative bodies and their presiding officers, in to dissolution

2001.06.20 Pervez Musharraf is sworn in as president

2002.08.24 President Pervez Musharraf issued Legal Framework Order provided for the general elections of 2002 and the revival of the 1973 Constitution of Pakistan,

2002.10.10 The elections for twelfth National Assembly was held

2002.11.16 The inaugural session of the National Assembly was held

2002.11.19 Chaudhry Amir Hussain was elected speaker of the National Assembly

2003.02.25-27 Indirect elections to the Senate were held

2003.03.12 Mohammedmian Soomro was elected unopposed chairman of the Senate

不丹 Bhutan

不丹原为不列颠保护领，1947年成为印度保护领。1953年不丹成立国民议会（National Assembly），作为咨询机构。1965年皇家顾问委员会（Royal Advisory Council）成立，为国王顾问咨询机构。1968年11月起在国王的建议下，实行二元君主制，国民议会拥有了立法权，自此议会通过的法案不再需要国王的批准。1998年6月，不丹第四世国王吉格梅·辛格·旺楚克对政治体制进行重大改革，国王不再兼任政府首脑，将政府管理权移交给大臣委员会。2001年9月，旺楚克国王下令筹备起草宪法。2007年12月，举行首次国家委员会（上院）选举。2008年3月，举行首次国民议会（下院）选举，成立首届民选政府。2008年7月不丹颁布首部宪法，实施宪政改革，正式施行两院制，议会（Parliament）由国王、国家委员会（上院）（Natinoal Council）、国民议会（下院）（National Assembly）组成，拥有立法权。新宪法不再设置皇家顾问委员会。

1998.06.10 Jigme Singye Wangchuck, the fourth King of Bhutan, known to his subjects as the Druk Gyalpo, has issued a kasho (royal edict) that could bring profound changes in the kingdom’s everyday life. By devolving full executive powers to an elected cabinet

2001.09.04 King Jigme Singye Wangchuck briefed the Lhengye Zhungtshog (Council of Ministers, or Cabinet), the Chief Justice, and the Chairman of the Royal Advisory Council on the need to draft a formal Constitution for the Kingdom of Bhutan

朝鲜 North Korea

1894年7月朝鲜推行政制改革，建立现代式内阁政府。1897年10月12日高宗称帝，14日改国名为大韩帝国。1910年8月22日成为日本属地，复称朝鲜。1945年8月美国和苏联分别占领朝鲜南、北部。1948年9月北朝鲜劳动党在朝鲜北部召开最高人民会议，朝鲜民主主义人民共和国成立。

东帝汶 Timor Leste

东帝汶原为葡萄牙属地，1974年4月葡爆发革命后，葡政府允许东帝汶举行公民投票，实行民族自决。1975年爆发内战，东帝汶独立革命阵线于1975年11月28日单方面宣布东帝汶独立。印度尼西亚出兵干预并于1976年并吞东帝汶。1998年印尼苏哈托下台，印尼新总统哈比比同意东帝汶通过全民公决选择自治或脱离印尼。1999年8月全民公决78.5％赞成独立，印尼亦表示接受。投票后东亲印尼派与独立派发生流血冲突，东帝汶局势恶化，安理会通过决议授权成立多国部队，转交联合国管治，9月20日与印尼驻军进行权力移交，正式进驻东帝汶。1999年11月，东帝汶成立具有准内阁、准立法机构性质的全国协商委员会（National Consultative Council），2001年8月举行制宪议会选举，9月15日成立制宪议会（Constitutional Assembly）。2002年5月20日东帝汶正式独立，宪法随即生效，制宪议会自动过渡成首届国民议会（National Parliament）。

菲律宾 Philippines

菲律宾原为西班牙属地，1896年爆发革命。1898年9月在马洛洛成立革命国会（Revolutionary Congress），制定宪法。1899年1月，正式颁布菲律宾资产阶级共和国宪法（史称马洛洛宪法）。1901年美国征服菲律宾，同年成立由美国把持的菲律宾委员会（Philippine Commission），作为民政机关，拥有立法和行政大权。1902年7月1日，美国国会通过了“菲律宾法案”，允许在菲律宾设立一个由选举产生的立法议会（Philippine Legislature），议会形式上有立法权，但是殖民总督对它的决议享有批准和否决的最高权力。立法议会由菲律宾委员会（上院）（Philippine Commission）和菲律宾议会（下院）（Philippine Assembly）共同组成。1907年举行了第一次立法议会选举。1916年8月29日，美国国会通过“菲律宾自治法案（琼斯法案）” （Philippine Autonomy Act (Jones Law)），菲律宾人获得自己选举上、下两院立法机构的权力，菲律宾委员会被废止，代之以参议院（Senate）和众议院（House of Representatives）。1934年7月召开制宪大会（Philippine Constitutional Convention），起草了一个10年过渡的宪法，取消两院制，改设国民议会（National Assembly）。1935年5月新宪法实施，菲律宾自治领成立。1940年4月宪法修正案恢复两院制参众两院。1942年日本侵占菲律宾，组织成立菲律宾执行委员会（Philippine Executive Commission），1942年12月8日建立新比岛建设奉仕团（KALIBAPI）规划执政方案，1943年6月19日建立菲律宾独立准备委员会（Preparatory Committee for Philippine Independence）起草宪法，9月新宪法通过，组织了国民议会（National Assembly），并于10月14日成立菲律宾第二共和国。 1945年美国重新占领菲律宾，菲律宾重建自治政府。1946年7月4日菲律宾独立，延循两院制。1972年9月23日，马科斯总统宣布实施军事管制法，国会参、众两院被解散。同年11月29日通过新宪法草案 ，1973年1月通过“公民大会”投票批准了新宪法，规定一院制国民议会（National Assembly）为国家立法机关。1976年9月21日设立立法咨询大会（Legislative Advisory Council，Batasang Bayan）；1978年6月12日成立临时国民议会（Interim National Assembly，Interim Batasang Pambansa）。1981年1月17日军事管制解除，此后1984年5月选举产生国民议会（Regular National Assembly，Regular Batasang Pambansa）。1986年2月马科斯下台，阿基诺总统执政。1986年4月组织宪法委员会（Constitutional Commission）起草新宪法，于1987年2月2日通过新宪法，恢复了众参两院。

1898.06.12 Emilio Aguinaldo proclaimed the independence of the Philippines at his house in Cavite El Viejo

1898.06.18 Aguinaldo issued a decree formally establishing his dictatorial government

1898.06.23 Aguinaldo issued another decree, this time replacing the dictatorial government with a revolutionary government and naming himself as President

1898.09.15 The Revolutionary Congress was opened by president Emilio Aguinaldo, and the Congress proceeded to elect Pedro A. Paterno as its president

1899.01.21 the Malolos Constitution, was promulgated

1899.01.23 The proclamation of the Malolos Constitution established an insurgent Philippine Republic government which replaced the Revolutionary Government

1901.03.23 Aguinaldo was captured

1901.04.01 General Miguel Malvar took over the leadership of the Filipino government

1901.04.19 Aguinaldo issued a Proclamation of Formal Surrender to the United States

1902.04.13 Miguel Malvar surrendered to U.S.

1899.01.20 President McKinley appointed the First Philippine Commission, headed by Jacob Schurman, president of Cornell University, to investigate conditions in the islands and make recommendations

1900.03.16 President McKinley appointed The Second Philippine Commission, headed by William Howard Taft. And it was granted legislative as well as limited executive powers

1901.07.04 Taft became governor of a civil administration for the Philippines

1902.07.01 The Philippine Organic Act was enacted by the United States Congress, provided for the creation of an elected Philippine Assembly. It proposed a bicameral legislature composed of the Philippine Commission as the upper house and the Philippine Assembly as the lower house

1907.07.30 The first Philippine Assembly elections were held

1907.10.16 The 1st Philippine Legislature was inaugurated at the Manila Grand Opera House, and Sergio Osmeña is elected as Speaker of the Assembly

1916.08.29 The Philippine Autonomy Act was enacted by the United States Congress and contained the first formal and official declaration of the United States Federal Government's commitment to grant independence to the Philippines. The law changed the Philippine Legislature into the Philippines' first fully elected body, changed the name of the Assembly to the House of Representatives, and replaced Commission with eleted Senate.

1916.10.03 The first-ever elections to Philippine Senate were held

1934.03.24 The Philippine Independence Act (Tydings–McDuffie Act) was enacted to provide authority and defined mechanisms for the establishment of a formal constitution via a constitutional convention.

1934.07.10 Election of delegates to the 1934 Philippine Constitutional Convention was held

1934.07.30 At the session of the House of Representatives Claro M. Recto was unanimously elected as President of Philippine Constitutional Convention

1935.02.08 The draft of the 1935 Constitution was adopted by the Philippine Constitutional Convention, provided for unicameral National Assembly and the President was elected to a six-year term without re-election

1935.03.25 The 1935 Constitution was ratified by Pres. Roosevelt in Washington D.C.

1935.05.14 A constitutional plebiscite was held and ratified the 1935 Philippine Constitution

1940.04.11 the [Philippine] Second National Assembly adopted Resolution No. 73 proposing amendments to the Constitution, provided a bicameral Congress composed of a Senate and House of Representatives

1942.01.02 The city of Manila is occupied by Japanese forces

1942.01.23 Philippine Executive Commission was organized and issued by Order No. 1 by the Commander-in-Chief of the Japanese Forces in the Philippines, Jorge B. Vargas was appointed its chairman

1943.06.19 Preparatory Committee for Philippine Independence was created and led by José P. Laurel

1943.09.04 The constitution was signed and unanimously approved by the Preparatory Committee

1943.09.07 the "KALIBAPI" general assembly ratified the draft Constitution

1943.09.20 the "KALIBAPI's" representative groups elected from among themselves members of the Philippine National Assembly

1943.09.25 National Assembly inaugural session was held and elected Benigno Aquino, Sr. as its first Speaker and José P. Laurel as President of the New Philippine Republic

1943.10.14 Second Philippine Republic was proclaimed with José P. Laurel being sworn-in as President

1945.02.27 General Douglas MacArthur declared that Philippine Commonwealth is restored

1945.06.09 First Commonwealth Congress first special session was held, Senators Manuel Roxas and Elpidio Quirino were elected as Senate President and Senate President Pro-Tempore, José Zulueta was elected Speaker of The House of Representatives

1945.08.17 The Second Philippine Republic was formally dissolved by Laurel in Tokyo

1946.07.04 the United States formally recognised the independence of the Republic of the Philippines

1970.11.10 A special election was held to elect the convention's delegates which will change the 1935 Constitution of the Philippines

1971.06.01 Former Philippine President Carlos P. Garcia was sworn in as the President of the Constitutional Convention

1971.06.14 Carlos P. Garcia died, and former President Diosdado Macapagal was elected to replace Garcia

1972.09.23 The formal announcement or promulgation of the proclamation No. 1081, declaring and imposing martial law in the entire country (dated Sept 21), suspended the 1935 Constitution, dissolved Congress, and assuming both legislative and executive powers

1972.11.29 The Constitutional Convention approved the new constitution, provided for the establishment of a unicameral National Assembly

1973.01.17 Marcos issued Proclamation No. 1102 certifying and proclaiming that the 1973 Constitution had been ratified by the Filipino people and thereby was in effect

1973.03.31 Supreme Court of the Philippines ruled that 1973 Philippine Constitution to come into full force

1976.09.21 President Marcos opened the inaugural session of the Batasang Bayan (English: Legislative Advisory Council) formed on 10 September

1978.06.12 The interim Batasang Pambansa was convened

1981.01.17 Martial law was lifted by President Marcos

1984.07.23 The regular Batasang Pambansa was convened

1986.03.25 The Batasang Pambansâ was subsequently dissolved when Proclamation No. 3, known as the 1986 Freedom Constitution, was promulgated

1986.04.23 President Aquino issued Proclamation No. 9, creating a Constitutional Commission

1986.06.02 The first session of the Constitutional commission was held and Cecilia Muñoz-Palma was elected president of the commission

1986.10.15 The ConCom completed their task on October 12, 1986 and presented the draft constitution to President Aquino, provided the Congress composed of the Senate and the House of Representatives

1987.02.02 The constitutional plebiscite was held, and the 1987 Constitution was ratified and took effect

韩国 South Korea

韩国国会历史开始于1919年4月10日为筹建大韩民国临时政府而成立的临时议政院（대한민국 임시의정원(大韓民國臨時議政院)）。1945年日本投降后，朝鲜南部即为美国管理。1945年8月15日吕运亨任委员长的建国准备委员会（Korean National Foundation Preparatory Committee）成立， 9月6日组织召开全国代表大会，会议通过了《朝鲜人民共和国临时组织法》,决定成立“朝鲜人民共和国”，但旋即被美国军事当局宣布为非法。1946年2月1日，李承晚、金九等人为筹建过渡政府成立非常国民议会（비상국민회의(非常國民會議)），后又组成最高政务委员会（최고정무위원회）；2月14日，非常国民议会最高政务委员会应美军政当局的要求改组为其咨询机关民主议院（남조선대한국민대표민주의원(南朝鮮大韓國民代表民主議院)），1947年2月14日更名国民议会（국민의회）。1946年8月24日，美国军政当局制定了《临时立法机构组织法》，10月13日公布，据此选举产生了临时立法议院（South Korean Interim Legislative Assembly，남조선과도입법의원(南朝鮮過渡立法議院)），12月12日正式成立。1948年5月在联合国监督下，选举产生韩国制宪国会，同年成立大韩民国。1948年7月12日通过大韩民国宪法，规定了一院制的国会（National Assembly，대한민국 국회(大韓民國 國會)）是国家最高立法机关。8月15日，大韩民国正式成立。1952年7月2日，总统李承晚为保证自己能连任，派军队强迫国会修宪，将总统产生办法改为由选民直接选举，并将国会改为两院制，由民议院（House of Representatives，민의원(民議院)）和参议院（House of Councilors，참의원(參議院)）组成。但事实上，直到1960年李承晚下台时止，韩国并未举行参议院的选举。1962年12月17日由朴正熙政府主持通过的第五次宪法修正案规定国会恢复采用一院制国会。1972年10月17日朴正熙发动自我政变（十月维新），废除宪法，解散国会；10月27日颁布维新宪法，据此组织了统一主体国民会议（National Conference for Unification，통일주체국민회의（統一主體國民會議）），负责选举总统。1980年10月27日再次修宪，国会的权限和宪政地位得到提高，依然维持一院制国会。

1945.08.15 Korean National Foundation Preparatory Committee is formed in Seoul, with Yo Unhyong as chairman, An Chae- hong and Chang Toksu as vice-chairmen [Chairman Aug 15 – Sep 3 여운형(呂運亨), Sep 3 – Sep 6 안재홍(安在鴻), Sep 6 – Sep 7 양재하(梁在廈)]

1945.08.17 Cho Mansik forms National Foundation Preparatory Committee in P’yongan Namdo [Chairman 조만식(曺晩植)]

1945.08.20 USSR’s 28th Army commanding General issues Decree Number 1, ordering formation of People’s Committee

1945.08.27 USSR Army Headquarters Pyongyang orders dissolution of right-wing National Foundation Preparatory Committee and its merger with P’yongan Namdo People’s Political Committee

1945.09.06 Korean National Foundation Preparatory Committee in SK announces establishment of People’s Republic of Korea

1945.09.07 US Army Far East Command announces establishment of US Military Government in SK

1945.09.14 Korean National Foundation Preparatory Committee announces Cabinet: Syngman Rhee President, Yo Unhyong Vice-president, Ho Hon Prime Minister. Rhee declines 7 November 1945

1945.09.16 USSR Army Political Bureau announces establishment of military government in NK

1948.07.24 Syngman Rhee and Yi Siyong inaugurated as ROK President and Vice-President

1948.08.15 Republic of Korea was formally established, and US Military Government terminated

柬埔寨 Cambodia

柬埔寨，1863年沦为法兰西保护领。1913年3月18日在法方压力下，柬埔寨国王成立咨议机构（Consultative Assembly）。1946年9月柬埔寨组织制宪议会（Constituent Assembly）选举，1947年5月6日颁布宪法，实行宪政，组建国民议会（相当于众议院）（National Assembly）和王国议会（相当于参议院）（Council of the Kingdom）。1953年11月9日柬埔寨最终取得独立。1970年3月首相朗诺发动政变夺权，改国名为高棉共和国，撤销国会，代之以制宪会议（Constituent Assembly），组织新宪法。1972年4月30日新宪法实施，国会（Parliament）由国民议会（National Assembly）和参议院（Senate）组成，9月组织了首次选举。1970年朗诺政变后，同年3月23日，西哈努克在北京宣布成立柬埔寨民族统一阵线，5月5日，成立以宾努亲王为首相的柬埔寨王国民族团结政府（Royal Government of the National Union of Kampuchea）。1975年4月红色高棉夺权，改国名为民主柬埔寨，通过国民大会制订了新宪法，于1976年1月5日公布，建立人民代表大会（Kampuchean People's Representative Assembly）。1978年12月越南入侵，柬埔寨出现抵抗政府（民主柬埔寨联合政府）与人民革命党政府（柬埔寨人民共和国，1989年5月1日改称柬埔寨国）对峙的局面。1981年6月柬埔寨人民共和国通过新宪法，议会位一院制的国民议会（National Assembly）。1990年9月柬成立全国最高委员会（Supreme National Council），西哈努克任主席。1993年柬埔寨各派达成和解，恢复统一。1993年5月组织了制宪会议选举，9月24日新宪法生效，恢复成为君主立宪制的王国，制宪会议转为国民议会（National Assembly）。1999年3月，修改宪法，增设参议院（Senate）。

1913.03.18 King Sisowath signed a royal decree to create a consultative assembly

1945.03.12 King Norodom Sihanouk proclaimed Cambodia’s independence from France

1946.01.04 France granted Cambodia internal autonomy

1946.09.01 The first general election in Cambodia is held and a Constituent Assembly was setup

1947.05.06 Cambodia was proclaimed a constitutional monarchy and first constitution created National Assembly and a Council of the Kingdom

1975.12.15-19 The text of a Constitution was adopted during a command group meeting, provided a Kampuchean People's Representative Assembly as legislative body

1976.01.05 A new constitution was promulgated, and the Democratic Kampuchea was proclaimed

1976.03.20 Parliamentary elections were held

1976.04.02 Prince Sihanouk resigned as head-of-state

1981.12.05 Pen Sovan was removed from office and replaced by Chan Sy

1982.06.22 The Coalition Government of Democratic Kampuchea (CGDK) was established by Prince Sihanouk (president), Khieu Samphan (vice-president), and Son Sann (prime minister) in opposition to the government

1989.05.01 The official name of the country was changed from People's Republic of Kampuchea to State of Cambodia

1993.05.23-28 General election was held to elect the constituent assembly

1993.06.15 Sihanouk proposed the formation of an Interim Joint Administration (GNPC) with Prince Ranariddh and Mr. Hun Sen as Co-Chairmen

1993.10.25 Chea Sim (CPP) became president of National Assembly

1999.03.04 The amendments of the constitution of the Kingdom of Cambodia which was promulgated by the National Assembly, creating a senate

1999.03.25 The new senate is sworn in by the King, and Chea Sim was elected president

老挝 Laos

老挝地区，1893年琅勃拉邦、万象和占巴塞被并入法属印度支那联邦。1945年9月15日，琅勃拉邦宣布老挝独立，10月12日成立伊沙拉（自由）政府，建立临时立法机构人民代表大会（Congress of People's Representatives），并逼迫国王退位；1946年4月在法国支持下国王复位，独立运动失败（伊沙拉政府流亡泰国，1949年10月最终解散）。1946年8月法国给予老挝内部自治，12月组织制宪大会（Constituent Assembly），1947年5月颁布宪法，实行宪政，成立国会（National Assembly）。1953年10月22日最终取得独立。1974年4月5日，以富马为首相的第三次联合政府（Provisional Government of National Union）和以苏发努冯为主席的民族政治联合委员会（National Political Consultative Council）成立。1975年12月2日老挝全国人民代表大会（National Congress of People's Representatives）宣布废除君主制，成立老挝人民民主共和国，成立最高人民议会（Supreme People's Assembly）。1991年8月老挝最高人民议会通过首部宪法，最高人民议会改名为国会（National Assembly），1993年2月换届时正式更名。

1945.03.09 Japan took over French rule in Indochina

1945.09.15 Lao Issara (Lao Freedom), led by Prince Phetsarath declared Laotian independence from France, by unify the Kingdom of Louangphrabang with the four southern provinces of Khammouan, Savannakhét, Champasak, and Saravan

1946.04.23 Sisavang Vong is reinstated as King of Laos, in return for royal legitimation of the provisional government’s actions.

1989.03.26 Election to Supreme People's Assembly was held

1992.12.20 Election to the new National Assembly was held.

马尔代夫 Maldives

马尔代夫，1887年成为不列颠保护国。1931年3月9日成立起草宪法的委员会，1932年12月22日颁布宪法，实行宪政，设立议会（Majlis）。1940年1月苏丹中止宪法，1942年4月23日提出新宪法，成立人民议会（People's Majlis）。1952年4月15日召开特别议会，决定废除伊斯兰教君主统治，成立共和国。1953年1月1日共和国成立，新宪法规定总统直选、司法独立，以及两院制的议会（Senate and House of Representatives）。同年8月21日共和国被废止，苏丹国于1954年1月恢复，3月7日颁布的新宪法保留了一院制议会（People's Majlis）。1965年7月26日取得独立。1968年3月15日全民公决，11月11日成为共和国。1980年3月29日设立公民特别议会（Citizen’ Special Majlis），审查新宪法，1997年11月27日通过，次年1月1日实施。1998年5月选举人民特别议会（People’s Special Majlis）修宪，10月召开会议，至2008年8月7日颁布新宪法。

1931.03.09 A council was set up by Sultan Muhammad Shamsuddeen III to draft the constitution of the Maldives

1932.12.22 The council completed and implemented the constitution, providing the first ever Majlis of the Maldives

1940.01.31 The Maldives’ first constitution was suspended shortly after World War II broke

1942.04.23 A new constitution was implemented

1952.02.21 Sultan Abdul Majeed Didi died

1952.04.13 The People's Majlis voted to form a commission with Amin Didi as its chairman to determine the country's future governance structure (Chief Justice Abdullah Jalaludeen, Majlis Speaker Malim Moosa Mafaiy Kilegefan are members)

1952.04.16 the People's Majlis affirmed the commission's decision to form a republic

1952.04.17-18 A constitutional referendum was held and The new constitution converted the country from a monarchy to a republic, with the new judiciary appointed by the president and a bicameral legislature

1953.01.01 the new constitution came into force and First Republic was declared under the short-lived presidency of Muhammad Amin Didi

1953.08.21 A revolution abolished the Republic

1954.01.31 The country reverted to a Sultanate

1954.02.22 The National Assembly voted to abandon the republic

1954.03.07 the ratification of the fourth Constitution of Maldives, and unicameral legislature was reinstated; The assembly elected Muhammad Farid Didi as Sultan and he was installed

1965.07.26 Maldives gained independence under an agreement signed with Britain

1968.03.15 In a national referendum, Maldivians abolished the sultanate and established a republic

1968.09.27 Ibrahim Nasir was elected president in referendum form of election

1968.11.11 The Second Republic was proclaimed under the presidency of Ibrahim Nasir

1973.09. Ibrahim Nasir was elected to a second term under the constitution as amended in 1972, which extended the presidential term to five years and which also provided for the election of the prime minister by the Majlis

1975.03.06 Newly elected prime minister Zaki was arrested in a bloodless coup and was banished to a remote atoll

1978.06. Nasir announced that, for health reasons, he would not seek reelection at the end of his second five-year term

1978.07.28 Maumoon Abdul Gayoom was elected to replace Nasir for a five-year presidential term

马来西亚 Malaysia

马来亚诸邦原为不列颠属地，分为海峡殖民地（Straits Settlements，包含新加坡Singapore、槟城Penang、马六甲Malacca，后又加入天定Dinding以及纳闽Labuan）、马来联邦（Federated Malay States，接受英国保护的马来王朝，包括雪兰莪Selangor、森美兰Negeri Sembilan、霹雳Perak和彭亨Pahang，首府吉隆坡Kuala Lumpur）、马来属邦（Unfederated Malay States，受英国保护但未加入马来联邦的土邦，包括玻璃市Perlis、吉打Kedah、吉兰丹Kelantan、登嘉楼Terengganu和柔佛Johor）、沙巴（Sabah，原英属北婆罗洲直辖殖民地Crown Colony of North Borneo）、沙捞越（Sarawak，原英属沙捞越直辖殖民地Crown Colony of Sarawak）等部分。英国政府在殖民地逐步设立立法会议，更于1909年12月在马来联邦设立了联邦委员会（Federal Council），作为联邦的中央立法机构。1948年2月英国将马来联邦、马来属邦和海峡殖民地（不包括新加坡）整合为马来亚联邦（Malayan Union），一个在英王统领下的皇家殖民地，同时设立咨议委员会（Advisory Council）。1948年1月，马来亚联邦改组为马来亚联合邦（Federation of Malaya），成立联邦立法委员会（Federal Legislative Council）取代原先的联邦委员会，在马独立前夕负责拟定宪法。1953年9月起马来人开始担任议长，1955年7月首次选举。1957年8月31日马来亚联合邦宣布独立，新宪法生效，国会（Parliament，Parlimen Malaysia）由上议院（Senate，Dewan Negara）和下议院（House of Representatives，Dewan Rakyat）组成。1963年9月16日马来亚与新加坡、沙巴、沙捞越合并为马来西亚（1965年8月9日新加坡退出），议会制度保持不变。

附录：各殖民地立法会议概述

  • 海峡殖民地：1867年4月1日设立立法委员会（Legislative Council），1942年2月15日日军占领马来和新加坡后废止。战后海峡殖民地撤销，大部分并入Malaya联邦，新加坡改英属直属殖民地，单独设立立法会议（Legislative Council of Singapore）。
  • 马来联邦：参见前马来西亚，联邦委员会部分。
  • 马来属邦：暂缺。
  • 沙巴（北婆罗洲）：1882年5月北婆罗洲特许公司成立，1888年5月北婆罗洲成为英国保护国，管治仍然完全在北婆罗洲特许公司的手中，英国只保留控制北婆罗洲的对外关系。1883年设立咨议委员会（Advisory Council），1912年为立法委员会（Legislative Council）取代。1946年7月北婆罗洲成为英属直属殖民地后，设立临时咨议委员会（Advisory Council），1950年10月被立法委员会（Legislative Council）取代，1963年并入马来西亚后改称沙巴州议会（Sabah State Legislative Assembly，Dewan Undangan Negeri Sabah）。
  • 沙捞越：1867年9月8日设立总委员会（General Council, Majlis Umum），1903年进化为Council Negri，1976年更名为沙捞越州议会（Sarawak State Legislative Assembly，Dewan Undangan Negeri Sarawak）。

1867.04.01 The Straits Settlements Legislative Council was established when Straits Settlements became a crown colony, headed by the governor

1896.07.01 Independent Malay States of Perak, Selangor, Pahang and Negeri Sembilan entered into a confederation collectively known as the Federated Malay States

1909.12.11 Federal Council was established as central legislative body combining executive and legislative functions, headed by the High Commissioner (Governor of the Straits Settlement) with 13 members including the Rulers of the four Federated Malay States, the Resident General, four British Residents and four unofficial members

1946.04.01 Malayan Union Advisory Council was formed

1948.02.01 Federation of Malaya created and Federal Legislative Council was established which replaced the Federal Council, with High Commissioner as speaker

1953.09.02 British High Commissioner ceased to preside over the Federal Legislative Council, in his place a Speaker was appointed, Dato’ Sir Mahmud bin Mat is the first speaker

1955.07.27 first general elections for Federal Legislative Council

1957.08.15 The Federal Constitution was unanimously adopted by the Federal Legislative Council, providing legislative authority of the Federation consist of the Yang di-Pertuan Agong and two Majlis (Houses of Parliament) to be known as the Dewan Negara (Senate) and the Dewan Rakyat (House of Representatives)

1957.08.27 The Constitution came into force by Federal Constitution Ordinance 1957

1957.08.31 independence was declared

1959.08.19 1st General Election was held. A bicameral Parliament was formed

1963.08.15 Parliament of the Federation of Malaysia approves the Malaysia Agreement

1963.09.04 Sarawak Legislative Assembly approved the Malaysia Agreement

1963.09.16 Malaysia was declared

1963.08.09 withdrawal of Singapore

蒙古 Mongolia

外蒙古原为中国属地，1921年3月事实上独立，改称蒙古。同年10月26日成立临时小呼拉尔（National Provisional Little Hural）。1924年5月20日博克多汗（哲布尊丹巴活佛）去世，11月正式废除君主制，建立蒙古人民共和国，成立国家大呼拉尔（National Great Hural）（其常设机构为国家小呼拉尔National Little Hural，1951年7月新宪法下废除，权力转归国家大呼拉尔）。1960年7月宪法修正，改称大人民呼拉尔（People's Great Khural，Ардын Их Хурал，Ulsyn Ikh Khural）。1990年3月一党制废除，同年7月的首次民主化多党议会自由选举，重新组建了国家小呼拉尔（State Little Khural，Бага Хурал, Baga Khural）。1992年1月通过新宪法，改名为蒙古国，改变大呼拉尔（行使国家最高权力）和小呼拉尔（行使立法和监督权）并存的议会格局，实行设有总统的议会制，国会称国家大呼拉尔（State Great Khural，Улсын Их Хурал），1992年7月正式选举产生。

1921.09.14 independence of Mongolia was proclaimed

1921.10.26 legislative assembly, the National Provisional Little Hural, opened

1924.05.20 Jebtsundamba Khutuktu died met in Niyslel Huree

1924.08.04-24 Third Party Congress of the Mongolian People's Party and renamed it the Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party

1924.11.26 with the adoption of a Soviet-style state constitution by the First National Great Hural, the new national assembly, the Mongolian People's Republic was formally established. The National Little Hural, the standing body when the National Great Hural was not in session, was elected; it, in turn, elected a cabinet with Balingiyn Tserendorj as premier and Choybalsan as commander in chief of the army

1924.11. The first State Great Khural was called to session, and elected the Little Khutal with its chairman was in effect head of state

1924.11.29 The first session of the Little Khural was held,

1949.02. constitution amendment introduced electoral reform

1951.07.06 Follow the amended Mongolia constitution the Little Khural was abolished

1960.07.06 a (third) new constitution was adopted and the body was renamed the "People's Great Khural" 

1990.04. Amendment to the constitution was adopted to institute State Presidency and State Little Khural established as the legislature

1990.07. The first free, democratic and multi-party election in Mongolia was held

1990.09. The first session of the People’s Great Khural elected Jambyn Gombojav as president

1990 the newly elected parliament changed the Constitution, established the State Baga Khural (Little Khural) within the People's Great Khural as the highest legislative body, with Radnaasümbereliin Gonchigdorj as Chairman and also served as the Vice President of Mongolian People's Republic

1990.09.03 the newly elected Parliament held its first session and chose Mr. P. Ochirbat as Mongolia’s first President of the Republic. Mr. R. Gonchigdorj was elected Vice-President and thus ex-officio Chairman of the Baga Hural. The new Prime Minister is Mr D. Byambasuren

1992.06.28 new election

1992.07.20 First session of the newly created Great Hural, with Natsagiyn Bagabandi as chairman

1992.07. Little Khural was abolished by the adoption of a new Constitution of Mongolia, which created a unicameral legislature

2001.09.29 Chairman Enebish died

孟加拉国 Bangladesh

孟加拉国原为巴基斯坦一部分，称东巴基斯坦，1971年3月独立。1972年4月10日召开制宪会议（Constituent Assembly），12月16日颁布宪法，建立国民议会（Parliament，Jatiya Sangsad），实行议会民主制。1973年3月国民议会首次选举。拉赫曼1974年12月宣布国家处于紧急状态，1975年1月25日国民议会通过宪法第四次修正案，改行总统制。同年8月15日，拉赫曼遇刺身亡，11月齐亚·拉赫曼发动政变，中止国民议会，自任军法管制首席执行官。1979年2月恢复宪法，举行新的议会选举。1981年5月30日，齐亚·拉赫曼遇刺身亡。1982年3月24日，陆军参谋长艾尔沙德发动不流血政变，再次实行军管，宪法中止实行。1986年5月恢复议会选举，11月恢复执行宪法。1990年12月艾尔沙德辞职，孟加拉恢复了民主制度。

1970.12.07

General Election in Pakistan was won by Awami Leageue.

1971.03.01

Under pressure of Pakistan People’s Party, President of Pakistan Yahya Khan postponed the national assembly meeting scheduled for March 3.

1971.03.25

Just before his arrest, Sheikh Mujibur Rahman sent a message declaring the independence of Bangladesh.

1971.04.10

members of both National Assembly (MNA) and Provincial Assembly (MPA) who were able to meet together in Kolkata formed themselves into a constituent assembly in exile and drafted the Proclamation of Independence, empowered the president with all executive and legislative powers.

1971.04.17

The formal meeting of the constituent assembly was held and with declaring of Proclamation of Independence, the Constituent Assembly was proclaimed supreme and sovereign authority of Bangladesh. Yusuf Ali was appointed Duly Constituted Potentiary.

1971.04.17

The Provisional Government of Bangladesh took oath in Mujibnagar, with Sheikh Mujibur Rahman named president; Syed Nazrul Islam acting president; Tajuddin Ahmed prime minister; and Gen. Ataul Gani Osmani as the commander-in-chief of the to-be-formed Bangladesh Armed Forces.

1971.12.16

Pakistan Army in Bangladesh surrendered in Dacca, and Bangladesh earned its de facto indepence.

1972.01.08

Sheikh Mujibur Rahman was released from Pakistan jail and via London arrived Dacca on Jan 10.

1972.01.11

In exercise of his legislative power, President Sheikh Mujibur Rahman promulgated the Provisional Constitution Order 1972, introducing a parliamentary democracy where president would exercise all of his functions on advice of the premier.

1972.01.12

Sheikh Mujibur Rahman stepped down as the president to become the prime minister, Justice Abu Sayeed Chowdhury was sworn in as the president.

1972.03.22

the president issued The Constituent Assembly of Bangladesh Order according to the provisional constitution.

1972.04.10

The Constituent Assembly had its first meeting, Shah Abdul Hamid was elected speaker. During the session, a Constitution Drafting Committee was formed under the Chairmanship of Kamal Hossain.

1972.05.01

Shah Abdul Hamid, Speaker of the Constituent Assembly, died of heart failure. Mohammadullah became acting speaker.

1972.11.04

the Constituent Assembly adopted the Constitution of the People’s Republic of Bangladesh, parliament (Jatiya Sangsad) was invested with all  legislative  power.

1972.12.16

The Constitution of the People’s Republic of Bangladesh was promulgated.

1973.03.07

General Elections were held for first time in indepdent Bangladash.

1973.04.07

The newly elected Parliament began its first session and elected Mohammadullah as speaker.

1973.04.08

President Justice Abu Sayeed Chowdhury was elected unopposed as President.

1973.12.24

President Justice Abu Sayeed Chowdhury resigned as President, Speaker of the Parliament Mohammadullah took over as Acting President according to the Constitution.

1974.01.24

Mohammadullah was elected president and sworn in on Jan 27.

1974.01.28

Abdul Malek Ukil was elected speaker of the Parliament to replace Mohammadullah.

1974.12.28

A state of emergency was proclaimed, and some articles of the Constitution suspended.

1975.01.25

The Parliament passed the fourth amendment of the constitution which introduced a one‐party presidential system of government curtailing fundamental rights, the powers of the parliament and the judiciary. The executive authority was vested in the President who would be directly elected, instead of a cabinet of ministers responsible to the parliament. Sheikh Mujibur Rahman sworn in as president and on Jan 26 the cabinet was formed and sworn in with Mohammad Mansoor Ali as prime minister.

1975.08.15

President Sheikh Mujibur Rahman was assassinated in a military coup attack, and government toppled. Khandakar Mushtaq Ahmed assumed the Office of the President.

1975.08.23

Former Prime Minister Mohammad Mansoor Ali was arrested.

1975.11.03

Brigadier General Khaled Mosharraf launched a coup to remove the assassins from power and Khondaker Mostaq Ahmad from the Presidency, while on same day, Syed Nazrul Islam, former Vice President and acting President, Tajuddin Ahmad, former Prime Minister, Muhammad Mansur Ali, former Prime Minister are killed in jail.

1975.11.06

Khandakar Mushtaq Ahmed resigned as president. Chief Justice Abu Sadat Mohammad Sayem took office as new President.

1975.11.08

President Abu Sadat Mohammad Sayem issued a proclamation assuming the powers of Chief Martial Law Administrator, and Chief of Army Staff Ziaur Rahman one of Deputy Chief Martial Law Administrators. Also the proclamation dissolved the Parliament effective as of Nov 6.

1976.11.29

President Abu Sadat Mohammad Sayem was rlieved from the post of Chief Martial Law Administrator and replaced by Ziaur Rahman.

1977.04.21

President Abu Sadat Mohammad Sayem resigned and Ziaur Rahman was appointed as president.

1977.05.30

A national vote of confidence in President Ziaur Rahman

1978.06.03

Bangladeshi presidential election was won by Ziaur Rahman

1979.02.18

General Elections

The newly elected Parliament held first session, Mirza Golam Hafiz was elected Speaker

1979.04.06

Martial Law was lifted.

1979.04.15

Shah Azizur Rahman was appointed prime minister.

1981.05.30

President Ziaur Rahman was assassinated, vice president Abdus Sattar became acting president.

1981.11.15

Presidential elections were held and won by acting President Abdus Sattar. Sattar sworn in on Nov 20.

1982.03.24

Army Chief of Staff Hossain Mohammad Ershad forced president Sattar to resign, imposed martial law and declared himself Chief Martial Law Adminstrator, Parliament was dissolved, all political parties banded, and Constitution suspended.

1982.03.27

A.F.M. Ahsanuddin Chowdhury was appointed president by Ershad and sworn in.

1983.12.11

Hossain Mohammad Ershad took over President of Bangladesh.

1984.03.30

President Hossain Mohammad Ershad appointed Ataur Rahman Khan, head of Jatiya Dal Party, as Prime Minister.

1985.01.07

President Hossain Mohammad Ershad appointed a new cabinet, and it excluded all Jatiya Dal Party members

1985.03.21

A Referendum to support Ershad’s rule as president

1986.05.07

1986.07.10

The inaugural session for the newly elected Parliament elected Shamsul Huda Chowdhury as speaker, and on same day Mizanur Rahman Chowdhury elected as prime minister.

1986.10.15

Presidential Election was won by Ershad.

1986.11.10

With Seventh Amendment Act legitimated the Martial Law, President Ershad repealed the martial law and restored the 1972 Cosntitution on Nov 11.

1987.11.29

A state of emergency was declared by President Ershad.

1987.12.06

President Ershad dissolved the Parliament.

1988.03.03

General Elections

1988.03.27

A new cabinet formed with Moudud Ahmed as prime minister.

1988.04.12

State of Emergency was repealed.

1988.04.25

The first session of the fourth parliament began, and elected Shamsul Huda Chowdhury as speaker.

1989.08.12

President Ershad appointed Kazi Zafar Ahmed as prime minister and former Prime Minister Maudud Ahmed as vice president, and former Vice President A.K.M. Nurul Islam had been relieved of his post.

1990.11.28

Ershad declared another state of emergency.

1990.12.04

President Hussain Mohammed Ershad declared resignation.

1990.12.06

President Hussain Mohammed Ershad lifted the state of emgergency, dissolved the Parliament and cabinet, administered the oath of office to Supreme Court Chief Justice Shahabuddin Ahmed as vice president, then he resigned as president, thus making Shahabuddin Ahmed acting president.

General Elections

Khaleda Zia was sworn-in as the first woman prime minister of Bangladesh.

1991.04.05

First session of the fifth parliament began and elected Abdur Rahman Biswas as speaker.

1991.08.06

The Twelvth constitutional amendment was passed in the Parliament to reintroduce the parliamentary form of government in place of the presidential one.

1991.09.15

A constitutional referendum was held to lead to the reintroduction of parliamentary government.

1991.09.19

Khaleda Kia took oath as Prime Minister under new parliamentary system.

1991.10.08

Presidential election was won by Abdur Rahman Biswas and he sworn in on Oct 10.

1991.10.12

Sheikh Razzaque Ali was elected new Parliament Speaker.

1995.11.24

President Biswas dissolved the parliament and called a new election

缅甸 Myanmar

缅甸1885年完全成为不列颠属地，1897年缅甸完全成为英属印度一个省份，5月1日设立立法会议（Legislative Council of Burma）。1935年5月30日英国国会通过缅甸政府法案，达成缅甸脱离印度管辖缅甸立法议会（Legislature of Burma）由参议院（Senate）和众议院（House of Representatives）组成。1937年4月1日缅甸政府法案正式实施。1948年1月4日缅甸独立，实行多党民主议会制，联邦国会（Union Parliament， Pyidaungzu Hluttaw）由民族院（Chamber of Nationalities，Lumyozu Hluttaw）和人民院（Chamber of Deputies，Pyithu Hluttaw）组成。1962年3月，奈温发动政变，解散国会，成立革命委员会（Union Revolutionary Council）。1974年1月，颁布新宪法，成立人民议会（People’s Assembly，Pyithu Hluttaw）。1988年9月军政府上台后成立国家恢复法律和秩序委员会（State Law and Order Restoration Council），解散人民议会，废除了原有宪法。1990年5月大选后，军政府以须先制宪为由，拒绝交权。1993年1月起军政府主导的制宪国民大会（National Convention）开始举行会议，但由于缅甸主要反对党全国民主联盟与军政府分歧严重，国民大会从1996年3月开始长期休会。2004年5月17日恢复，2007年9月3日制宪国民大会闭幕，明确了制宪原则缅甸未来国名为缅甸联邦共和国，实行总统制，缅甸联邦议会（Assembly of the Union，Pyidaungsu Hluttaw）设立民族院（上院）（House of Nationalities，Amyotha Hluttaw）和人民院（下院）（House of Representatives，Pyithu Hluttaw）两院。此原则遭到反对党的抵制（包含如下条款：军队在各级议会中必须拥有２５％非选举产生的议会代表名额；三军总司令是缅甸武装力量的最高统帅，在国家陷入危机时可以接管国家政权）。2008年5月29日，军政府组织公投通过新宪法，2010年10月21日更改国名为缅甸联邦共和国，新宪法开始实施。11月7日举行首次议会选举，此后全国民主联盟领袖昂山素季被释放。2015年11月8日大选民盟获胜，2021年2月1日军方再次发动政变，宣布2020年11月8日选举结果作废，依据宪法实施紧急状态并接管政权。

A Chronology of Burma's International Relations

1897.05.01

Legislative Council of Burma was established as an advisory council to the British colonial governor, with lieutenant governor of Burma as Council Chair

1922.11.21

First Legislative Council election, with the enactment of the Montagu-Chelmsford Reforms, the Legislative Council was recast as a partially elected body

1923.01.02

The provice of Burma of British India was constituted a Governor’s Province under the Government of India Act 1919, and there’s a Council of Chiefs set up

1935.08.02

Government of Burma Act 1935 received the Royal assent, for Burma a Legislature which shall consist of His Majesty represented by the Governor, and two Chambers, to be known respectively as the Senate and the House of Representatives

1937.04.01

Burma was separated from India and was made a separately administered territory of Britain

1947.01.27

Aung San-Attlee Agreement signed, which provided for Burmese independence from Britain within one year

1947.04.09

Constituent Assembly election held

1947.06.09

The Constituent Assembly convened

1947.06.11

Thakin Nu was unanimously elected President of the Constituent Assembly

1947.06.17

The Constituent Assembly established the Union of Burma

1947.07.19

Aung San and members of his government assassinated

1947.07.30

Sao Shwe Thaik replaced Thakin Nu as President of the Constituent Assembly

1947.09.24

The Constituent Assembly adopted a constitution, and Sao Shwe Thaik was elected the provisional president on Sept 25. According to the constitution, the Union Parliament consist of the President, a Chamber of Deputies and a Chamber of Nationalities

1947.10.17

U Nu-Attlee Agreement

1947.12.10

The British parliament approved the Burma Independence Act on

1948.01.04

Burma formally achieved its independence from Britain at 4:20AM. U Mya (b. 1896, Pyawbwe) was sworn in as Speaker of the Provisional Parliament, which is Constituent Assembly has turned into

1952.03.03

General elections were held in Burma over several months between June 1951 and April 1952. On this date, Chamber of Deputies met for first time after the general election.

1952.03.05

U Mya was elected speaker of the Chamber of Deputies.

1952.03.12

Ba U was elected President of the Union of Burma

1952.03.13

Ba U sworn in as President of the Union of Burma, and former provisional president Sao Shwe Thaik was elected speaker of the Chamber of the Nationalities.

1954.02.23

Bo Hmu Aung (b. 1919.09.30 in Kyauktaga, Pegu District) was elected speaker of the Chamber of Deputies after death of U Mya in December 1953.

1956.04.27

General elections were held for Chamber of Deputies

1956.05.22

General elections were held for Chamber of Nationalities

1956.06.05

U Nu resigned as Prime Minister, and Ba Swe cabit sworn in on June 12.

1956.06.11

Bo Hmu Aung was re-elected speaker of the Chamber of Deputies

1957.02.28

Chamber of Deputies elected U Nu as new prime minister and U Nu returned to office as Prime Minister on March 1.

1957.03.11

Win Maung was elected president of the Union of Burma and took office on March 13.

1958.07.16

Bo Hmu Aung resigned as speaker of the Chamber of Deputies to take role as Deputy Premier

1958.09.26

U Nu resigned as Prime Minister and invited Army Chief of Staff Ne Win to take over as caretaker Prime Minister.

1958.10.28

Ne Win was ratified as caretaker Prime Minister by Chamber of Deputies and took office the next day.

1958.10.31

U Tin (b. 1906.02.03 in Myanaung) was elected speaker of the Chamber of Deputies

1960.02.06

General elections were held

1960.04.04

Mahn Ba Saing (b. 1907.02.05 in Youtalin Village, Henzada District) was elected speaker of the Chamber of Deputies. On same day U Nu took office as Prime Minister

1960.04.11

Sao Hkun Kyi (b. 1893.04.10 in Samka, Southern Shan States) was elected speaker of the Chamber of Nationalities

1962.03.02

Army Chief General Ne Win led a coup to overthrow U Nu government and set uo a Revolutionary Council, and on March 3 Parliament was dissolved and constitution suspended.

1962.04.30

Revolutionary Council under Ne Win announced a new national ideology called ‘The Burmese Way to Socialism’ to guide the country

1962.07.04

Burma Socialist Programme Party established with Ne Win as Party Chairman

1971.06.28-07.11

The first Party Congress of Burma Socialist Programme Party

1971.09.25

The Central Committee of BSPP announced the formation of a State Constitution Drafting Commission, headed by Brigadier San Yu as Chairman

1973.08.14

The Revoluntionary Council enacted Law Relating to Holding of National Referendum for Confirmation of the Draft Constitution of the Socialist Republic of the Union of Burma

1973.08.16

The Revoluntionary Council forms the National Referendum Commission with U Dingra Tang as Chairman

1973.10.08-21

The Second Party Congress of Burma Socialist Programme Party

1973.12.15

National Referendum on the State Constition began and lasted till December 31

1974.01.03

The Revoluntionary Council proclaimed new Constitution adopted, and it came into force on Jan 4, creating unicameral Pyithu Hluttaw (People’s Assembly)

1974.02.10

General Elections were held between Jan 27 and Feb 10

1974.03.02

The Revolutionary Council handed over power to the new Pyithu Hluttaw (People’s Assembly), and Ne Win became the Chairman of the Council of States thus president according to the new Constitution.

1974.03.04

The People’s Assembly elected the Council of Ministers, with Sein Win as Prime Minister.

1977.02.21-03.01

The Third Party Congress of Burma Socialist Programme Party.

1977.03.29

Prime Minister U Sein Win resigned and was replace by Maung Maung Kha

1978.01.15

General Elections were held between Jan 1 and Jan 15

1978.03.02

Ne Win was reelected as Chairman of the Council of States

1981.08.03-08

The Fourth Party Congress of Burma Socialist Programme Party

1981.10.18

General Elections were held between Oct 4 and Oct 18

1981.11.09

BSPP General Secretary San Yu was elected Chairman of the Council of States (President)

1985.08.02-07

The Fifth Party Congress of Burma Socialist Programme Party

1985.10.20

General Elections were held between between Oct 6 and Oct 20

1985.11.04

San Yu was reelected Chairman of the Council of States (President)

1988.07.23

BSPP Extraordinary Congress, Ne Win announced proposing a referendum on a multiparty system, and also tendering his resignation from the party chairmanship and indeed the party, and reporting San Yu resignation from President and BSPP vice-chairman. The Congress declined to endorse the referendum but accepted all resignations.

1988.07.26

The choice to fill both positions was announced as Sein Lwin, and he was elected by Party Congress as the Chairman

1988.07.27

Sein Lwin was elected by Pyithu Hluttaw as State President

1988.07.29

Maung Maung Kha stepped down as prime minister in favor of Tun Tin

1988.08.12

Sein Lwin resigned both as BSPP Chairman and State President, and Party Vice Chairman Aye Ko took acting role.

1988.08.19

Attorney Geneal Maung Maung was named State President and BSPP Chairman at emergency session of the Parliament and party leadership

1988.09.10

An Emergency BSOO Congress approved a resolution calling a multipary general election within three months, and this is endorsed by the Pyithu Hluttaw on Sept 11.

1988.09.18

Military under Chief Staff Saw Maung seized power and formed a State Law and Order Restoration Council with himself as Chairman. All state organs including the Pyithu Hluttaw were disbanded

1988.09.20

SLORC presented a new cabinet and Saw Maung was appointed Prime Minister on next day Sept 21.

1990.05.27

General Elections were held, the first multi-party election since 1960

1990.07.27

SLORC issued Order 1/90, explaining it had legitimacy to rule the nation by martial law and to exercise legislative, executive and judicial power

1992.03.20

Saw Maung turned the defense portfolio over to Than Shwe.

1992.04.23

Saw Maung stepped down as SLORC chairman and prime minister, both given to Than Shwe (prime minister’s role on April 24)

1992.04.24

The SLORC announced that the National Convention to write a new constitution will convene at an unspecified future date

1992.05.28

A Steering Committee is formed to plan the convention, with Rangoon Military Commander Lt. Gen. Myo Nyunt chair the committee

1993.01.09

The National Convention started its first session but adjourned just two days. Chairman of the National Convention Convening Commission is Lt.Gen. Myo Nyunt; chairman of the National Convention Convening Work Committee was Chief Justice U Aung Toe

1997.11.15

SLORC was reconstituted as the State Peace and Development Council with Thein Sein as chairman.

2004.05.17

The National Convention was resumed, chairman of the National Conventional Convening Commission was Lt. Gen. Thein Sein.

2007.09.03

The National Convention completes work after 14 years working out the broad outline of a “disciplined” democracy

2007.10.18

SPDC announced a commission to draft a new constitution as part of its “roadmap to democracy”, chaired by Chief Justice U Aung Toe

2008.05.10

Myanmar constitutional referendum

2008.05.29

SPDC announced the promulgation of the new constitution, which provides The Pyidaungsu Hluttaw (Assembly of the Union) composed by the Pyithu Hluttaw (House of Representatives) and the Amyotha Hluttaw (House of Nationalities)

2010.11.07

General Elections were held in accordance with the new Constitution 2008

The new Assembly was convened for the first time, Shwe Mann was elected speker of House of Representatives and Khin Anug Myint speaker of House of Nationalities.

The State Peace and Development Council is dissolved, and Thein Sein is sworn in as president.

2018.03.21

The Speaker of House of Representatives U Win Myint resigned.

Pyidaungsu Hluttaw (Union Parliament) which comprises Pyithu Hluttaw (House of Representatives) and Amyotha Hluttaw (House of Nationalities) in legislation.

尼泊尔 Nepal

尼泊尔1815年12月2日被迫签订塞格里条约，沦为不列颠保护领，1923年12月21日依据英尼两国永久和平条约获得独立。1947年5月25日拉纳首相组织宪政改革委员会（Constitution Reform Committee）并于次年4月1日实施尼泊尔政府法案，但同月30日即遭废止。直到1950年9月22日，依据1948政府法案设立的立法机构才被召集，旋即拉纳家族与皇室矛盾激化，尼泊尔国王特里布文出走印度大使馆。

1951年2月国王联合尼泊尔大会党势力，终结拉纳家族统治，4月颁布临时宪法，实行宪政。1958年2月新国王马亨德拉宣布组织宪法起草委员会（Constitution Drafting Commission），1959年2月12日颁布了第一部宪法，成立议会（Parliament，Mahasabha），由参议院（Senate，Maha Sabha）和众议院（House of Representatives，Pratinidhi Sabha）组成。1960年12月15日马亨德拉国王解散政府和议会，同时宣布停止宪法某些条款的效力。1961年1月宣布禁止一起政党活动，宣布实行无党派评议会制度（Rastriya Panchayat）。1962年12月16日颁布尼泊尔为印度教君主国的宪法。1981年5月，跟据1980年修改后的宪法规定通过直接选举的方式产生议会。1990年2月全国爆发了反对无党派政治体制的运动，同年4月8日比兰德拉国王宣布实行多党议会制，建立了民主多党制的政治体制。1990年11月9日颁布了新宪法，规定议会由众议院（下院）（House of Representatives，Pratinidhi Sabha）和国民议会（上院）（National Assembly，Rastriya Sabha）组成。2001年6月王室血案发生后，贾南德拉国王即位。2002年5月贾南德拉国王解散下院，10月4日更宣布推迟大选。2006年4月，尼主要政党组成的“七党联盟”与尼泊尔共产党（毛主义）联合发起反国王街头运动。国王妥协，4月24日宣布恢复2002年被解散的议会，5月18日国会通过法案，限制国王权利，国王只成为象征元首。2007年1月15日，尼议会颁布临时宪法，规定现议会解散，组建包含尼共（毛主义）的临时议会（Interim Legislature），并暂时中止国王权限。2008年4月10日举行制宪会议（Nepalese Constituent Assembly）选举，5月28君主制，宣布改为共和国。制宪会议直到2012年5月28日解散依然未能达成新宪法。2013年11月19日举行第二次尼泊尔制宪会议选举，2014年1月20日开幕，2015年9月16日终于通过新宪法，20日颁布实施。新宪法规定尼泊尔联邦议会（Federal Parliament of Nepal，Sanghiya Sansada Nepala）由作为咨询机关的国民议会（上议院）（National Assembly，Rastriya Sabha）和作为立法机关的众议院（下议院）（House of Representatives，Pratinidhi Sabha）组成。宪法实施后，制宪会议转变为立法议会（Legislature Parliament），直到新宪法框架下选举后为联邦议会所取代。2017年12月7日众议院选举举行，次年1月22日开始运作。国民议会由省议会选举产生以及总统提名共同组成，2018年2月正式组成。

1947.05.25

Rana Prime Minister Padma Shamsher forms Constitution Reform Committee to draft first constitution of Nepal

1948.01.26

The Government of Nepal Act 1948 was promulgated

1948.04.01

The Government of Nepal Act, 1948 took into effect

1948.04.30

Prime Minister Padma Shamsher resigned and was replaced by Mohan Shamsher, and most of the Articles of the Constitution was suspended

1950.09.22

Prime Minister Mohan Shamsher convened the legislature according to The Government of Nepal Act 1948

1950.11.06

King Tribhuvan took refuge at the Indian Embassy against the Ranas. On next day Prime Minister Mohan Shamsher crowned the three years old Gyanendra as the new king

1951.02.15

King Tribhuvan and the leading members of the Nepali Congress returned to Kathmandu

1951.02.18

King Tribhuvan announced Nepal’s first steps to democracy with a historical proclamation and a cabinet split among the Ranas and the Nepali Congress Party

1951.03.30

The Interim Government of Nepal Act 1951 was promulgated by the king

1951.04.11

The Interim Government of Nepal Act 1951 came into force

1951.11.12

Prime Minister Padma Shamsher resigned

1951.11.16

Matrika Prasad Koirala, then President of Nepali Congress, was named first commoner Prime Minister under the democratic set up

1952.08.10

Matrika Prasad Koirala resigned from the PM’s post, and King Tribhuvan formed a government under his own chairmanship, leaving the country without a prime minister

1953.06.15

Matrika Prasad Koirala was appointed as Prime Minister again.

1955.03.02

MAtrika Prasad Koirala was dismissed as Prime Minister by Mahendra whie King Tribhuvan was in medical treatment in Switzerland

1955.03.13

King Tribhvan died and Mahendra’s coronation took place the following day

1958.02.01

King Mahendra issued a Royal Proclamation to serve as the roadmap for Nepal's constitution-making process and announced the establishment of a five member Constitution Drafting Commission to prepare a new constitution, with Bhagvati Prasad Singh as its chairman

1958.03.16

The Constitution Drafting Commission was formally formed

1959.02.12

The Constitution of the Kingdom of Nepal, 1959 was promulgated by the King, providing a House of Representative and Senate

1959.02.18-04.03

First National Parliamentarty eletion got under way

1959.05.27

BP was constitutionally declared prime minister of Nepal

1959.07.24

King inaugurated the joint session of the first elected Parliament of Nepal

1960.12.15

In a self coup, King Mahendra assumed direct rule,abrogating constitution and dissolving parliament, and BP imprisoned

1962.05.08

A new Constitution Drafting Commission was created to draft a new constitution

1962.12.16

The constitution of Nepal, 1962 was promulgated and introduced the Panchayat System, with a National Panchayat, and chairman be appointed by His Majesty

1963.04.14

The first National Panchayat was inaugurated and Biswa Bandhu Thapa was elected as the Chairman

1964.07.03

Thapa resigned as Chairman of the National Panchayat, and the King brought in Rajeshwar Devkota as new Chairman

1972.01.31

King Mahendra died

1972.03.09

Rajeshwar Devkota resigned as Chairman of the National Panchayat

King Birendra made a public declaration that a referendum will be held to deicide whether introducing a multiparty system or retain the panchayat system

1980.05.02

The referendum is held and the panchayat system was retained

1990.01.15

Six different factions of the Communist Party of Nepal joined together to form a united front: United Left Front

1990.01.18-20

The Nepali Congress held a national conference and announced Feb 18 as the launching date for its non-violent pro-democracy movement against Panchayat.

1990.04.06

King Birendra removed Prime Minister Shrestha and appointed Chand Prime Minister with a promise to reform, but this failed to sway the movement

1990.04.08

The king removed the ban on political parties.

1990.04.16

The king amended 1962 constitution to accommodate multi-parry democract and dissolved the current partliament

1990.04.19

The king called on KP Bhattarai to forma an intrim coalition government to draft a new constitution and to hold national election

1990.06.01

The Constitutional Recooemdation Commission was formed to draft new constitution

1990.11.09

The Constitution of the Kingdom of Nepal, 1990 was promulgated. A legislature called Parliament was introduced which consisted of His Majesty and two Houses, namely the House of Representatives and the National Assembly

1991.05.12

First multi-party election was held and Nepali Congress General Secretary Girija Prasad Koirala was appointed Prime Minister on May 26 and the government formed on May 29.

1991.06.20

The first session of the new Parliament was opened by King Birendra, Beni Bahadur Karki was elected chairman of the National Assembly and Daman Dhungana as Speaker of the House of Representatives

Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala resigned after losing vote of confidence. On July 11 The king dissolved the House of Representatives

1994.11.15

Nepal House of Representatives election

1994.11.30

CPN-UML leader Man Mohan Adhikari was appointed Prime Minister

1994.12.17

King Birendra acted on Prime Minister’s advice to dissolve the parliament and set for fresh election on Nov 23.

1995.08.28

Chief Justice Vishwanath Upadhyay declared the dissolution unconstitutional and moved to reinstate the dissolved House of Representatives

1995.09.10

The House passed a non-trust motion against the government of Adhikari, and on next day Sher Bahadur Deuba is appointed Primie Minsiter by the King.

1999.01.15

The House of Representatives was prematurely dissolved by King Birendra and general elections were announced for May

1999.06.23

The newly elected House of Representatives elected Taranath Ranabhat as Speaker

Mohammad Mohsin was elected chairman of National Assembly

2001.11.26

King Gyanendra–Birendra’s brother, crowned following the royal massacre–declared a state of emergency in response to a spate of killings by Maoist rebels

Parliament got dissolved and set for new general election on Nov 13

King Gyanendra reinstated the old Nepal House of Representatives dissolved in 2002

A proclamation by Nepal House of Representatives stripped all the privileges and powers of King Gyanendra and declaring sovereign and supreme of the House

2006.11.21

Peace talks end with the signing of the Comprehensive Peace Accord between Prime Minister Koirala and Maoist leader Prachanda, allowing Maoists to take part in interim government and legislature

2007.01.15

An interim Constitution was approved by the parliament and replaced the Constitution of 1990. The Prime Minister will also the role of the head of state and the King has been suspended until the election of the constituent assembly. The Parliament then dissolved itself and to be replaced by the interim legislature.

The interim legislature Legislative Parliament was inaugurated and elected Subash Nembang as its speaker, as Chairperson of the Constituent Assembly respectively

Constituent Assembly election

The Constituent Assembly held its first session and voted to abolish the monarchy declaring Nepal a Federal Democratic Republic

2008.07.24

Subas Nembang, who had served as Speaker of the Legislative Parliament was elected unopposed as the Speaker of the Constituent Assembly

Legislature-Parliament Speaker Subash Chandra Nembang resigned

日本 Japan

1889年2月11日日本颁布帝国宪法，实行宪政。1890年11月29日成立帝国议会（Imperial Diet，帝国議会, Teikoku-gikai），由贵族院（House of Peers，貴族院, Kizoku-in）和众议院（House of Representatives ，衆議院, Shūgiin）组成。1945年8月日本战败后，1946年11月3日公布，1947年5月3日实施新宪法，由绝对天皇制国家变为以天皇为国家象征的议会内阁制国家。国会由众议院和参议院（House of Councillors ，参議院, Sangiin）两院组成，为最高权力机关和唯一立法机关。

斯里兰卡 Sri Lanka

锡兰1802年成为不列颠殖民地。1833年3月13日不列颠在锡兰设立立法会议。1931年4月15日多诺莫尔宪法（Donoughmore Constitution） 实施，设立国务委员会（State Council of Ceylon），成为英国殖民地里第一个拥有普选权的地区。1946年通过的索尔伯里宪法（Soulbury Constitution）规定实行两院制，议会（Parliament）由众议院（House of Representatives）和参议院（Senate）组成，据此1947年7月国务委员会解散，首次选举于8、9月间举行。1948年2月4日锡兰正式独立，宪法得以持续。1971年10月2日宪法修正案决定废除参议院。1972年5月22日议会通过共和国宪法，改国名为斯里兰卡，规定议会实行一院制的国民议会（National State Assembly）。1978年9月7日新宪法改议会制为总统制，立法机关更名为议会（Parliament）。

2015.06.26

The Parliament was dissolved for new elections.

2015.08.17

General Elections were held.

2015.09.01

First meeting of the new Parliament was held and Kari Jayasuriya was elected new Speaker of the Parliament.

2018 Sri Lankan constitutional crisis

2020.03.02

The Parliament was dissolved for new elections.

2020.08.05

General Election

1972.05 – 1978.09
