1978.09 –

Parliament

*议会

泰国 Thiland

1932年6月24日暹罗人民党发动政变，建立君主立宪政体；6月24日颁布临时宪法，规定主权归属人民和人民议会（People’s Assembly）。人民议会于28日召开，同年12月10日颁布宪法，立法机关为国民议会（National Assembly）。1939年改国名为泰国（但在1945 - 1949年间一度恢复国名为暹罗）。1946年5月9日颁布新宪法，规定国会由众议院（House of Representatives）和参议院（Senate）两院组成。泰国长期由军人实行统治，国民议会曾多次被解散。1933年4月，仅仅就职5个月的总理批耶玛诺巴功宣布解散国会，以政令代替法令；仅仅两个月后，他被批耶帕凤推翻，国会得以恢复。1946年3月比里帕侬荣救人总理后，颁布新宪法，众议院全员直选，参议院由众议院选举产生，但仅仅5个月以后比里被迫辞职。1947年11月宽·阿派旺政变上台后，颁布新宪法，设置了新的最高国务委员会（Supreme State Council），并恢复王权，参议院改为国王指定。1948年4月宽·阿派旺在政变中下台，新任总理銮披汶·颂堪于1949年1月颁布新宪法进一步扩大王权，最高国务委员会改为枢密院（Privy Council）。1951年11月銮披汶发动政变解散国会，1952年3月恢复了1932年政变后颁布的宪法，重组一院制的国民议会（National Assembly）。1957年9月沙立将军发动军事政变，并于1958年10月废除宪法和国会。1968年6月20日通过的新宪法恢复了两院制，参议院由皇室指定，参议院议长兼任国会主席。1971年11月陆军元帅他侬·吉滴卡宗发动自我政变，废除宪法，解散国会，立法权由军方的国家执行委员会（National Executive Council）行使。1972年12月他侬公布临时宪法，制定一院制的国民议会。1973年10月他侬被人民推翻后，设立新的宪法起草委员会（Constitution Drafting Committee），1974年10月5日通过的新宪法恢复了两院制，参议院恢复为由众议院选举产生。1976年10月沙鄂·差罗如政变推翻政府，废止宪法，解散国会，颁布临时宪法，成立国家行政改革委员会（National Administrative Reform Council）统治，立法权则由国家行政改革会议（National Administrative Reform Assembly）行使。1977年10月沙鄂再次政变，废止1976年临时宪法，11月颁布另一部临时宪法，组建国家立法会议（National Legislative Assembly），行使立法权和制宪权。1978年12月新宪法公布，恢复两院制，参议院议员由总理指定。1991年2月顺通·空颂蓬发动政变，推翻差猜·春哈旺内阁，废止宪法，解散国会，成立全国维持和平委员会（National Peace Keeping Council）；3月组建国家立法议会（National Legislative Assembly），行使立法权和制宪权。1997年10月11日新宪法颁布，恢复两院制，众参两院均改为直选，国会主席改为由众议院议长担任。2006年9月军方发动军事政变，推翻他信政府，宣布暂时接管国家行政权力，废除1997年宪法，解散看守政府和国会。2006年10月任命了立法议会（National Legislative Assembly），2007年1月任命了宪法起草委员会（Constitution Drafting Assembly），同年8月全民公决通过新宪法，依然保持两院制，唯参议院改为一半选举一半指定。2014年5月巴育·占奥差发布政变，推翻英拉政府，成立国家和平秩序维护委员会（National Peace and Order Maintaining Council），国会也被解散。同年7月军政府颁布临时宪法，再次组建国家立法议会（National Legislative Assembly）。2016年8月修宪公投通过，2017年4月6日颁布，保持两院制，参议院由军方指定。2019年5月大选后，国家立法议会结束，参众两院恢复，依然军方主导。

1932.06.24

Revolution led by People’s Party (Khana Ratsadon) converted the absolute monarchy to a constitutional one.

1932.06.27

A provisional constitution (Temporary Charter) was signed by King Prajadhipok. The charter stated that sovereign power belongs to the people of Siam, and a People’s Assembly, a People’s Committee are enpowered to exercise the power.

1932.06.28

The People’s Assembly met for first time and elected Phraya Manopakorn Nititada as Chairman man of the People’s Committee and Chaophraya Thammasakmontri as Speaker of the Assembly.

1932.12.10

A new constitution was adopted by the National Assembly, providing a partially elected National Assembly.

1933.04.01

King Prajadhipok pronounced the adjournment sine die of the Paraliament, the appointment of a new government and the suspension of parts of the Constitution, to response to the Pridi economic plan (The Yellow Cover Dossier). This is also calle a silent coup.

1933.06.20

Phya Phaholphonphayuhasena led a coup ousting Prime Minsiter Phraya Manopakorn Nititada (who fled to Peneng of British Malaya and died there 1948) and recalled the People’s Assembly. Phaholphonphayuhasena was appointed new Prime Minister on June 21.

1933.11.15

General Election to the National Assembly for the first time. Phya Phaholphonphayuhasena was reappointed Prime Miniser on Dec 16.

1937.11.07

General Election to the National Assembly. The National Assembly convened on Dec 10, and Phya Phaholphonphayuhasena was reappointed Prime Miniser on Dec 21.

1938.09.11

National Assembly dissolved.

1938.11.12

General Election to the National Assembly. Plaek Pibulsongkram was appointed Prime Minister on Dec 16, and his cabinet took office Dec 26.

1944.07.24

Plaek Pibulsongkram Government resigned. Khuang Aphaiwong was appointed Prime Minister on August 1.

1945.08.17

Khuang Aphaiwong and his wartime cabinet resigned and was replaced by Thawi Bunyaket on August 31.

1945.09.17

Seni Pramoj was appointed as the new Prime Minister.

1945.10.15

National Assembly dissolved.

1946.01.06

General Election to the National Assembly. (A second round on August 5) Khuang Aphaiwong was appointed Prime Minister on Jan 31.

1946.03.20

Prime Minister Khuang Aphaiwong and cabinet resigned. Pridi Banomyong was appointed Prime Minister on March 24.

1946.05.09

A new constitution promulgated, with a House of Representstives fully elected by people, and a new Senate elected by the House.

1946.08.21

Prime Minsiter Pridi Banomyong resigned. Thawan Thamrongnawasawat was selected as new Prime Minister on August 23.

1947.05.30

Thawan Thamrongnawasawat was reappointed as Prime Minister and named his cabinet on May 31.

1947.11.07

Prime Minisger Thawan Thamrongnawasawat was overthrown by military coup. Khuang Aphaiwong was appointed new Prime Minister on Nov 8.

1947.11.09

A new Constitution (temporary charter) was promulgated by the Regent Prince Chainat, thus abandon the 1946 Constitution. This new charter gave the monarch more power by reinstall a permanent Supreme State Council (later Privy Council), and the Senate became fully monarch appointed.

1948.01.29

General Election. Khuang Aphaiwong resigned on Feb 6 and was reappointed on Feb 21, and his cabiet on Feb 25.

1948.04.06

A military coup lead by same officers for 1947 coup forced Prime Minister Khuang Aphaiwong to resign, and on April 8 Plaek Pibulsongkram was appointed Prime Minister. His cabinet announced on April 15.

1949.01.23

1949 Constitution promulgated as a permanent instrument to replace the temporary 1948 Charter. This new constitution gave the monarch the most power since 1932, with Supreme State Council transformed into Privy Council selected by the throne, and Senate appointed by the monarch.

1951.11.29

A military coup put the 1949 Constitution abrogated, and the Parliament dissolved.

1952.02.26

General Election.

1952.03.08

A new constitution based on 1932 Constitution promulgated, brought back the unicameral of National Assembly, while keeping the Privy Council.

1957.02.26

General Election.

1957.09.17

Army Chief Sarit Thanarat ousted Prime Minister Plaek Pibulsongkram. On Sept 21 Pote Sarasin was appointed as Provisional Prime Minister, and his cabinet on Spet 23.

1957.12.15

General Election. On Dec 26 Pote Sarasin resigned as Prime Minster.

1958.01.01

Thanom Kittikachorn was appointed new Prime Minister.

1958.10.20

Army Chief Sarit Thanarat seized Prime Minister role for himself. With the martial law, the 1952 Constitutino abrogated, and National Assembly abolished.

1959.01.28

A temporary charter of Constitution promulgated, gave the Premier near absolute power, political partiese banned, Privy Council remained, while a Constitution Drafting Council appointed by the throne will be charge of drafting a new Constitution and also perform legislative functions.

1959.02.03

The Constitution Drafting Council opened and on Feb 6 Sut Suthisarakorn was appointed its chairman.

1959.02.09

Sarit Thanarat was voted by the Constitutial Assembly to be Prime Minister, and his cabiet on Feb 10.

1963.12.08

Prime Minister Sarit Thanarat died. Thanom Kittikachorn became new Prime Minister

1968.06.20

A new Constitution promulgated. This Constitution established a bicameral parliament, with an elected House of Representatives and a royal appointed Senate, with Senate President was President of the Parliament.

1969.02.10

General Election.

1971.11.17

Prime Minister Thanom Kittikachorn executed a coup against his own government, thereby ending the three-year experiment for parliamentary democracy. The 1968 constitution was suspended, political parties banned, and undisguised military rule imposed. Executive and legislative authority was held by a military junta, the National Executive Council, led by a triumvirate that included Thanom Praphat Charusathian, his deputy prime minister; and Thanom's son (also Praphat's son-in- law), Narong Kittikachorn.

1972.12.15

A new temporary Charter was announced by Thanom, which reinforced the military exist, and a wholly appointed unicameral National Assembly was established.

1973.10.14

The Student Movement and Popular Uprising brought 77 deaths, and Thanom Kittikachorn military cabinet resigned and Sanya Thammasak became new Prime Minister, and his cabinet appointed Oct 16.

1973.10.24

A Constitution Drafting Committee was setup with Justice Minister Prakob Hutasingha as its Chairman.

1973.12.11

King appointed members of a National Convention which selected a 299-member Nationals Assemblt on Dec 19 which in turn is to pass a new Constitution.

1974.05.21

Prime Minister Sanya Thammasak resigned, and he was reappointed on May 27, with cabinet on May 30.

1974.10.05

A new Constitution was approved by the convention and promulgated on Oct 7. It introduced with a House of Representstives fully elected by people, and a new Senate elected by the House

1975.01.26

General Election. Seni Pramoj was appointed Prime Minister on Feb 15, and his cabinet named Feb 21. Seni Pramoj sworn in on Feb 27.

1975.03.06

The coalition Government of Seni Pramoj was defeated in a confidence vote in the National Assembly, and he resigned as Prime Minister.

1975.03.14

Kukrit Pramoj was appointed new Prime Minister and his cabinet appointed on March 17.

1976.01.12

House of Representatives dissolved.

1976.04.04

General Election. Seni Pramoj was appointed Prime Minister on April 20, and his cabinet appointed April 21.

1976.10.06

Supreme Commander of the Thai Armed Forces Sangad Chalotyu ousted the civilian government of Prime Minister Seni Pramoj, martial law imposed, constitution abrogated, National Assembly dissolved, and political parties banned. A National Administrative Reform Council (NARC) was set up with Sangad as Chairman.

1976.10.08

The NARC appointed Thanin Kraivichien as the new Prime Minister, and his cabinet lineup was announced on Oct 22.

1976.10.22

The NARC released a new Constitution. It reinforced the military rule and set up Advisory Council to the King and Advisory Council to the Prime Minister, both to be appointed by the NARC. A national Administrative Reform Assembly to be appointed by the King to perfrom legislative functions.

1977.10.20

Sangad Chalotyu stagef another copt to remove Prime Minister Thanin Kraivichien and abrogate the 1976 Constitution. He led a Revolutionary Council in directly governing the country.

1977.11.10

A new temporary Constitution was promulgated. It provided for the establishment of the National Legislative Assembly with legislative functions and also drafting for new permament Constitution. The Revolutionary Council transformed into the National Policy Council and it has the power to recommend to the King to strip the Prime Minsiter of his posisiton, thus the superor power.

1977.11.11

General Kriangsak Chamanan was appointed the new Prime Minister and he named his cabiet on Nov 12.

1978.12.22

The new Constitution was promulgated. An elected House of Representatives and an appointed Senate which nominated by the Prime Minister.

1979.04.22

General Election. Kriangsak Chamanan was reappointed as Prime Minister on May 12, and his cabinet named on May 24.

1980.02.29

Prime Minister Kriangsak Chamanan resigned. Prem Tinsulanonda was named Prime Minister on March 3, and his cabinet named on March 12.

1983.03.19

National Assembly dissolved for new election.

1983.04.18

General Election. Prem Tinsulanonda was reappointed as Prime Minister on April 30, and his cabinet named on May 7.

1986.05.02

National Assembly dissolved for new election.

1986.07.27

General Election. Prem Tinsulanonda was reappointed as Prime Minister on August 5, and his cabinet named on August 11.

1988.04.29

Prime Minister Prem Tinsulanonda let National Assembly dissolved for new election.

1988.07.24

General Election. Chatichai Choonhavan was appointed Prime Minister on August 4, and his cabinet named August 9.

1990.12.09

Chatichai Choonhavan resigned as was reappointed as Prime Minister, and he made his new cabinet on Dec 14.

1991.02.23

Armed Forces led by supreme commander Sunthorn Kongsompong seized power and arrested Prime Minsiter Chatichai Choonhavan. The constitution abrogated, National Assembly dissolved, martial law enforced. A junda named National Peacekeeping Council is set up with Sunthorn as Chairman.

1991.03.01

An interim constitution was promulgated, provided a National Legislative Assembly to perform the legislative function and draft a new constitution.

1991.03.02

Anand Panyarachun was named new Prime Minister and his cabinet named on March 6.

1992.03.22

General Election. Suchinda Kraprayoon was named Prime Minister on April 7, and his cabinet named April 17.

1992.05.24

Embattled Thai Prime Minister Suchinda Kraprayoon resigned as Prime Minister amid protest. Deputy Prime Minister Meechai Ruchupan was named as acting Prime Minsiter.

1992.06.10

King appointed Anand Panyarachun as caretaker Prime Minsiter till next election. He named his cabinet on June 14.

1992.06.30

National Assembly dissolved for new election.

1992.09.13

General Election. Chuan Leekpai was appointed Prime Minister on Sept 23, and his cabinet named on Sept 29.

1994.06.09

The National Assembly established the Committee for Democrtic Development, with Prawase Wasi as its Chairman. The committee issued recommendations to the National Assembly on April 28, 1995 to amend the constitution to create a Constitution Drafting Assembly.

1995.05.19

National Assembly dissolved for new election.

1995.07.02

General Election. Banharn Silpa-archa was appointed Prime Minister on July 13, and his cabinet named on July 18.

1996.08.08

Prime Minister Banharn Silpa-archa ordered the establishment of the Political Reform Committee to draft a blueprint for political and administrative reform following the recommendations prepared by the Committee for Democratic Development. He appointed his brother, Chumphorn Silapa-acha, as Chairman for this committee. Finally the Constitution amendment was passed on Oct 22.

1996.09.21

Prime Minister Banharn Silpa-archa agreed to resign. But on Sept 27 He dissolved National Assembly for new election instead.

1996.11.17

General Election. Chavalit Yongchaiyudh was appointed Prime Minister on Nov 25 and he named his cabinet on Nov 29. The cabinet sworn in on Dec 1.

1996.12.26

The election to the Constitution Drafting Assembly was held between Dec 15 to Dec 26. Uthai Phimchaichon was elected its President on Jan 7, 1997.

1997.10.11

New Constitution promulgated, and for the first time there’s both House and Senate popular elected.

1997.11.06

Chavalit Yongchaiyudh resigned as Prime Minister. Chuan Leepkai was appointed on Nov 9 and cabinet appointed Nov 14.

2000.03.04

Senate Election. The new Senate held its first session and elected Sanit Vorapanya as its President.

2001.01.06

General Election to the House of Representatives.

2005.02.06

General Election to the House of Representatives.

2006.04.02

General Election to the House of Representatives. The election result was invalidated by the Constitution Court on May 8. New Election was set for Oct 15.

2006.04.19

Senate Election. But the Senate was never convened as 1997 Cosntitution prohibited the Senate from meeting in the absence of a House of Representatives.

2006.09.19

The armed forces dismissed the government and revoked the country's 1997 constitution and created the junta as Council for Democratic Reform (CDR).

2006.09.19

The CDR named Meechai Ruchuphan as Chairman for the legal panel to compose a new Constitution, but he resigned on Oct 1 when the interim constitution promulgated. He was replaced by Jaran Pakdithanakul.

2006.09.26

An interim charter was announced and then promulgated on Oct 1. There will be a king appointed National Legislative Assembly act as House and Senate; and a Constitution Drafting Assembly selected by Council for Democratic Reform.

2007.01.01

The Constitution Drafting Assembly member was appointed by the King, and on Jan 8 Noranit Setabutr was elected its Chairman.

2007.01.22

The Constitution Drafting Committee (under CDA) was appointed, and on Jan 25 Prasong Soonsiri was elected Chairman.

2007.07.06

The Constitution Drafting Assembly approved a final draft of a new constitution, paving the way for an August 19 constitutional referendum.

2007.08.19

Constitutional referendum. The new Constitution came into force on August 24, with now Senate will be half elected and half appointed.

2007.12.23

General Election to the House of Representatives.

2008.03.02

Senate Election. The Senate met for first time on Match 14 and Prasobsook Boondech elected new Senate President.

2011.04.12

The Senate renewed its appointed members. On May 4 Teeradej Meepien was appointed new Senate President.

2011.05.10

The House of Representatives was dissolved.

2011.07.03

General Election to the House of Representatives.

2012.07.25

Teeradej Meepien was disqualified as Senate President when he was sentenced to a suspended jail sentence.

2012.08.14

Nikom Wairatphanich was elected new Senate President.

2013.12.09

The House of Representatives was dissolved.

2014.02.02

General Election to the House of Representatives. This election was nullified by Constitutional Court on March 21.

2014.03.20

Senate Speaker Nikom Wairatphanich was suspended due to The National Anti-Corruption Commission recommendation about his impeachment. Deputy Spealer Surachai Liangboonlertchai took over acting his role.

2014.03.29

Senate Election.

2014.05.08

Surachai Liangboonlertchai was elected new Speaker but before King appointment the coup dissolved the Senate.

2014.05.20

Royal Thai Army commander Prayut Chan-o-cha imposed martial law and established a Peace and Order Maintaining Command with himself as its commander.

2014.05.22

Prayut announced army assuming control and established junta National Council for Peace and Order (NCPO). The 2007 Constitution partial repealed, and caretaker government dissolved.

2014.05.22

The NCPO dissolved the Senate.

2014.07.22

An Interim Constitution was signed and took into effect. The interim constitution provided for the establishment of the National Legislative Assembly to exercise legislative power, a provisional cabinet to take charge of public administration, the National Reform Council to execute extensive national reforms and approve a draft new constitution, and a Constitution Committee to draft the new constitution.

2014.07.31

Member to the National Legislative Assembly was appointed.

2014.08.07

The National Legislative Assembly officially opened and on August 8 first meeting Pornpetch Wichitcholchai was elected President.

2014.10.06

Members to the National Reform Council was appointed.

2014.10.21

The National Reform Council convened its first meeting and elected Thienchay Kiranandana as its Chairman.

2014.11.04

Borwornsak Uwanno was handicked by NCPO as chairman of the Constitution Drafting Committee (CDC).

2015.08.06

The National Reform Council rejected the CDC Cosntitution draft submitted on August 29, thus according to the 2014 interim Constitution both the NRC and the CDC are dissolved and to be replaced by a new CDC.

2015.10.05

The NCPO appointed a new Constitution Drafting Committee headed by Meechai Ruchupan.

2016.08.07

Constitutional referendum.

2017.04.06

New Constitution ratifiled. It provided The National Assembly consisting of the House of Representatives and the Senate. The House members are comsposed of constituency electied and party list; while the Senate composed of 250 military-appointed members.

2019.03.24

General Election to the House of Representatives.

2019.05.07

The National Legislative Assembly's last meeting, before the official termination of its duties on May 21, 2019, when the new National Assembly opened.

2019.05.24

The newly elected Parliament was officially opened by King. Pornpetch Wichitcholchai was elected President of the Senate on same day. Chuan Leekpai was elected Speaker of the House of Representatives in its first session on 25 May.

文莱 Brunei

文莱1888年9月17日签订条约，成为不列颠保护领。1907年6月29日设置文莱国务委员会（Brunei State Council）。1953年5月15日设立文莱宪法建议委员会（Brunei Constitutional Advisory Committee， Tujuh Serangkai）负责起草宪法。1959年9月29日颁布宪法，开始实行宪政，国务委员会撤销，设立立法院（Legislative Council of Brunei，Majlis Mesyuarat Negara Brunei）。1962年8月曾举行文莱史上首次选举，12月文莱人民党叛乱，立法会被解散，取而代之以紧急委员会（Emergency Council ，Majlis Darurat），直至1963年7月。1970年取消立法会选举，全体议员改由苏丹任命。1984年1月1日文莱获得独立。1984年2月13日，苏丹宣布终止立法会，立法以苏丹圣训方式颁布。2004年7月，苏丹宣布重开立法会。9月25日立法会恢复运作。

http://pelitabrunei.gov.bn/SitePages/Arkib.aspx

government newspaper

1847.05.27

Britain and Brunei signed a Treaty of Friendship and Commerce, thus the beginning of British to control extermal affairs.

1888.09.17

British-Brunei Protectorate Treaty. surrendered jurisdiction over foreign relations to Britain but managed to keep a fully independent state internally with the traditional State Council running the administration.

1905.12.03

Brunei Sultan stamped his seal to the new Supplementary Agreement to the Protectorate Treaty, introducing residency system and thus executive authorities also gave to British.

1906.01.02

British High Commissioner in Malaya Sir John Anderson arrived in Brunei to complete the Agreement on behalf of the British Government.

1907.06.29

Brunei State Council first meeting took place.

1953.05.15

A Brunei Constitutional Advisory Committee was appointed (known as the Tujuh Serangkai) to prepare for Brunei Constitution. The committee Chairman was Yang Amat Mulia Pengiran Maharaja Lela Pengiran Muda Abdul Kahar bin Pengiran Pemancha Pengiran Anak Mohd Yasin.

1959.09.29

The Cosntitution was agreed with British and promulgated by Sultan Omar Ali. The old State Council was revoked and replaced by an Executive Council and a Legislative Council, internal self governance granted, and British Residency replaced by a High Commissioner.

1959.10.21

First sitting of the Legislative Council.

1962.08.31

First ever direct election to District Councils, which set to elect Legislative Council members among District Council councillors themselves.

1962.12.08

Parti Rakyat Brunei (PRB) lead a rebellion to against the Malaya Merger plan, and a state of emergency was proclaimed by the Sultan on Dec 12.

1962.12.19

The Legislatve Council was dissolved and on next day an Emergency Council (Majlis Darurat) was established with Sultan Omar Ali as the chairperson; also, an Emergency Executive Committee (Jawatankuasa Kerja Darurat) temporarily replaced the Executive Council (Majlis Mesyuarat Kerajaan) with the Chief Minister (Menteri Besar) Dato Marsal bin Manu as its chairperson. The rule of the Emergency Council lasted till July 23, 1963.

1965.01.06

The Brunei Constitution was amended to provide for general election to the Legislative Council, and the Executive Council was renamed Council of Ministers.

1965.03.20

General Election to the Legislative Council was held for last time.

1970.04.12

The Emergency Order made the composition of the Legislative Council entirely appointed.

1984.02.13

The Legislative Council was dissolved by Sultan Bolkiah.

2004.09.25

The Legislative Council was reinstated by Sultan Bolkiah.

Dewan Undangan Negara Brunei

新加坡 Singapore

新加坡1824年成为不列颠属地，1826年归属海峡殖民地（1867年海峡殖民地脱离印度管控成为直辖殖民地）。1867年4月1日海峡殖民地设置立法会议（Legislative Council）。1946年4月海峡殖民地解体，

1948年3月1日不列颠在新加坡实施新的枢密令，设立立法会议（Legislative Council of Singapore）。1955年2月8日伦代尔宪法（Rendel Constitution）实现了立法议会的部分民选，1958年11月27日实现全部民选。1963年9月16日马来西亚成立，新加坡加入马来西亚，脱离不列颠。 1965年8月9日脱离马来西亚独立，12月22日州宪法经修改成为新加坡共和国宪法，立法议会改称国会（Parliament of Singapore）。

1867.02.04

Letter Patent provided the Straits Settlements Colony a colonial constitution that to establish a Legislative Council of the Straits Settlements.

1867.04.01

The Legislative Council of the Straits Settlements formed and member took oath, when the Straits Settlements (comprising Singapore, Penang and Malacca) became a crown colony.

1946.03.26

Straits Settlements (Repeal) Act, 1946 received royal assent.

1946.03.27

The Singapor Order-in-Council provided for the appointment of a Governor and the eventual establishment of an Executive Council and a Legislative Council.

1946.04.01

The Straits Settlements was dissolved, Singapore together with the Cocos-Keeling and Christmas islands, became a separate crown colony, while Penang and Malacca joined the new Malayan Union. (Labuan was briefly annexed to Singapore before becoming a part of the new colony of British North Borneo on July 15, 1946.)

1947.07.18

The Legislative Council Election Ordinance enacted which introduce general election for the first time, based on the report of the Reconstitution Committee chaired by Singapore Colonial Secretary Patrick A. B. McKerron.

1948.03.01

The new constitution came into effect, with significant changes to introduce democratic elections.

1948.03.20

First ever general election to elect six members to the Legislative Council.

1948.04.01

First Legislative Council first meeting.

1951.04.10

General election to the Legislative Council.

1951.04.17

Second Legislative Council first meeting.

1951.09.22

Singapore was proclaimed a City of the British Commonwealth by a royal charter, and this day as official ceremony.

1953.07.21

A constitutional Commission headed by Sir George Rendel was set up, and their report was made official on Feb 22, 1954.

1954.07.29

George Oehlers was appointed by Governor John Nicoll to be first Speaker of the Lesiglative Assembly next year when LA was set up.

1955.02.08

The Rendel Constitution came into effect, introducing a single chamber Lesiglative Assembly with 2/3 of members popularly elected.

1955

Election Day: April 2, 1955

First Session Day: April 22, 1955

Dissolution Day: March 31, 1959

1955.04.02

First Legislative Assembly general election.

1955.04.06

David Marshall was appointed first Chief Minister, and his cabinet sworn in on April 7.

1955.04.22

The Legislative Assembly started its first session, and George Oehlers was officially Speaker.

1956.06.07

David Marshall resigned as Chief Minister and Lim Yew Hock was asked to take over. He accepted and named his cabinet (no change) on June 8.

1958.08.01

The State of Singapore Bill receiveied royal assent, and Singapore's status was changed from a colony to a state.

1958.11.27

The Singapore (Constitution) Order-in-Council was enacted and it created the position of a Yang di-Pertuan Negara as the constitutional head of state, a prime minister and a 51-elected member Legislative Assembly.

1959.06.03

The State of Singapore Constitution took into force by proclamation and Governor William Goode swore in as Yang di-Pertuan Negaram, the head of state.

1959

Election Day: May 30, 1959

First Session Day: July 1, 1959, George Oehlers reelected as Speaker.

Dissolution Day: Sept 3, 1963

1959.06.05

Lee Kuan Yew was installed as first Prime Minister of Singapore and sworn in with his cabinet.

1959.12.03

Yusof bin Ishak was appointed Yang di-Pertuan Negaram, the head of state, replacing William Goode.

1963.09.16

Malaysia was formed, and consisted of the Federation of Malaya, Singapore, Sarawak and North Borneo (now Sabah).

1963

Election Day: Sept 21, 1963

First Session Day: Oct 22, 1963, Edmund William Barker elected Speaker. He was appointed Minister for Law in the new Lee cabinet on Oct 29, 1964 and resigned as Speaker on Oct 31, 1964. Arumugam Ponnu Rajah was elected Spekaer on Nov 2, 1964, and he was appointed High Cimmissioner to London in 1966 so resigned as Speaker on August 5, 1966. Punch Coomaraswamy was elected new Speaker on August 17, 1966.

Dissolution Day: Feb 8, 1968

1963.10.19

Lee Kuan Yew formed a new cabinet.

1963.12.04

The Yang di-Pertuan Agong of the Federation of Malaysia, on the advice of the Singapore State Government, appointed Tun Yusof bin Ishak to be the Yang di-Pertuan Negara of the State of Singapore.

1965.08.09

The proclamation declaring Singapore’s independence was announced, and The Malaysian Prime Minister simultaneously announced the separation of Singapore from Malaysia. Constitution of Malaysia (Singapore Amendment) Bill, 1965 was passed and enacted on the same day.

1965.12.22

The Republic of Singapore Independence Act 1965 was passed and made retrospective to 9 August 1965, with Yusof bin Ishak as President and Legislative Assembly was renamed the Parliament of Singapore from that date.

1967.11.30

Yusof bin Ishak was reelected by Parliament as President and he sworn in on Dec 4.

1968

Election Day: April 13, 1968

First Session Day: May 6, 1968, Punch Coomaraswamy reelected Speaker, and he was appointed High Commissioner to India so resigned on Jan 19, 1970. Yeoh Ghim Seng was elected Speaker on Jan 27, 1970.

Dissolution Day: August 16, 1972

1968.04.16

Lee Kuan Yew formed a new cabinet.

1970.11.23

President Yusof bin Ishak died in office. The Speaker of Parliament, Yeoh Ghim Seng, was installed by Parliament as acting president.

1970.12.30

Benjamin Henry Sheares was elected President and he took office on Jan 2, 1971.

1972

Election Day: Sept 2, 1972

First Session Day: Oct 12, 1972, Yeoh Ghim Seng was reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: Dec 6, 1976

1972.09.16

Lee Kuan Yew formed a new cabinet.

1974.11.06

Benjamin Henry Sheares was reelected President and he took office on Jan 2, 1975.

1976

Election Day: Dec 23, 1976

First Session Day: Feb 7, 1977, Yeoh Ghim Seng was reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: Dec 5, 1980

1976.12.31

Lee Kuan Yew formed a new cabinet.

1978.12.29

Benjamin Henry Sheares was reelected President and he took office on Dec 30, 1978.

1980

Election Day: Dec 23, 1980

First Session Day: Feb 3, 1981, Yeoh Ghim Seng was reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: Dec 4, 1984

1981.01.06

Lee Kuan Yew formed a new cabinet.

1981.05.12

President Benjamin Henry Sheares died in office. The Speaker Yeoh Ghim Seng was again installed by Parliament as acting president.

1981.10.23

C.V. Devan Nair was elected Presidenrt and he took office on Oct. 24.

1984

Election Day: Dec 22, 1984

First Session Day: Feb 25, 1985, Yeoh Ghim Seng was reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: August 17, 1988

1985.01.02

Lee Kuan Yew formed a new cabinet.

1985.03.28

President C.V. Devan Nair resigned. Chief Justice Wee Chong Jin was installed by Parliament as acting president until 29 March when he was replaced by Speaker of the Parliament Yeoh Ghim Seng

1985.08.30

Wee Kim Wee was elected President and he took office on Sept 2.

1988

Election Day: Sept 3, 1988

First Session Day: Jan 9, 1989, Tan Soo Khoon was elected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: August 14, 1991

1988.09.13

Lee Kuan Yew formed a new cabinet.

1989.08.31

Wee Kim Wee was reelected President and he took office on Sept 2.

1990.11.26

Prime Minister Lee Kuan Yew announced his resignation. President asked Goh Chok Tong to form a new cabinet which sworn in on Nov 28.

1991

Election Day: August 31, 1991

First Session Day: Jan 2, 1992, Tan Soo Khoon was reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: Dec 16, 1996

1991.09.07

Goh Chok Tong formed a new cabinet.

1991.11.30

Legislation on direct election of President came into effect.

1993.08.28

First direct presidential election won by Ong Teng Cheong and he took office on Sept. 1.

1997

Election Day: Jan 2, 1997

First Session Day: May 26, 1997, Tan Soo Khoon was reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: Oct 18, 2001

1997.01.25

Goh Chok Tong formed a new cabinet.

2001

Election Day: Nov 3, 2001

First Session Day: March 25, 2002, Abdullah Tarmugi was elected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: April 20, 2006

2001.01.23

Goh Chok Tong formed a new cabinet.

2004.08.10

Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong resigns. Lee Hsien Loong is sworn in as prime minister on August 12.

2006

Election Day: May 6, 2006

First Session Day: Nov 2, 2006, Abdullah Tarmugi was reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day: April 19, 2011

2006.05.30

Lee Hsien Loong formed a new cabinet and sworn in.

2010

Election Day: May 7, 2011

First Session Day: Oct 10, 2011, Michael Palmer was elected Speaker, and he resigned on Dec 12, 2012. Halimah Yacob was elected Speaker on Jan 14, 2013.

Dissolution Day: August 25, 2015

2011.05.21

Lee Hsien Loong formed a new cabinet and sworn in.

2015

Election Day: Sept 11, 2015

First Session Day: Jan 16, 2016, Halimah Yacob was reelected Speaker, and She resigned on August 7, 2017 to stand for presidential election. Tan Chuan-Jin was elected Speaker on Sept 11, 2017.

Dissolution Day: June 23, 2020

Lee Hsien Loong formed a new cabinet and sworn in.

2020

First Session Day: August 24, 2020, Tan Chuan-Jin reelected Speaker.

Dissolution Day:

2020.07.27

Lee Hsien Loong formed a new cabinet and sworn in.

新加坡原为不列颠属地，1948年不列颠在新加坡设立立法议会。1955年Rendel Constitution实现了立法议会的民选。1963年新加坡脱离不列颠，加入马来西亚。 1965年8月脱离马来西亚独立，12月22日州宪法经修改成为新加坡共和国宪法，立法议会改称国会。

印度 India

印度地区（包括今印度、巴基斯坦和孟加拉国）自1600年东印度公司成立以来逐步成为不列颠属地。1853年8月根据特权法案不列颠在印度设立立法会议（Legislative Council）。1857年反英起义后，1858年英国废黜莫卧儿王朝，撤销东印度公司，印度改由英国政府直接统治。根据1919年12月的印度政府法案，立法分为立法会议（Legislative Assembly）和国务会议（Council of States），印度人获得一部分权力。1946年12月制宪议会（Constituent Assembly）召开，1947年8月15日印度独立，立法会议和国务会议结束，制宪议会同时拥有立法权。1949年11月26日新宪法通过，1950年1月26日生效，联邦议会（Parliament，Bharatiya Sansad）为两院制，包括联邦院（Council of States，Rajya Sabha）和人民院（House of the People，Lok Sabha），首次大选于1951-1952年举行。

1773.06.21

Regulating Act of 1773 came into law (Royal assent on June 10), provided for a Governor and a Council consisting of 4 members for the administration of Bengal.

1783.08.13

Pitt’s India Act came into law, provided a powerful Governor-General and a Board of Control in London to supervise the administration of India.

1834.04.22

Charter Act of 1833 came into force (Royal Assent on Aug 28, 1833), completely centralized administration in India, and the Governor-General in Council could make Acts for all over India.

1853.08.20

Charter Act of 1853 received royal assent after passing the Commons on July 29 and the Lords on August 12. This act separated the executive from the Legislative powers and for the first time a Legislative Council was established.

1858.11.01

Government of India Act of 1858 proclaimed (Royal Assent on August 2), the post of Secretary of State for India was created with a Council of India, while abolished East India Company, the Company's Court of Directors and the Home Government's Board of Control.

1861.08.01

The Indian Councils Act of 1861 received Royal Assent, allowing Indians to become members of the Council, to be nominated by the Governor-General.

1919.12.23

The Government of India Act of 1919 received Royal Assent (passed in Parliament Dec 18), the Central Legislature was divided into the Legislative Assembly and the Council of States.

1921.02.03

Frederick Whyte was appointed by the Governor-General as the first President of the Legislative Assembly, and Alexander Phillips Muddiman was appointed to work as the President of the Council of State.

1925.08.24

Vithalbhai Patel was elected President of the Legislative Assembly.

1930.04.25

Vithalbhai Patel resigned as President of the Legislative Assembly.

1930.07.09

Maulvi Muhammad Yakub was elected as President of the Legislative Assembly.

1930.07.31

Presidenr Maulvi Muhammad Yakub term expired with the expiry of the term of the Legislative Assembly.

1931.01.17

Ibrahim Rahimtoola elected President of the Legislative Assembly.

1933.03.07

Ibrahim Rahimtoola resigned as President of the Legislative Assembly.

1933.03.14

The Legislative Assembly unanimously elected R. K. Shanmukham Chetty as its President.

1934.12.31

President R. K. Shanmukham Chetty term expired with the expiry of the term of the Legislative Assembly.

1935.01.24

Sir Abdur Rahim elected President of the Legislative Assembly.

1945.10.01

President Sir Abdur Rahim Chetty term expired with the expiry of the term of the Legislative Assembly.

1946.01.24

Ganesh Vasudev Mavalankar elected President of the Legislative Assembly.

1946.12.06

Constituent Assembly of India was officially formed.

1946.09.02

The Interim Government of India led by Jawaharlal Nehru was formed.

1946.12.09

The first meeting of Constituent Assembly of India, Sachchidananda Sinha was appointed temporary Chairman of the Assembly.

1946.12.11

Rajendra Prasad was eleceted Chairman of the Consituent Assembly.

1947.07.18

Indian Independence Act 1947 received Royal Assent.

1947.08.14

The Legislative Assembly and the Council of State dissolved after India independence, and the Constituent Assembly was empowered to function also as a sovereign legislature of the country.

1947.08.15

India achieved independence, and Jawaharlal Nehru sworn in as Prime Minister.

1947.08.29

Bhimrao Ramji Ambedkar was appointed Constitution Drafting Committee Chairman of the Constituent Assembly.

1947.08.29

The Consituent Assembly resolved that the business of the Assembly as a constitution-making body should be clearly distinguished from its functions as the Dominion Legislature, and a Spekaer should be elected to preside over the Assembly for the latter capacity.

1947.11.17

Ganesh Vasudev Mavalankar was nominated Speaker of the Constituent Assembly (Legislative) when this ordinary law-making function performed in first meeting of the first session. Rajendra Prasad vacated the Chairmanship which was then occupied by Speaker Mavalankar.

1949.11.26

Constitution of India passed and adopted by the Constituent Assembly, providing Parliament for the Union which shall consists of the President and two Houses to be known respectively as the Council of States (Rajya Sabha) and the House of the People (Lok Sabha).

1950.01.20

Ganesh Vasudev Mavalankar was elected Speaker of the Provisional Parliament.

1950.01.24

Last meeting of the Constituent Assembly, and Rajendra Prasad was elected President of India. He took office on Jan 26.

1950.01.26

Constitution of India came into force, and the Constituent Assembly became the Provisional Parliament of India, and Mavalankar took office as Speaker.

1950.01.26

Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru sworn in.

1952.02.21

First election to the Lok Sabha held from Oct 25, 1951 to Feb 21, 1952.

1952.04.15

Jawaharlal Nehru sworn in as Prime Minister after the genral election.

1952.04.17

The Lok Sabha (House of the People) was duly constituted for the first time, Ganesh Vasudev Mavalankar as Speaker pro tem.

1952.05.02

Rajandra Prasad was elected President and sworn in on May 13.

1952.05.13

The first Session of the First Lok Sabha commenced, Bhubanananda Das as Speaker pro tem.

1952.05.13

New cabinet of Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru sworn in.

1952.05.15

Ganesh Vasudev Mavalankar elected first Speaker of the Lok Sabha.

1956.02.27

Lok Sabha Speaker Ganesh Vasudev Mavalankar died.

1956.03.08

M. A. Ayyangar was unanimously elected Speaker of the Lok Sabha. (Sardar Hukam Singh was appointed on March 7 as Speaker pro tem as Ayyangar resigned as Deputy Speaker to prepare for election for Speaker)

1957.04.04

First Lok Sabha dissolved by President.

1957.03.14

General Election held between 24 February to 14 March 1957.

Constituted: April 5, 1957

First Sitting: May 10, 1957, Seth Govind Das as Speaker pro tem.

Speaker: M. A. Ayyangar elected May 11, 1957

Dissolved: March 31, 1962.

1957.04.17

New cabinet of Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru sworn in.

1957.05.06

Rajendra Prasad was reelected President and sworn in on May 13.

1962

General Election held between 19 to 25 February 1962.

Constituted: April 2, 1962

First Sitting: April 16, 1962, Seth Govind Das as Speaker pro tem.

Speaker: Sardar Hukam Singh elected April 17, 1962

Dissolved: March 3, 1967

1964.05.27

Lal Bahadur Shastri became Prime Minister.

1966.01.11

锡金Sikkim

锡金1861年成为不列颠保护领，1947年后成为印度保护领。1953年3月23日成立国务会议（State Council），作为咨询机关。1973年1月选举后骚动不断，5月8日在印度调停下达成协议，原则上同意实施宪政，建立锡金立法议会（Sikkim Legislative Assembly）。1974年4月13日举行选举，议会5月10日开幕。6月20日，锡金议会通过了由印度拟定的政府法案，规定印度政府派驻的首席执行官为政府首脑和议会议长，7月4日新宪法通过，为锡金并入印度铺平道路。1975年4月10日，锡金议会通过决议废黜国王及君主制，把锡金变为印度的一个邦，4月14日全民公决通过，5月16日锡金正式成为印度的一个邦。锡金议会成为邦议会（Sikkim Legislative Assembly）。

*国务会议 1974.6.20 - 1975.5.16

印度尼西亚 Indonesia

东印度群岛，1619年荷兰东印度公司占领，1800年成为荷属东印度。1916年12月荷兰议会批准在东印度成立所谓人民议会（People's Council，Volksraad），赋予在立法方面给予总督建议的职责，1918年5月18日正式成立，1942年日本占领东印度后停止活动。1945年3月1日日本占领当局组织了独立筹备工作调查委员会（Investigating Committee for Preparatory Work for Independence，Badan Penyelidik Usaha-usaha Persiapan Kemerdekaan），8月7日又批准了印度尼西亚独立筹备委员会（Preparatory Committee for Indonesian Independence，Panitia Persiapan Kemerdekaan Indonesia），由苏加诺出任主席。日本战败投降后，1945年8月17日苏加诺单方面宣布独立，改称印度尼西亚。根据8月18日印尼独立筹备委员会通过的宪法，人民协商会议（People’s Consultative Assembly，Majelis Permusyawaratan Rakyat）为最高权力机关，人民代表会议（People’s Representative Council，Dewan Perwakilan Rakyat）是立法机关，两者共同构成具有印尼特色的代议制度，同时规定在上述国家机构正式组建之前，会成立一个民族委员会（National Committee，Komite Nasional），和总统共同行使权力。1945年8月29日，组建了中央民族委员会（Central Indonesian National Committee，Komite Nasional Indonesia Pusat），10月16日规定该委员会享有立法权，直至人民协商会议和人民代表会议建立。1949年12月27日荷兰当局将主权移交新成立的印度尼西亚联邦共和国（United States of Indonesia），联邦宪法随即生效，规定国会（Parliament）由参议院（上院）（Senate，Senat）和人民代表会议（下院）（People’s Representative Council，Dewan Perwakilan Rakyat）组成。1950年5月印度尼西亚联邦共和国和印度尼西亚共和国达成合并意向，并制定了临时宪法，组建临时国会（Provisional People's Representative Council，Dewan Perwakilan Rakyat Sementara），由中央民族委员会和印度尼西亚联邦共和国下院成员组成，并规定组建制宪会议（Constitutional Assembly，Konstituante Republik Indonesia）制定宪法。1950年8月17日印度尼西亚共和国正式成立。1955年9月人民代表会议选举，1956年3月就职；1955年12月制宪会议选举，1956年11月就职。宪法起草工作一直陷于停滞，因此苏加诺总统1959年7月5日颁布法令，解散制宪议会，恢复1945年宪法。由此，1960年9月15日建立起第一个临时人民协商会议（Provisional People's Consultative Assembly，Majelis Permusyawaratan Rakyat Sementara）。与此同时，原国会继续工作，凡支持恢复1945年宪法者议员均可留任。1960年3月5日，苏加诺命令国会停止活动，6月25日组建合作国会（Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council，Dewan Perwakilan Rakyat Gotong Royong）。这些机构在1965年九三十事件后均得以保留。1971年7月，首次真正选举产生人民协商会议和人民代表会议。2001年11月9日宪法修正案通过，2004年10月新建立了地方代表理事会（Regional Representative Council，Dewan Perwakilan Daerah），作为上院存在。人民代表会议（国会）和地方代表理事会共同组成人民协商会议。

1916.12.16

The Dutch parliament approved the creation of the Volksraad, or 'People's Council', in the East Indies, which was ro advice the Governor-General on legislative and financial matters, with a chairman appointed by the King, and a College of Delegates (College van Gedelegeerden), subseqyently called ‘Legislative Council’, the permanat body was also established.

1917.08.01

Volkraad establishment provided in Article 53 to Article 80 Section Two Indische Staatsregelling, Wet op de Staatsinrichting van Nederlandsh-Indie (Indies Staatsregeling/Dutch East Indies Constitution) came into effect.

1917.10.16

First Dutch East Indies Volksraad election.

1918.05.18

Governor General Johan Paul Graaf van Limburg Stirum, on behalf of the Dutch government, established and inaugurated the Volksraad.

Voorzitter van de Volksraad (Chairman of the Volksraad)

  1. Jacob Christiaan Koningsberger (1918.01.01-1919.09.03)
  2. Willem Martinus Godfried Schumann (1919.09.03-1925.05.06)
  3. Adriaan Neytzel de Wilde (1925.05.06-1929.05.03)
  4. Jan Willem Meyer Ranneft (1929.05.03-1933.04.26)
  5. Henricus Johannes Spit (1933.05.18-1935.03.24)
  6. Willem Henri van Helsdingen (1935.05.18-1939.04.18)
  7. Jan Anne Jonkman (1939.04.27-1942.03.08)

1918.05.21

First meeting of the Volkseaad.

1942.02.27

The last meeting of the Volksraad took place.

1942.03.08

Volksraad ceased to exist when Dutch surrendered to Japan.

1945.03.01

Japanese ocuparion 16th Atmy announced the establishment of Investigating Committee for Preparatory Work for Independence (Badan Penyelidik Usaha-usaha Persiapan Kemerdekaan), and chairman is Radjiman Wediodiningrat.

1945.03.24

Sumatran Central Advisory Cocuncil (Chuo Sangi In) was announced to be set up and by end of May Mohammad Sjafei was appointed Chairman.

1945.07.25

Mohammad Sjafei is appointed Chairman of the Committee to Investigate the Preparation of Independence.

1945.08.07

Japanese Southern Area Commander Hisaichi Terauchi gave permission for the Preparatory Committee for Indonesian Independence (Panitia Persiapan Kemerdekaan Indonesia).

1945.08.09

Sukarno was appointed Chairman of the Preparatory Committee for Indonesian Independence.

1945.08.17

Sukarno declared independence of Indonesia.

1945.08.18

the Preparatory Committee for Indonesian Independence approved The Constitution of the Republic of Indonesia drafter by the Investigating Committee, for a six-month transition period, the new republic would be governed by a president, assisted by a National Committee, which would establish the two chamber legislatures mandated by the constitution. Sukarno was elected as president and Hatta as vice-president.

1945.08.29

Sukarno dissolved the Preparatory Committee for Indonesian Independence (PPKI) and established the Central Indonesian National Committee (Komite Nasional Indonesia Pusat, KNIP). At the first session Kasman Singodimedjo was elected Chairman.

1945.10.16

Vice-Presidential Edict No.X transferring the powers the Constitution conferred on the People’s Consultative Assembly and People’s Representative Council from the President to the KNIP, making the government more parliamentary in nature.

1945.10.16

Kasman Singodimedjo was removed from his position as KNIP Chairman at its second plenary session, and his place taken temporarily by Adam Malik.

1945.10.17

The Executive Committee of the KNIP was established with Sutan Sjahrir as Committee Chairman.

1945.11.11

KNIP, in its penary session, decided to assign Sutan Sjahrir wit the formation of first parliamentary cabinet, and his cabiet was announced on Nov 14.

1945.11.27

During the KNIP session, Soepeno was elected KNIP and its Working Committee Chairman.

1946.02.28

Sutan Sjahrir cabinet resigned and he was asked to form a new cabinet, which was set up by March 12.

1946.03.03

In the KNIP session between Feb 28 and March 3, Assaat was elected KNIP and its Working Committee Chairman.

1946.06.27

Premier Sjahrir was kidnapped by forces that believed the government has betrayedthe ideals of total independence.

1946.06.28

President Sukarno issued a degree to take control of the government and return Indonesia to a presidential system and dissolve the cabinet.

1946.07.03

Sutan Sjahrir was released and his kidnappers arrested.

1946.10.02

Sutan Sjahrir was asked to form a new government on July 25 and the cabinet was announced on Oct 2. On the same day President Sukarno delegated his full executive powers to the new cabinet. The new cabinet was officialy inaugurated on Oct 5.

1947.03.03

During new Session of KNIP between Feb 25 and March 5, it is expanded on March 2. On March 3 a new Working Committee was elected with Assaat reelected as Chairman.

1947.06.27

Premier Sutan Sjahrir handed his resignation to President Sukarno, who once again announced a state of emergency.

1947.07.03

Amir Sjarifuddin was appointed Prime Miniter, and there’s a cabinet reshuffle to include the Masyumi Party on Nov 11.

1948.01.23

Amir Sjarifuddin resigned after losing support of major coalition parties due to the Renville Agreement. On the same day Presidenr Sukarno asked Vice President Hatta to form a National Government.

1948.01.29

Hatta Cabinet was formed and formally took office on Feb 2.

1948.12.19

Dutch Operation Kraai attacked Republic of Indonesia capital Yogyakarta, President Sukarno and the Cabinet were captured and exiled.

1948.12.19

Former Prime Minister Amir Sjarifuddin, who plotted Madiun Affair on Sept 18 and was arrested by the Republic Army on Dec 4., was killed during Dutch attack afraid of their escape.

1948.12.23

Finance Minister Sjafruddin Prawiranegara broadcasted to eatabmish the Emergency Government of the Republic of Indonesia (Pemerintahan Darurat Republik Indonesia) and cabinet in the city of Bukittinggi.

1949.05.07

Agreement are made between the Netherlands and Indonesian Republicans to agree on major issues before Round Table Conference to discuss Indonesia’s independence.

1949.07.06

Republican leaders Sukarno and Hatta released.

1949.07.13

Sjafruddin Prawiranegara handed back the mandate to President Sukarno and the Republican cabinet led by Hatta resumed function.

1949.08.02

All component authorities of the future United States of Indonesia held a Inter-Indonesian Conference outlined for the Federal Constitution of 1949.

1949.08.04

President Sukarno issued a degree for the new setup of the Presidential Cabinet with Hatta as Prime Minister.

1949.11.02

The Dutch-Indonesian Round Table Conference held in The Hague between Aug 23 and Nov 2, ended with agreement on the cession of sovereignty to the United States of Indonesia.

1949.12.14

The Indonesian legislature, the Central Indonesian National Committee, ratified the Dutch-Indonesian agreement, and Sukarno was elected President of the United States of Indonesia on Dec 16 and took office on Dec 17. Mohammad Hatta was appointed Prime Minister on Dec 18, and his cabinet appointed and sworn in on Dec 20.

1949.12.20

With Sukarno and Hatta took positions in the United States of Indonesia respectively, and both never resigned as President and Prime Minister of the Republic of Indonesia, KMIP Chairman Assaat took the acting President. On Jan 4, 1950 Assaat asked Susanto Tirtoprodjo, Mohammad Natsir and Abdul Halim for a National Cabinet, and Jan 16 Abdul Halim formed his cabinet.

1949.12.27

Sovereignty was transferred to the United States of Indonesia and the Federal Constitution came into force, creating a bicameral legislature, the People’s Representative Council and Senate.

1950.02.15

The People’s Representative Council met for first time.

1950.02.16

The Senate was formed and members sworn in.

1950.02.17

Melkias Agustinus Pellaupessy was elected Speaker of the Senate. This was confirmed by President Sukarno on Feb 25, and Pellaupessy officially took office on Feb 27.

1950.02.21

Sartono was elected Speaker of the People’s Representative Council, and took office on Feb 22.

1950.05.19

Prime Minister Hatta of the United States of Indonesia (also represent State of East Indonesia and East Sumatra) and Prime Minister Halim of the Republic of Indonesia reached an agreement to establish a Unitary State with Republic of Indonesia as the base. Thereafter a Joint Committee was setup and chaired jointly by the United States of Indonesia Justice Minister Soepomo and Republic of Indonesia Prime Minister Abdul Halim.

1950.07.20

Both Government announed that the draft of the Provisional Constitution of the Unitary State of the Republic of Indonesia was approved by both governments. The constitution provides a unicameral legislation the House of Representatives.

1950.08.14

The People’s Representative Council and the Senate of the United States of Indonesia, and the Working Committee of the Central Indonesian National Committee of the Republic of Indonesia approved the Draft Constitution respectively.

1950.08.15

The Provisional Constitution was promulgated and Provisional People's Representative Council set up composed by People's Representative Council of the United States of Indonesia and the Working Committee of the Central Indonesian National Committee of the Republic of Indonesia.

1950.08.17

The new Republic of Indonesia was officially reconstituted with Sukarno as President.

1950.08.19

Sartono was elected Speaker of the Provisional People’s Representative Council, and President Sukarno confirmed the result on August 21.

1950.08.22

President Sukarno instructed Mohammad Natsir to form a new cabinet.

1950.09.06

Mohammad Natsir cabinet announced and took office on Sept 7.

1950.10.14

Hatta was elected by the Provisional People’s Representative Council as Vice President of the Republic.

1950.10.25

Sukarno and Hatta took oath as President and Vice President.

1951.03.21

President Sukarno accepted Prime Minister Mohammad Natsir resignation, and on April 18 Sukiman was asked to form a new government.

1951.04.27

Sukiman Wirjosandjojo cabinet announced and took office.

1952.02.23

Sukiman Wirjosandjojo cabinet resigned.

1952.04.01

Wilopo government was announced and then took office on April 3.

1953.06.03

Wilopo cabinet resigned.

1953.07.31

Great Indonesia Unity Party Leader Wongsonegoro succeeded in getting a coalition government with Ali Sastroamidjojo as Prime Minister, and himself as First Deputy Prime Minister.

1955.07.24

Prime Minsiter Ali Sastroamidjojo cabinet resigned .

1955.08.11

Burhanuddin Harahap presented his cabinet and sworn in the next day.

1955.09.29

First Legislative election to the People’s Representative Council.

1955.12.15

Constitutional Assembly election.

1956.02.28

Provisional People’s Representative Council Chairman Sartono resigned in protest to the motion to dissolve the Netherlands-Indonesian Union. First Deputy Chairman of the Council, Parkindo’s Tambunan immediately assumed the chairmanship.

1956.03.03

Burhanuddin cabinet resigned.

1956.03.20

Ali Sastroamidjojo cabinet was announced and took office on March 26.

1956.03.26

People’s Representative Council first session, and Sartono is re-elected Chairman of the Council. He was ratified by President Sukarno on March 29.

1956.11.09

The members elected to the Constitutional Assembly took oath, and on next day the Assembly was officially inaugurated and Wilopo elected its Speaker.

1956.12.01

Vice President Hatta resigned.

1957.02.21

President Sukarno detailed his plan for the Guided Democracy.

1957.03.14

Ali Sastroamidjojo cabinet returned his mandate to the President.

1957.04.04

President Sukarno held a meeting to announce his intention to form an emergency extra-parliamentary working cabinet, whose members Sukarno would choose.

1957.04.08

The working cabinet headed by non-partisan Prime Minister Djuanda Kartawidjaja was announced and took office the next day.

1957.07.12

The National Council was inaugurated with Sukarno as Chairman and Ruslan Abdulgani as Vice Chairman.

1959.07.05

President Sukarno issued a decree to reinstate the 1945 constitution and dissolving the Constitutional Assembly.

1959.07.09

A working cabinet with Sukarno as prime minister and Djuanda Kartawidjaja as First Minister was announced.

1959.07.23

Sartono was sworn again as the chairman of the further renewed People's Representative Council after the July 5 Presidential Degree.

1960.03.05

President Sukarno dissolved the elected People’s Representative Council.

1960.03.27

President Sukarno formed the Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council (Dewan Perwakilan Rakyat Gotong Royong, DPR-GR).

1960.06.25

The Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council was inaugurated and Zainul Arifin was appointed Speaker, following the presidential degree on the previous day. Arifin was officially appointed by Presidential Degree on Sept 20.

1960.08.15

President Sukarno formed the Provisional People's Consultative Assembly (Majelis Permusyawaratan Rakyat Sementara, MPRS).

1960.09.15

The Provisional People's Consultative Assembly was inaugurated and Chairul Saleh appointed its Chairman.

1963.03.02

Speaker Zainul Arifin of the Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council died. Arudji Kartawinata was appointed by President as Speaker on March 4.

1963.11.07

First Minister Djuanda Kartawidjaja died and his position was never replaced.

1965.09.30

Sept 30 Movement

1965.11.15

The Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council resumed after purging of the Indonesian Communist Party (PKI).

1966.02.21

President Suakrno announced the new cabinet, in which Chairul Saleh continue as Provisional People’s Consultative Assembly Chairman, and I Gusti Gde Subamia as Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council Speaker. The cabinet was sworn in on Feb 24.

1966.02.26

I Gusti Gde Subamia was officially inaugurated as Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council Speaker.

1966.03.11

President Sukarno signed Supersemar to give Suharto authority to take whatever measures to restore orders, effectively transfer of executive power from Sukarno to Suharto.

1966.03.18

Chairul Saleh, The Chairman of the Provisional People's Consultative Assembly was arrested, and Deputy Chairman Wiluyo Puspoyudo took acting chairman role.

1966.03.30

The new cabinet line-up, agreed between Suharto and Sukarno, was inaugurated.

1966.05.02

A Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council caretaker leadership was appointed to better shape the Council leadership, composed of Achmad Sjaichu, Mursalin Daeng Mamanggung and Syarif Thayeb.

1966.05.17

Achmad Sjaichu was elected Speaker of Mutual-Cooperative People’s Representative Council, and this is ratified by President on May 23 with retroactive period from May 17.

1966.06.20

Abdul Haris Nasution was elected Chairman of the Provisional People's Consultative Assembly at the new session.

1966.07.05

Sukarno was stripped of the “President for Life”.

1967.03.12

The special session of Provisional People's Consultative Assembly removed Sukarno as President, and appointed Suharto as acting President.

1968.03.27

Suharto was officially elected President of the Republic and sworn in on same day.

1971.07.03

First Legislative election under the New Order regime.

1971.10.28

Parliament inaururation, and Idhim Chalid was elected Parliament Speaker on Oct 29 and installed officially on Nov 1.

1973.03.22

Suharto reelected President and he sworn in on March 23. Hamengkubuwono IX, Sultan of Yogyakarta was elected Vice Presient on March 23 and took office on March 24.

1977.05.02

Legislative election.

1977.10.01

New parliament opened. Adam Malik was elected Speaker on Oct 3 and officially sworn in on Oct 4.

1978.03.22

Suharto reelected President, and on March 23 Adam Malik was elected Vice President. Both took office on March 23.

1978.05.18

Daryatmo was elected new Speaker of the Parliament. He sworn in on May 20.

1982.05.04

Legislative election.

1982.10.01

New parliament opened. Amir Machmud was elected Speaker on Oct 2 and officially sworn in on Oct 3.

1983.03.10

Suharto reelected President, and on March 11 Umar Wirahadikusumah was elected Vice President. Both took office on March 11.

1987.04.23

Legislative election.

1987.10.01

New parliament opened. Kharis Suhud was elected Speaker on Oct 2.

1988.03.10

Suharto reelected President, and on March 11 Sudharmono was elected Vice President. Both took office on March 11.

1992.06.09

Legislative election.

1992.10.01

New parliament opened. Wahono was elected Speaker on Oct 2.

1993.03.10

Suharto reelected President and on March 11 Try Sutrisno was elected Vice President. Both took office on March 11.

1997.05.29

Legislative election.

1997.10.01

New parliament opened. Harmoko was elected Speaker on Oct 2.

Legislative election.

New parliament opened.

Amien Rais was elected Speaker of People's Consultative Assembly (MPR).

1999.10.05

Akbar Tandjung was elected Speaker of People's Representative Council (DPR).

MPR: Sidarto Danusubroto

2014.10.02

Zulkifli Hasan was elected and sworn in as Speaker of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR).

2015.12.16

Setya Novanto resigned as Speaker of the People's Representative Council (DPR) amidst allegations of solicit kickbacks.

2015.12.18

Lawmaker Fadli Zon was appointed acting People's Representative Council (DPR) Speaker.

2016.01.11

Ade Komarudin was elected Speaker of the People’s Representative Council (DPR).

2016.10.05

The Regional Representatives Council (DPD) discharged Irman Gusman from his position as speaker due to under investigation for bribary.

2016.10.11

Mohammad Saleh was elected as the new Regional Representative Council (DPD) Speaker in place of Irman Gusman.

2016.11.30

The People’s Representative Council (DPR) returned Setya Novanto as Speaker, replacing Ade Komarudin.

2017.04.03

Oesman Sapta Odang was elected new Regional Representative Council (DPD) Speaker, replacing Mohammad Saleh.

2017.12.11

Setya Novanto again resigned as Speaker of the People's Representative Council (DPR) when charged with graft, and Fadli Zon was appointed acting speaker again.

2018.01.15

Bambang Soesatyo was elected Speaker of the People’s Representative Council (DPR).

State of East Indonesia

1946.11.15

Linggadjati Agreement was concluded by the Dutch administration and the unilaterally declared Republic of Indonesia in which the Dutch recognized the Republic as exercising de facto authority in Java, Madura and Sumatra. The agreement was finally signed on March 25, 1947 after both side ratified.

1946.12.24

Denpasar Conference was held between Dec 7 and Dec 24, resulting in establishment of the State of Great East (Negara Timoer Besar). On Dec 24 the Regulations on Forming the State of Indonesia were approved, and became the provisional constitutionesia were approved, and became the provisional constitution. The proposed solution included a Head of State, a People’s Representative Body and a Senate to represent regional interests.

1946.12.24

Tjokorda Fde Raka Soekawati was elected Head of State and Tadjoeddin Noor Chair of the Provisional Representatives Body, and the Denpasar Conference delegates became the Provisional Representatives Body.

1946.12.27

The State of Great East renamed the State of East Indonesia (Negara Indonesia Timoer or NIT). https://www.bukalapak.com/

1947.01.13

Nadjamoedin Daeng Malewa formed first cabinet.

1947.05.27

Tadjoeddin Noor was replaced as Chair of the Provisional Representatives Body by Sultan Muhammad Kahareoddin III.

1947.06.02

Nadjamoedin Daeng Malewa reshuffled his cabinet and gained approval by the Provisional Representatives Body.

1947.10.11

The S.J. Warrouw Cabinet

1947.12.15

The First Ide Anak Agung Gde Agung Cabinet

1949.01.12

The Second Ide Anak Agung Gde Agung Cabinet

1949.05.28

The Provisional Senate of East Indonesia (Senat Sementara Negara Indonesia Timur) was inaugurated with W. A. Sarapil as Speaker.

1949.12.27

The J.E. Tatengkeng Cabinet

1949.12.27

With the realisation of the United States of Indonesia, State of East Indonesia became a constituent of the new federation.

State of East Java (ref: Surabaya, City of Work: A Socioeconomic History, 1900-2000)

1948.11.26

The State of East Java (Negara Jawa Timur) was formally approved by Batavia Dutch government.

1948.12.01

Achmad Kusumonegoro, Regent of Banjuwagi was elected Wali Negara of the new State of East Java, and Regent of Surabaya as Chairman of the the Provional Representative Body.

1948.12.03

Bondowoso Conference concluded (open on Nav 16) and Achmad Kusumonegoro sworn in.

1949.11.02

An Agreement was reached at the Round Table Conference in the Hague to transfer sovereignty from the Netherlands to the United States of Indonesia to take effect on Dec 27.

1950.01.19

After Wali Negara resigned from the position, the Government of the United States of Indonesia appointed Samadikoen as Commissioner.

1950.02.24

The residency of Surabaya formmaly handed over to the Republic and on Feb 25 the Provional Parliament of the Negara dissolved itself and merged with the United States of Indonesia, then Samadikoen became the Governor of the Province of East Java.

1950.03.09

The Province of East Java was merged into Republic of Indonesia.

 (December 1947), Madura and West Java (February 1948), South Sumatra (September 1948) and East Java (November 1948).

1948.03.09

Dutch Governor General of the Dutch East Indias Hubertus van Mook established a Provisioanl Federal Government which remaining in the hands of the Dutch.

1948.05.27

The Bandung Conference was opened by von Mook to discuss issues related to the form of government of the future federal state, and its relationship with the Netherlands.

1948.07.08

Unsasified with the Dutch effort to establish a state on terms favourable to the Dutch, Premier of East Indonesia Ide Anak Agung Gde Agung and Premier of Pasundan Adil Poeadiredja took the inititive to invite all thirteen Heads of Constituent States to a Conference at Bandung, to try to find a solution for Indonesia.

1948.07.12

The delegates held first meeting and elected Tengku Bahriun of Medan as Chairman.

1948.07.15

A resolution was drafted and was submitted to van Mook on July 17. And the delegates renamed themselves the Federal Consultative Assembly (Majelis Permusyawaratan Federal atau Bijeenkomst voor Federaal Overleg).

  • Representatives from Bandjar, Bangka, Billiton, Greater Dajak, East Indonesia, West Borneo, South-West Boreno, East Boreno, Pasoendan, Riouw, South Sumatra, East Sumatra, Madoera
  • Observbers from Mid Java, East Java and Padang

1949.01.13

Chairman of the Federal Consultative Assembly Tengku Bahriun died.

1949.01.16

Sultan Hamid II of Pontianak was elected new Chairman of the Federal Consultative Assembly.

1950.08.17

The United States of Indonesia dissolved

Regional Representatives Council

**地方代表理事会

越南 Vietnam

越南1884年成为法兰西属地。1945年8月日本投降后，越南北部爆发革命，9月2日成立越南民主共和国。1946年1月6日举行首次选举，成立国民大会（National Assembly，Quốc dân Đại hội）。1960年1月1日新宪法，改称国会（National Assembly，Quốc hội）。1976年4月南北统一后首次国会选举，7月2日越南社会主义共和国正式成立，组成统一的国会。

1945.03.09

Japanese coup overthrown French administations.

1945.03.11

Bao Dai declared independence of Vietnam, with an official independence ceremony took place on May 8. (Cambodia March 13, Laos April 11)

1945.04.17

Emperor Bao Dai appointed Tran Trong Kim as Prime Minister.

1945.08.07

In the wake of the resignation of two ministers and the death of a third, Kim brought his entire cabinet resignation to Emperor Bao Dai.

1945.08.17

The Viet Minh took control of Honoi.

1945.08.19

Tran Trong Kim resigned and on Aug 23 his cabinet was dissolved.

1945.08.26

Bao Dai issued an edict of abdication, which he then read to a large crowd during a formal ceremony held on 30 August.

1945.08.29

The Provisional Government of the Democratic Republic of Vietnam came into being, with Ho Chi Minh as the President of the Government.

1945.09.02

Democratic Republic of Vietnam proclaimed.

1946.01.06

National Assembly elections were held in areas controlled by Viet Minh.

1946.03.02

First meeting of the National Assembly, the Provisional Government was replaced by a coalition government still headed by Ho Chi Minh; Nguyen Van To was elected Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly.

1946.11.09

Second session of the National Assembly held between Oct 28 and Nov 9. First Constitution was adopted on last day of this session, which formalized National Assemly as the highest body of authority of the Democratic Republic of Vietnam.

1946.11.09

At last day of the second session of the National Assembly, Bui Bong Doan was elected new Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly.

1955.04.13

Bui Bong Doan, Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly, died.

1955.09.20

Ton Duc Trang was elected Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly on the fifth session of the First National Assembly held between Sep 15 and Sep 20. At same meeting Pham Van Dong was elected Prime Minister.

1960.01.01

New Constitution promulgated after National Assembly approved it the previous day.

1960.05.08

National Assembly Elections

1960.07.15

First session of the second National Assembly was held between July 6 and 15, Ho Chi Min was elected President, Ton Duc Thang Vice President, Pham Van Dong Prime Minister, Truong Chinh Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly.

1964.04.26

National Assembly Elections

1964.07.03

First session of the third National Assembly was held between June 25 and July 3, Ho Chi Min was reelected President, Ton Duc Thang Vice President, Pham Van Dong Prime Minister and Truong Chinh Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly.

1969.09.02

President Ho Chi Minh died.

1969.09.22

Sepcial (fifth) Session of the National Assembly elected Ton Duc Thang as President and Nguyen Luong Bang Vice President.

1971.04.11

National Assembly Elections

1971.06.10

First session of the fourth National Assembly was held between June 7 and June 10, Ton Duc Thang was reelected President, Nguyen Luong Bang Vice President, Pham Van Dong Prime Minister and Truong Chinh Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly.

1975.04.06

National Assembly Elections

1975.06.06

First session of the fifth National Assembly was held between June 3 and June 6, Ton Duc Thang was reelected President, Nguyen Luong Bang Vice President, Pham Van Dong Prime Minister and Truong Chinh Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly.

1976.04.25

First Parliament Election since reunified.

1976.07.02

First session of the sixth National Assembly was held between June 24 and July 3. On July 2, Socialist Republic of Vietnam was proclaimed, Ton Duc Thang was elected President, Nguyen Luong Bang and Nguyen Huu Tho Vice President, Pham Van Dong Prime Minister and Truong Chinh Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly.

1979.07.20

Vice President Nguyen Luong Bang died.

1980.03.30

President Ton Duc Thang died, and Vice President Nguyen Huu Tho became acting President on April 1.

1980.12.18

New Constitution adopted by National Assembly and promulgated on the next day, which introduced a Nation Assembly headed by a Chairman of the National Assembly, and a State Council as the highest functioning body of the National Assembly and the presidium of the state.

1981.04.26

National Assembly election.

1981.07.04

The first session of the seventh National Assembly was held between June 25 and July 4. Nguyen Huu Tho was elected Chairman of the National Assembly, Truong Chinh Chairman of the State Council, Pham Van Dong Chairman of the Council of Ministers.

1987.04.19

National Assembly election.

1987.06.18

The first session of the eighth National Assembly was help between June 17 and June 22. On June 18, Vo Chi Cong was elected Chairman of the State Council in place of Truong Chinh, Pham Hung succeeded Pham Van Dong as Chairman of the Council of Ministers, Le Quang Dao succeeded Nguyen Huu Tho as Chairman of the National Assembly.

1988.03.10

The Chairman of the Council of Ministers Pham Hung died of a heart attack. The Council of State issued resolution appointing Vice Chairman Vo Van Kiet as acting Chairman.

1988.06.22

Du Muoi was elected Chairman of the Council of Ministers at the third session of the eighth National Assembly.

1991.08.09

Vo Van Kiet was elected Chairman of the Council of Ministers at the ninth session of the eighth National Assembly.

1992.04.15

The eleventh and last session of the National Assembly passed the new Constitution which remove the Council of State, reestablish the position of President and Vice President, set up of Standing Committee of the National Assembly as permanent body of the National Assembly led by Chairman of the National Assembly, and the Chairman of the Council of Ministers is renamed Prime Minister.

1992.07.19

National Assembly election.

1992.09.23

The first session of the ninth National Assembly was held between Sept 19 and Oct 8. On Sept 23, Le Duc Anh was elected President, Nguyen Thi Binh Vice President, and Nong Duc Manh Chairman of the National Aseembly. On Sept 24, Vo Van Kiet was elected Prime Minister

1997.07.20

National Assembly election.

1997.09.24

The first session of the tenth National Assembly was held between Sept 18 and Sept 29. On Sept 24, Tran Duc Luong was elected President, Nguyen Thị Bình Vice President, and Nong Duc Manh Chairman of the National Aseembly. On Sept 24, Phan Van Khai was elected Prime Minister.

2001.06.27

Nguyen Van An was elected Chairman of the National Assembly, replacing Nong Duc Manh at the ninth session of the tenth Natinoal Assembly.

2002.05.19

National Assembly election.

2002.07.23

The first session of the eleventh National Assembly was held between July 19 and August 12. On July 23, Nguyen Van An was relected Chairman of the National Aseembly. On July 25, Tran Duc Luong was elected President, Truong My Hoa elected Vice President, and Phan Van Khai Prime Minister.

2006.06.26

Nguyen Phu Trong was elected new Chairman of the National Aseembly.

2007.05.20

National Assembly election.

2007.07.23

The first session of the twlevth National Assembly was held between July 19 and August 4. On July 23, Nguyen Phu Trong was reelected new Chairman of the National Aseembly.

2011.05.22

National Assembly election.

2011.07.23

The first session of the thirteenth National Assembly was held between July 21 and August 6. On July 23, Nguyen Sinh Hung was elected new Chairman of the National Aseembly.

2016.03.31

Nguyen Thi Kim Ngan was elected new Chairman of the National Aseembly at the 11th session of the 13th National Assembly, replacing Nguyen Sinh Hung who resigned on March 30.

2016.05.22

National Assembly election.

2016.07.21

The first session of the thirteenth National Assembly was held between July 20 and July 29. On July 21, Nguyen Thi Kim Ngan was reelected new Chairman of the National Aseembly.
