1960.05 –

Quốc hội Việt Nam

National Assembly

*国会

南越 [South] Viet Nam

越南南部的交趾支那1864年起为越南占领，1887年成为法属印度支那的一部分。1880年2月法国当局设立印度支那殖民委员会（Indochina Colonial Council，conseil colonial），1946年2月以咨议委员会（Cochinchian Advisory Council，Conseil consultatif de Cochinchine）取代。1946年3月26日，法国炮制了南圻自治共和国临时政府，6月1日正式成立南圻自治共和国（République autonome de Cochinchine，Cộng hòa Tự trị Nam Kỳ），咨议委员会改组为印度支那委员会（Council of Cochinchina，Conseil de Cochinchine）。1947年10月13日南圻自治共和国更名为越南南方临时政府；1948年5月20日组织国会，政府改组为越南临时中央政府。1949年6月14日，以保大为元首的越南国（State of Vietnam，Quốc gia Việt Nam）正式成立，越南南方实现法理统一。1952年9月，越南国组织了临时民族委员会（Provisional National Council）；1953年10月国会（National Congress，Quốc hội）成立。1955年10月23日吴廷琰操纵公投废黜保大，10月26日建立越南共和国，独掌大权。1956年3月选举制宪会议（Constituent Assembly，Quốc hội lập hiến），10月26日颁布新宪法，设立一院制的国民议会（National Assembly，Quốc hội）。1963年11月1日政变吴廷琰被杀，国民议会被解散，宪法被终止；11月4日军事革命委员会公布临时宪法，宣布立法权归军事革命委员会所有。1964年9月26日军政府召集国家高级委员会（High National Council，Thượng Hội đồng Quốc gia），负责组织选举和制定宪法，12月20日遭解散。1966年9月选举产生制宪会议（Constituent Assembly，Quốc hội lập hiến），1967年4月1日颁布新宪法，决定建立两院制议会，国民议会（National Assembly，Quốc hội Việt Nam Cộng hòa）由参议院（上院）（Senate，Thượng Nghị Viện）和众议院（下院）（House of Representatives，Hạ Nghị Viện）组成。1967年9-10月间举行了首次选举。1975年4月越南南方民族解放阵线推翻本政府，夺取越南南部之统治权。1976年7月与[北]越南实现统一。

1880.02.08

Indochina Colonial Council (conseil colonial) created.

1945.08.26

Bao Dai abdicated as Emperor of Annam.

1946.02.04

French High Commissioner in Cochinchina Henry d’Argenlieu replaced the Colonial Council of Cochinchina with the Cochinchian Advisory Council (Conseil consultatif de Cochinchine), and Jean Cédile was appointed its president.

1946.03.26

Indochina High Commissioner d'Argenlieu unilaterally approved the establishment of the Autonomous Republic of Cochinchina and Nguyen Van Thinh was elected by the Advisory Council as President of the Provisional Government of Republic of CochinChina.

1946.06.01

The autonomous Republic of Cochinchina was formally proclaimed under French auspices and a Provisional Government established with Nguyen Van Thinh as President and Nguyen Van Xuan as Vice President.

1946.07.26

Cochinchian Advisory Council was renamed as Council of Cochinchina (Conseil de Cochinchine)

1946.11.10

Nguyen Van Thinh committed suicide.

1946.11.29

Le Van Hoach was elected President of the Cochinchina Provisional Government.

1946.12.07

The new government under Hoach took office.

1947.03.25

Le Van Hoach declared that legally Bao Dai remained empreror since his abdication was not voluntary.

1947.09.15

Nguyen Van Xuan arrived back from France to take up post as Vice President of the Cochinchina Provisional Government.

1947.09.29

Le Van Hoach resigned.

1947.10.01

Nguyen Van Xuan was elected President of the Cochinchina Provisional Government.

1947.10.08

The new Government of Xuan took office.

1947.10.13

The name was changed to the Provisional Government of South Vietnam.

1948.05.20

A National Congress was held in Saigon to establish a Provisional Central Government of Vietnam, with Nguyen Van Xuan as President.

1948.05.27

Xuan became the President of the Government and Tran Van Huu Vice President.

1948.06.05

Joint Declaration at Bay of Along by French High Commissioner Bollaert and President Xuan with countersigned by Bao Dai, stated France recognizes the independence of Vietnam, and this was approved by French government on August 19.

1949.03.08

French President Vincent Auriol exchanged letters with Bao Dai, agteed to a procedure to achieve unity and independence of Vietnam.

1949.03.14

Territorial Assembly of Cochinchina

1949.04.25

Bao Dai flew back to Vietnam and arrived on April 28.

1949.06.04

France officially recognized the State of Vietnam under Chief of State Bao Dai.

1949.06.14

Bao Dai was officially inaugurated as Chief of Sate of State of Vietnam.

1949.06.20

Bao Dai accepted the resignation of the Provisional Central Government of Nguyen Van Xuan, and the new government will be led by himself.

1949.07.01

Bao Dai formally established State of Vietnam with himself as Chief of State and Premier.

1950.01.05

Bao Dai resigned as Premier and proposed Nguyen Phan Long as successor on Jan 9.

1950.01.21

Nguyen Phan Long took office as Premier of State of Vietnam.

1950.04.27

Bao Dai signed degree dissolving the government of Nguyen Phan Long and appointing Tran Van Huu to form a new cabinet. Huu accepted the appointment the next day.

1950.05.07

New cabinet led by Tran Van Huu sworn in.

1952.06.03

Bao Dai issued degrees dismissing the Huu cabinet and appointing Nguyen Van Tam as Premier.

1952.06.25

Nguyen Van Tam took office as Premier.

1952.09.01

The Provisional National Council of Vietnam was installed and held first meeting.

1953.10.12

The Vietnam National Congress met and Tran Trong Kim was elected President of the Congress on Oct 13.

1953.10.15

The Vietnam National Congress passed a resolution demanding complete independence for Vietnam.

1953.12.17

Nguyen Van Tam left office as Premier. On Dec 18 Bao Dai asked Prince Buu Loc to take the Premier position.

1954.01.16

Prince Buu Loc took office as Premier.

1954.06.16

Head of State Bao Dai accepted the resignation of Prime Minister Prince Buu Loc, and named Ngo Dinh Diem to form a new government.

1954.07.07

Ngo Dinh Diem took office as Prime Minister.

1955.10.23

State of Vietnam Referendum was held and Emperor Bao Dai was deposed.

1955.10.26

The referendum result was announced, Ngo Dinh Diem became President of the new Republic of Vietnam.

1956.03.04

Constituent Assembly election.

1956.03.15

The Constituent Assembly inaugurated its first session.

1956.03.22

The Constituent Assembly elected Tran Van Lam as Speaker.

1956.10.26

The Constitution of the Republic of Vietnam was promulgated, providing legislative of a single body named National Assembly. By Constitution

  • Article 95, the first legislative Assembly begins as from the promulgation of the Constitution.
  • Article 96, Ngo Dinh Diem is the first President of the Republic.
  • The President should designate the first Vice President.

1956.11.09

The National Assembly held its first session and Tran Van Lam is again elected Speaker.

1956.12.15

Tran Van Lam is elected President of the National Assembly.

1956.12.28

Nguyen Ngoc Tho was confirmed as Vice President by the National Assembly.

1961.04.09

Presidential Election was won by President Ngo Dinh Diem and Vice President Nguyen Ngoc Tho.

1961.04.29

Presidential Inauguration.

1963.11.01

Major General Duong Van Minh, Tran Van Don and Le Van Kim carried out a coup d’etat against President Ngo Dinh Diem. Diem was killed on next morning.

1963.11.02

Military leaders set up a provisional government headed by Vice Oresident Nguyen Ngoc Tho, also the Constitution was suspended and the National Assembly was dissolved.

1963.11.04

Provisional Cosntitutional Act No. 1 promulgated by the Military Revolutionary Council, which centralized legislative and executive powers to MRC itself. As Chairman of the MRC, Duong Van Minh was Chief of State; Executive power was entrusted to a provisional government headed by a Premier, who was designated by MRC.

1963.11.04

On same day, Duong Van Minh appointed Nguyen Ngoc Tho as Premier of the Provisional Government.

1963.11.05

Duong Van Minh was also appointed Chairman of the Executive Committee of the Revolutionary Military Council.

1964.01.30

Nguyen Khanh acts to take over control of the government in a bloodless internal coup that removes the civilian government and puts him in power

1964.02.08

Nghyen Khanh announced formation of a new government with himself as Premier and Duong Van Minh as nominal Chief of State.

1964.07.02

A Second Provisional Charter

1964.08.16

Nghyen Khanh was elected President by the Military Revolutionary Council, and a third Provisional Charter was installed.

1964.08.25

Under pressure, the Military Revolutionary Council announced the resignation of President Nghyen Khanh and the annulment of the August 16 Constitution.

1964.08.27

The Military Revolutionary Council was disbanded, and August 16 Constitutution withdrawn. Nguyen Khanh, Duong Van Minh and Tran Thien Khiem formed a Provisional Leadership Committee.

1964.08.29

Nguyen Xuan Oanh was named acting Premier to head a caretaker government.

1964.09.03

Nguyen Khanh resummed as Premier.

1964.09.08

Duong Van Minh restored as Chief of State.

1964.09.26

Vietnam High National Council inaugurated and charged with preparing new constitution, chaired by Phan Khac Suu

1964.10.20

A Provisional Constitution was presented, provided transfer of authority to a civilian government.

1964.10.24

Phan Khac Suu elected Chief of State by High National Council.

1964.10.26

The Provisional Leadership Committeeformally relinquished control to Chief of State Phan Khac Suu.

1964.10.30

Nguyen Xuan Chu replaced Phan Khac Suu as Chairman of High National Cocuncil

1964.11.01

Tran Van Huong named Premier of Vietnam, and he took office Nov 4.

1964.11.05

Chairman of High National Cocuncil Nguyen Xuan Chu resigned.

1964.11.18

Le Van Thu was elected new Chairman of High National Cocuncil.

1964.12.18

Armed Forces Council set up with Nguyen Khanh as its chairman.

1964.12.20

Military dissolved the provisional legislature High National Council.

1965.01.27

Tran Van Huong was ousted by military.

1965.01.28

Nguyen Xuan Oanh appointed acting Premier.

1965.02.16

Armed Forces Council named Phan Huy Quat as new Premier.

1965.02.17

Armed Forces Council named a National Legislative Council with Pham Xuan Chieu as Chairman.

1965.02.20

Armed Forces Council demanded resignation of Nguyen Khanh, and he did so on Feb 21.

1965.06.11

Premier Phan Huy Quat resigned and asked Armed Forces to take over.

1965.06.12

Phan Khac Suu resigned as Chief of State.

1965.06.14

National Leadership Committee was formed.

1965.06.19

National Leadership Committee officially formed, with Nguyen Van Thieu as Chairman (Chief of Sate) and he named Nguyen Cao Ky as Chairman of Central Executive Committee (Prime Minister) and proclaimed the sixth constitution, another provisional charter

1966.09.11

Constituent Assembly was elected to draft a new Constitution.

1966.10.26

Phan Khac Suu was elected Speaker of the Constituent Assembly.

1967.03.18

The Constituent Assembly approved the draft Constitution.

1967.03.27

Vietnam Armed Forces Council approved the constitution.

1967.04.01

Constitution of South Vietnam (1967) was promulgated, Legislative authority is vested by the people in the National Assembly, which includes two houses, the House of Representatives and the Senate.

1967.09.03

General Election for President, Vice President and Senate.

1967.10.22

General Election for House of Representatives.

1967.10.31

President Nguyen Van Thieu and Vice President Nguyen Cao Ky inaugurated, Prime Minister Nguyen Van Loc assumed full responsibility under new Constitution.

1967.11.08

Lower House of the National Assembly hled first session and Nguyen Ba Luong was named acting Chairman.

1967.12.22

Nguyen Van Huyen was elected Chairman of the Senate. (1968, 1969, 1970.10.17, 1971, 1972.10.06)

1968.01.17

Nguyen Ba Luong was elected Chairman of the Lower House. (1968.10.11, 1970)

1968.05.25

A new cabinet headed by Than Van Huong was formed to replace Prime Minister Nguyen Van Loc.

1969.08.23

Tran Thien Khiem was appointed as Prime Minister, to replace Tran Van Huong who resigned the previous day.

1969.09.01

Tran Thien Khiem cabinet took office.

1971.08.29

House of Representatives Elections

1971.10.03

Presidential Election was won by Nguyen Van Thieu as President and Tran Van Huong as Vice President.

1971.10.31

President and Vice President inaugutated.

1971.12.03

Nguyen Ba Can was elected Chairman of the Lower House. (1972, 1973.10.11, 1974)

1973.08.26

Senate Elections.

1973.10.15

Tran Van Lam was elected Chairman of the Senate. (1974)

1975.04.04

President Thieu replace Prime Minister Than Thiem Khiem with Nguyen Ba Can, the Chairman of the Lower House.

1975.04.21

Nguyen Van Thieu resigned as President and Vice President Tran Van Huong resumed the presidency.

1975.04.24

Prime Minister Nguyen Ba Can resigned.

1975.04.27

National Assembly voted to have President Huong transfer power to Duong Van Minh, and he assumed the Presidentcy on April 28.

1975.04.28

Duong Van Minh took oath, Nguyen Van Huyen was appointed Vice President and Vu Van Mau Prime Minister.

1975.04.30

Duong Van Minh surrendered to Provisional Revolutionary Government of South Vietnam.

西亚北非地区

阿尔及利亚 Algeria

阿尔及利亚原为法兰西属地，1947年法兰西在阿尔及利亚成立议会。1962年7月3日阿尔及利亚独立，9月20日举行首次立法选举，成立制宪国民议会，一年后宪法通过，制宪议会自动转成国民议会。1965年6 月，胡阿里·布迈丁发动政变上台，解散了国民议会。1976年11月22日通过的新宪法规定组建全国人民议会，并于1977年2月举行了首次选举。1992年1月，沙德利总统辞职，阿成立最高国务委员会行使总统职权，并相继成立国家咨询委员会和国家过渡委员会，完成修宪工作。1996年11月28日，阿举行全民公投，通过宪法修正案，规定会由国民议会（众议院）和民族院（参议院）组成。国民议会于1997年6月普选产生，为阿历史上首届多党议会；民族院于1997年12月产生。

网址：

民族院：http://www.majliselouma.dz/

国民议会：http://www.apn-dz.org/apn/french/index.htm

*议会

**民族院

**国民议会

阿拉伯联合酋长国 United Arab Emirates

特鲁西尔诸国1820年成为不列颠保护领。1971年3月1日，英国宣布同各酋长国签订的条约于年底终止。联邦最高委员会于1971年7月18日通过临时宪法，同年12月2日，阿拉伯联合酋长国宣告成立，临时宪法生效。联邦最高委员会（Federal Supreme Council，المجلس الأعلى للاتحاد‎）由七个酋长国的酋长组成，是最高权力机构。联邦国民议会（Federal National Council，المجلس الوطني الإتحادي，al-Majlis al-Watani al-Ittihadi），亦称全国协商议会，成立于1972年2月12日，是咨询机构。2006年8月，阿联酋颁布新的议会选举法，规定联邦国民议会一半成员由各酋长国选举产生，这被视为阿在民主改革道路上迈出的重要一步。

*联邦国民议会

阿曼 Oman

马斯喀特苏丹国1892年成为不列颠保护领。1913年5月阿曼山区部落反英起义，建立阿曼伊斯兰教长国。1920年9月25日，英国与教长国签订条约承认其独立，阿曼被分为马斯喀特苏丹国和阿曼伊斯兰教长国。1959年1月马斯喀特最终攻灭阿曼教长国，1967年，统一为马斯喀特和阿曼苏丹国。1970年7月23日，卡布斯发动宫廷政变，废父登基，宣布改国名为阿曼苏丹国并沿用至今。1981年10月18日，卡布斯苏丹颁发命令，宣布成立国家咨询委员会（State Consultative Council），作为咨询机构；1991年11月12日由卡布斯苏丹颁布诏书成立协商会议（Consultative Assembly，مجلس الشورى‎，Majlis al-Shura），取代原国家咨询委员会成为国家最高审议监督机构。1996年11月6日，卡布斯苏丹颁布诏书，公布了《国家基本法》（相当于宪法），开始实行宪政。1997年12月16日，卡布斯苏丹根据阿曼国家基本法发布敕令，组建阿曼国家委员会（Council of State of Oman，مجلس الدولة العماني‎ Majlis ad-Dawla al-ʿUmāniyyi）；12月27日正式成立。国家委员会（相当于议会上院）和协商会议（相当于议会下院）共同组成阿曼委员会（Council of Oman，مجلس عُمان）。

埃及 Egypt

1866年11月埃及总督伊斯梅尔下令组建代表协商会议，但是在1879年6月被新总督陶菲克下令禁止。1881年9月埃及爆发起事，成立议会。1882年9月起英国控制埃及。1883年5月埃及制定基本法，实行宪政，规定议会由两院组成。1913年7月两院均被废止，另组立法议会。法令原定立法议会为期6年，但是仅仅数月后，一战爆发，英国在埃及实施军管法，立法议会被中止。1914年12月，埃及被宣布为英国的保护国，立法议会更被无限期推迟，直至1923年4月新宪法生效。新宪法埃及获得了独立，议会由两院组成。1930年10月通过新宪法，但是1934年11月即被废止，同时终止议会。1935年12月恢复1823年宪法。议会此期间曾得多次被解散，最后一次恰好在1952年七月革命前夕，革命后宪法被彻底废除。1953年6月废除君主制，建立共和政府。根据1956年新宪法，1957年7月建立了国民议会。1958年2月埃及与叙利亚合并为阿拉伯联合共和国，3月组建了联合的国民议会，1961年9月叙利亚退出，联盟解体。1964年3月，临时宪法规定埃及恢复国民议会。1971年9月新宪法生效，复国名为埃及，不再称阿拉伯联合共和国，国民议会亦改称人民议会。1980年11月根据1979年4月宪法修正案，组建了协商会议。

网址：

协商会议：http://www.shoura.gov.eg/

人民议会：http://www.parliament.gov.eg/

巴勒斯坦 Palestine

1994年5月12日巴勒斯坦民族权力机构成立，由巴勒斯坦人实行自治。根据奥斯陆协议，1996年1月20日选举产生立法委员会（Palestinian Legislative Council，المجلس التشريعي الفلسطيني），作为立法机关，3月7日正式成立。2006年1月第二次立法委员会选举后哈马斯获胜；2007年6月加沙之战后，9月巴勒斯坦总统阿巴斯通过总统令将立法委员会的投票系统改为完全比例代表制，绕过功能失调的立法委员会。立法委员会事实上处于停摆状态。2018年12月22日，阿巴斯宣布根据巴勒斯坦最高宪法法院决定解散立法委员会，哈马斯认为解散决定无效。第三届立法委员会选举目前定于2021年5月22日举行。

巴林 Bahrain

巴林1880年成为不列颠保护领。1971年3月英国宣布其同波斯湾诸酋长国签订的所有条约在同年年底终止。1971年8月15日巴林宣告独立。1972年12月选出制宪议会（Bahraini Constituent Assembly），1973年6月2日颁布宪法，开始实行宪政；12月6日正式实施，成立国民议会（National Assembly）。1975年8月26日国民议会被解散。1992年12月20日重新设置协商会议（Consultative Council）。2002年2月14日，颁布新宪法，解散协商议会，设两院制国民议会（National Assembly，المجلس الوطني البحريني‎

），协商会议（上院）（Consultative Council，Majlis al-shura，مجلس الشورى البحريني）和代表理事会（下院）（Council of Representatives，Majlis an-nuwab，مجلس النواب البحريني），2002年10月24日选举后正式成立。

卡塔尔 Qatar

卡塔尔1846年建立酋长国，1916年成为不列颠保护领，1971年9月3日独立。1970年4月2日颁布临时宪法。1972年2月22日，哈利法就任埃米尔，原计划适用于过渡时期的临时宪法成为卡塔尔国的根本大法，4月成立协商议会（Consultative Assembly，مجلس الشورى القطري‎，Majlis as-Shura），作为咨询机构。2003年4月29日全民公投通过永久宪法，2005年6月7日正式生效。

科威特 Kuwait

科威特酋长国1756年建立，1913年沦为不列颠保护领。科威特议会的历史可追溯到1938年7月成立的由14名成员组成的国家立法委员会（Legislative Council）。同年12月21日立法委员会因与埃米尔争夺石油收入的分配权而遭到解散。此后虽举行了第二次选举，但最终埃米尔1939年3月7日决定彻底解散立法委员会，取而代之的是以王储为主席的咨议委员会（Advisory Council），1940年7月亦无疾而终。1961年6月19日科威特独立，1962年11月12日颁布宪法，正式把君主政体确定为二元制的君主立宪政体，立法机构由埃米尔和国民议会（National Assembly，مجلس الأمة‎）组成。1963年1月29日国民议会成立，1976年8月29日，埃米尔第一次宣布解散议会，1981年2月恢复。1986年7月3日，由于国民议会对政府政策的激烈批评，埃米尔第二次宣布解散议会，1990年4月22日，埃米尔为应对公众日益强烈的恢复国民议会的要求，宣布成立一个由75名成员组成的国家委员会（National Council），但是遭到反对派强烈抵制。1990年8月2日，伊拉克入侵科威特。在被伊拉克占领期间，流亡国外的埃米尔与所有政治派别的代表达成了协议。埃米尔向全国人民许诺，一旦科威特获得解放，政府将同意关于扩大民主范围的要求，举行议会选举，恢复国民议会。1991年6月2日，埃米尔正式宣布废止1986年颁布的中止国民议会的法令，1992年10月5日举行了大选，20日议会恢复。

1938.06.29

Three leading merchants of Kuwait elected a Legislstive Council.

1938.07.06

The Ruler finally signed the necessary document to establish the Council. Sheikh Abdulla al-Salim al-Sabah was elected as President of the Council.

1938.12.21

The Legislative Council was dissolved by the Ruler.

1939.03.07

The Ruler finally dissolved the Legislative Council, after a second election and their refusal to new constitution proposal from the Emir that tuen the Council into an advisory body.

1939.03.12

The Ruler formed a new and representative Advisory Council under the presidency of his counsion, Abdulla Salim. The Advisory Council lasted till July 1940 when the meeting suddenly stopped.

Iraq invaded Kuwait.

1990.11.21

The Crown Prince announced the formation of a new body, the Supreme Advisory Council, containing 35 appointed members. It is headed by the Crown Prince himself. Though never explicitly stated, it was understood that soon after liberation, the 1962 Constitution would be fully restored and the National Assembly would be reconvened.

1991.06.02

The Emir announced that new elections for the National Assembly were to be held in October 1992.

the Amir re-appointed the Crown Prince Sheik Saad al-Abdullah al-Sabah as Prime Minister. The latter, on 17 October, appointed a 16-member Cabinet.

1992.10.20

The National Assembly elected an opposition member, Mr. Ahmed al-Saadun, as Speaker. He had previously been Speaker of the dissolved legislature.

国民议会

黎巴嫩 Lebanon

黎巴嫩，1517年被奥斯曼帝国占领，1861年6月欧洲列强强迫奥斯曼签署协议，组建黎巴嫩山行政委员会（Administrative Council of Mount Lebanon，Majlis Idara Jabal Lubnan)，1915年3月一战爆发后奥斯曼当局将其解散。1918年10月法国恢复行政委员会，直到1920年7月将其强制解散。第一次世界大战后，1920年9月1日为法兰西委任统治地，称大黎巴嫩 。法国当局组织行政委员会（Administrative Committee），1922年3月被选举产生的代表委员会（Representative Council）代替。

1925年6月法国当局组织宪法委员会制定宪法，1926年5月23日代表委员会通过宪法，立法权归属两院制的议会（Parliament），由参议院（Senate）和众议院（Chamber of Deputies，Chambre des députés，مجلس النواب‎ Majlis an-Nuwwab）组成。1927年10月17日宪法修正案取消参议院。1932年5月，法国高级专员取消宪法，自行延长黎巴嫩总统任期，直到1936年1月恢复。1939年9月21日因二战爆发法国高级专员宣布中止宪法，解散议会。1940年6月起为法国维希政府控制，1941年7月英军在自由法国部队协助下占领黎巴嫩。同年11月26日自由法国部队宣布结束对黎的委任统治。1943年8月议会选举恢复，11月9日新议会通过决议结束法国托管地位，11月22日获真正独立。

1861.06.09

The Protocal (Organic Statute, Reglement Organique) signed between the European Powers and the Ottoman Empire defined the composition and duties of the newly created Administrative Council of Mount Lebanon (Majlis Idara Jabal Lubnan), with advisory tole in matters concerning revenues and expenditures. It was dissolved by Ottoman in March 1915.

1918.10.22

The new reconvened Administrative Council of Mount Lebanon was officially reinstated. This Council was dissolved by French authorities on July 12, 1920.

1920.09.01

Greater Lebanon under French mandate.

1920.10.04

Election of President of Administrative Committee, Daoud Amoun elected President.

1922.03.13

The Administrative Committee was replaced by a partly elected Representative Council.

1925.06.15

A Commission, under the Chairmanship of Joseph Paul-Boncour, was appointed to prepare the constitution law for Lebanon. It was ready by May 15, 1926.

1926.05.22

The Representative Council, sittign as a constituent assembly, adopted the Constitution and it was promulgated on May 23. The Parliament composed of two chambers, a Senate and a Chamber of Deputies.

1926.05.24

The High Commissioner Jouvenel named the Senate members.

1926.05.26

The Chamber of Deputies (previous Representative Council) held a joint meeting with the Senate, at which Charles Dabbas was officially elected President of the Lebanese Republic.

1926.05.31

A cabinet was formed under Auguste Adid Pasha.

1927.10.17

Constitutional Law amendment decided the legislative power shall be vested in a single Chamber of Deputies.

1932.05.09

French high commissioner Henri Ponsot suspended the constitution and extended the term of President Dabbas for one year.

1939.09.21

French High Commissioner Gabriel Puaux suspended the constitution and dissolved the Chamber of Deputies. Legislative and Executive functions are to be carried out by a Secretary of State, Abdullah Beyhum, appointed by the high commissioner.

1941.07.14

The Vichy government's control of Lebanon and Syria ended with an armistice signed in Acre.

1941.11.26

General Georges Catroux, delegate general under de Gaulle, proclaimed the independence of Lebanon.

1943.08.29

General election held and a second round on 4 Sep.

1943.09.21

The new Chamber of Deputies elected Bishara al Khuri as president.

1943.11.08

The Chamber of Deputies amended the Constitution, abolishing the articles that referred to the Mandate and modifying those that specified the powers of the high commissioner, thus unilaterally ending the Mandate.

1943.11.22

The French authorities released the prisoners (a number of prominent Lebanese politicians, including the president, the prime minister, and other cabinet members) at Rashayya who they arrested due to the mandate abolishment. This day has been celebrated as Independence Day for Lebanon.

1946.12.31

French troops were completely withdrawn from the country, with the signing of the Franco-Lebanese Treaty.

利比亚 Libya

昔兰尼加、的黎波里塔尼亚和费赞原为意大利属地，1949年6月1日塞努西在昔兰尼加建立昔兰尼加王国，并颁布宪法，实行宪政。1950年成立国民议会，由上下两院参议院和代表院组成。1951年12月24日昔兰尼加、的黎波里塔尼亚和费赞独立，并合并为利比亚。 1969年9月1日卡扎非发动政变，12月颁布临时宪法，废除君主制，建立共和政府。1973年卡扎菲发动“文化革命”，宣布停止执行一切现行法律。1977年3月发表的《人民权力宣言》规定《古兰经》为利的社会法典。国家最高权力机构是总人民大会，常设机构为总人民大会秘书处，秘书即为议长；总人民委员会是国家最高行政机构，也是总人民大会的组成部分。1976年11月举行第一次大会。

毛里塔尼亚 Mauritania

毛里塔尼亚原为法兰西属地，1946年法兰西在毛里塔尼亚设立总议会(General Council)(1952年改称议会Territorial Assembly)。1958年11月毛里塔尼亚成为法兰西共同体之自治共和国，1960年11月28日正式独立。1959年5月议会选举产生立法议会，1961年5月20日宪法通过后改称国民议会，直至1978年7月军事政变。1978 - 1992年间长期由军人统治，无议会。1991年7月12日通过新宪法，议会实行两院制，由国民议会和参议院组成。1992年3、4月间分别举行了国民议会和参议院的选举。2005年8月政变后，军政权宣布解散国民议会。2006年11-12月和2007年1月分别举行了新的国民议会和参议院选举。

摩洛哥 Morocco

阿拉维原为法国保护领，1956年11月18日独立，1956年起成立咨询国民议会，作为咨询机构。1958年颁布《王家宪法》，开始实行宪政。1962年11月宪法改为参、众两院制议会。1965年6月发生了暴乱，国王解散议会。1970年7月宪法实行一院制，称代表院。1972年8月未遂政变后哈桑二世宣布解散代表院。1977年10月，通过选举组成第二届代表院。根据1996年9月新宪法，开始实行两院制，议会由参议院和众议院组成，1997年11月举行首次选举。

沙特阿拉伯 Saudi Arabia

1921年8月伊本·沙特建立内志苏丹国；1924年8月开始攻伐汗志王国（1916年6月麦加大谢里夫自奥斯曼独立）。1924年12月19日设立了汗志本地委员会（Domestic Council，al-Majlis al-Ahli），协助处理汗志事务；1926年1月8日伊本·沙特即位汗志国王，同月13日组建协商会议（Consultative Council，Majlis al-Shura），以费萨尔亲王为协商会议主席。1932年5月12日协商会议制度最终确定，承担部分立法职责。1932年9月23日沙特阿拉伯王国建立。1992年3月1日，法赫德国王颁布治国基本法。1993年12月29日，协商会议正式成立。

1992.3 -

苏丹 Sudan

苏丹原为不列颠属地，1910年设置总督委员会，1943年1月设北苏丹咨询委员会，1948年设立立法会议，1954年改组为议会，由参众两院组成。1956年1月1日苏丹独立。1958年11月政变后议会被解散。1962年军政府组织了立法委员会，1965年4月选举产生制宪议会，1969年5月政变后被再次解散。1972年1月军政府组织了人民议会，并于1973年4月12日通过苏丹的第一部宪法。1985年4月政变后被废除，同年10月10日通过临时宪法，1986年4月举行了大选，成立了新议会。1989年6月巴希尔政变上台后，解散议会，冻结了1985年临时宪法。1992年2月，成立了过渡国民议会。1995年12月，过渡国民议会颁布第13号宪法法令，规定全国议会为国家最高权力机构，1996年3月举行了首次选举，1998年3月通过新宪法。1999年12月，巴希尔总统宣布解散议会，罢免议长图拉比。2000年12月，选举产生新一届议会。苏丹政府与南方反政府武装“苏丹人民解放运动”（SPLM）于2005年1月9日在内罗毕签署《全面和平协议》，苏丹内战宣告结束，苏丹于7月9日起进入为期六年的过渡期。根据协议，组成了过渡期立法机构，任期亦为六年，由国民议会和州议会组成。

网址：http://www.sudan-parliament.org/

突尼斯 Tunisia

1861年1月29日突尼斯颁布宪法，实行宪政，成立国务会议，是为阿拉伯及伊斯兰世界首个君主立宪宪法，1864年被废除。其后突尼斯成为法国保护领。1905年法兰西在突尼斯设立咨询会议(1922改称大议会)。1956年3月20日突尼斯独立，组成制宪议会。1957年7月25日突制宪会议通过决议，废黜国王，宣布成立突尼斯共和国。1959年成立国民议会。2002年5月通过宪法修正案，改为两院制，由众议院和参议院组成。2005年7月，突举行首次参议员选举。

网址

众议院：http://www.chambre-dep.tn/

土耳其 Turkey

1876年12月奥斯曼颁布基本法，实行宪政。1877年3月成立国会，由两院组成，1878年2月被废止，恢复君主专制政体。1908年7月爆发革命，再次实行宪政，恢复1876年宪法，组成帝国议会。1920年3月凯末尔宣布解散帝国议会，代之以大国民议会，4月23日正式组成。1922年废除君主制，建立共和政府，并改国名为土耳其。1960年5月政变后，组成制宪议会，1961年7月通过新宪法，规定大国民议会由参众两院组成。1980年9月政变后宪法中止，再次建立制宪议会，1982年11月通过新宪法，恢复一院制。

1876.08.31

Ottoman Sultan Murad V was deposed, and his younger half-brother Abdul Hamid II ascended the throne.

1876.09.10

A Committee called Cemiyet-I Mahsusa was established for preparation of the constitution, with Midhat Pasha as Chairman.

1876.12.19

Midhat Pasha was named Grand Vizier.

1876.12.23

The 1876 Constitution was signed by Abdul Hamid II. It created the Ottoman Parliament (also called General Assembly, Meclis-i Umumî), composed of a Senate (Meclis-i Âyân) as upper house and Chamber of Deputies (Meclis-i Mebusân) as lower house.

1877.03.19

Parliament convened. It adjourned on June 28. Ahmed Vefik Pasha and Issac Pasha presided over the Chamber and Server Pasha was President of Senate.

1877.12.13

Parliament convened for its second term. Hasan Fehmi Pasha was President of the Chamber.

1878.01.31

The Ottoman was defeated in the Russo-Turkish War and a truce was signed with Russia.

1878.02.14

Sultan Abdul Hamid II took the opportunity to prorogue the parliament, and with no election the Constitution was in fact suspended.

1908.07.23

Ottoman Sultan Abdul Hamid II announced the restoration of the 1876 Constitution and reconvening of the Parliament.

1908.12.17

The Senate reconvened for the first time in over 30 years. The Chamber elected Ahmed Riza Bey as Chairman.

1912.01.18

The Sultan dissolved the Parliament and asked for new election.

1912.04.18

The Parliament convened after new election and it was dissolved on August 5. President Halil Menteşe.

1913.01.23

Coup led by Committee of Union and Progress put Ottoman Empire under the leadership of the triumvirate known as the Three Pashas.

1914.05.14

The Paliament convened and it was dissolved on Dec 21, 1918 after Armistice of Mudros. President Halil Menteşe.

1920.01.12

The last convening of the Parliament.

1920.03.16

The Allied occupation of Constantinople, forced the de jure closure of the Parliament on March 18.

1920.04.11

The Sultan officially proclaimed the Parliament dissolved under the pressure from the Allies.

1920.04.23

The Grand National Assembly opened in Ankara, by the Committee of Rpresentation, headed by Mustafa Kemal.

1920.04.24

Mustafa Kemal Atatürk was elected President of the Grand National Assembly, and held this until Oct 29, 1923 when he was elected President of the Republic of Turkey.

1921.01.20

The first Turkish Constitution was ratified by the Grand National Assembly.

1923.10.29

Turkey became a Republic.

1924.04.20

New Constitution ratified, legislative power still on the unicamel Natioanl Assembly.

1960.05.27

Military coup put all members of the Assembly under arrest.

1960.06.12

The Parliament was legally abolished, and the Committee of National Unity (Milli Birlik Komitesi) assumed the powers of the Assembly by a provionsal constitution.

1961.01.06

The Constituent Assembly (Kurucu Meclis), named House of Representatives (TBMM 1961 Temsilciler Meclisi) was established to draft a new constitution. Kazim Orbay elected Speaker on Jan 9. Constitutional Committee under presidency of Enver Ziya Karal ve Turhan Feyzioğlu.

1961.05.27

The Constituent Assembly adopted the new Constitution, bicameral parliament composed of a National Assembly and a Senate (Cumhuriyet Senatosu).

1961.07.09

Constitution Referendum.

1961.10.15

General Election. New Parliament opened on Oct 25.

1980.09.12

Military coup led by Chief of the General Staff Kenan Evren extended the martial law, abolished the Parliament and the Government, and suspended the Constitution.

1981.06.29

The Law on the Establishment of the Constituent Assembly issued by the National Security Council (Millî Güvenlik Konseyi, MGK), the Constituent Assembly consisted of MGK and the Advisory Council (TBMM 1981 Danışma Meclisi, DM).

1981.10.23

The Advisory Council opened. Sadi Irmak elected President on Oct 27.

1981.11.20

A Constitutional Commission was established with Orhan Aldıkaçtı as Chairperson.

1982.07.17

The Constitution was submitted to the Advisory Council, and it was adopted by the Constituent Assembly on October 18, 1982. It provided a unicameral parliament, the Turkish Grand National Assembly.

1982.11.07

Constitution Referendum.

1983.11.06

General Election. New Parliament opened on November 24, 1983.

叙利亚 Syria

叙利亚1516年成为奥斯曼属地，1918年9月30日英国远征军攻占大马士革，叙利亚独立，但随即为法兰西占领。1919年6月举行首次选举，成立国民大会（Syrian National Congress），准备组织宪法。1920年3月8日宣布费萨尔为国王，但7月即被法国当局逼迫退位，国民议会也被解散。1920年9月法国拼凑了阿勒频、大马士革、德鲁兹山区等国。1922年6月成立联邦会议（Federal Council），将阿勒颇、大马士革组成叙利亚联邦，并成为法兰西委任统治地，此后在各组成国设立代表委员会（Representative Council）。1925年1月1日叙利亚联邦改称叙利亚国，各代表委员会合并，行使议会职能。1928年4月组织制宪议会（Syrian Constituent Assembly），1929年2月即被法国当局强行休会。1930年5月14日法国公布法国托管下的宪法，组建议会（Assembly of Deputies）。1932年6月议会开幕，叙利亚名义上独立，1933年11月被法国终止；1936年12月恢复，1939年7月议会再次被法国当局解散，并暂停宪法。1941年7月，维希政府的控制结束，9月27日，自由法国名义宣布叙利亚独立。直到1943年3月宪法才得以恢复，7月议会恢复，并组织了第一个叙利亚政府。迟至1946年4月17日法国才完成全部撤军，叙利亚才真正获得独立。1949年3月胡斯尼·扎阿姆政变上台，中止宪法并解散议会，同年8月被推翻并处死，宪法及议会得以恢复。1949年12月制宪议会开幕（Constituent Assembly），1950年9月通过新宪法，保持一院制的议会。1951年12月施舍克里政变后解散议会，1953年6月炮制新宪法，7月当选总统，10月组织议会，1954年2月施舍克里被迫辞职，1950年民选政府和宪法、议会得以恢复。1958年2月埃及与叙利亚合并为阿拉伯联合共和国，3月组建了联合的国民议会（National Assembly），1961年9月叙利亚退出，联盟解体。1963年3月阿拉伯复兴社会党上台后，再次解散议会。1964年4月临时宪法规定国家革命委员会（National Revolutionary Council）行使立法职权，1965年9月正式成立，1966年2月政变后被终止。1970年11月哈菲兹·阿萨德通过纠正运动夺取政权，1971年2月成立人民议会（People’s Assembly）。，1973年3月12日通过新宪法，规定一院制的人民议会。2012年2月26日通过新宪法。

1918.09.30

The Egyptian Expeditionary Force under British Commander Edmund Allenby captured Damascus.

1918.10.03

Faisal bin Hussein ented the city of Damascus.

1918.10.05

Faisal announced the establishment of a fully and absolutely independent Arab constitutional government, and appointed General Rida Rikabi to head the government.

1919.05.05

Faysal made an important address calling for the creation of a Syrian National Congress.

1919.06.03

The first session of the Syrian Congress was held in Damascus. Hashim Atassi was elected to preside the congress. (some commentators claim that Mohamed Fawzi Al- Azzem was the fi rst elected president of the Syrian congress a few weeks before his death and that Hashim Atassi subsequently became its second president). In July 1919, a Constitutional Commission from Comgress members was appointed with Hashim Atassi as Chairman, and it was tasked to draft a constitution. This is not finished till its dissolve in July 1920, but it did set the legislature as a parliamentary monarchy with two chambers, the Senate and the General Assembly of Deputies.

1920.03.08

The independence of the Kingdom of Syria was proclaimed. (the Syrian Congress inaugurated on March 6 and passed the Declaration of Independence on March 7.) The Syrian congress reaffirmed its representative legitimacy and considered itself to be representative of ‘the Syrian nation’ in these three geographical regions, namely the inland, coastal, and Palestinian zones.

1920.03.09

The first monarchic government was formed under Rida Rikabi. It presented ints programe to the Congress on March 27 and secured a vote of confidence.

1920.05.02

The Rikabi cabinet resigned, and it was replaced on May 8 by a government formed by Hashim Atassi, the President of the Congress.

1920.07.14

The Frech issued an ultimatum to the Syrian to submit to French control and Faysal surrendered, bringing to an end of the Kingdom. The Syrian Congress suspended its work on July 19.

1920.07.25

Following the defeat in the Battle of Maysalun and French entering Damascus, the French rule was officially reinstalled. A new government was named with Alaa el-Din Droubi as Prime Minister.

1920.08.21

Droubi was ambushed and killed during a tour of the Hawran.

1920.09.01

The State of Aleppo was declared by French High Commissioner Henri Gouraud.

1920.09.01

The State of Greater Lebanon was declared. (see Lebanon)

1920.09.02

A Territory of Alawis was created under direct French rule.

1920.09.03

The State of Damascus was declared by French High Commissioner Henri Gouraud.

1921.05.01

The Druze State was formed. On March 4, 1922 it was proclaimed as the State of Souaida. In 1927 it was renamed Jabel Druze State.

1921.10.20

Sanjak of Alexandretta became autonomous under Treaty of Ankara. In 1923 it was attached to the State of Aleppo, and in 1925 attached to the State of Syria.

1922.06.28

Henri Gouraud announced the Syrian Federation which included the states of Damascus, Aleppo and the Alawite State. A Federal Council was appointed by the High Commissioner which elected Subhi Barakat as President of the Syrian Federation at its first meeting in late July 1922. In June 1923 the High Commissioner decided to bestow Representative Councils on the Stztes of Damascus, Aleppo and Alawi.

1923.10.29

Final election to the Representative Council. Mu’ayyad al-Azm Presiendt of the Damascus Representative Council.

1925.01.01

The Syrian Federation became the State of Syria. (decree on 5 Dec 1924). Lebanon and the Alawi State were not included. The two elected Respresentative Councils of Damascus and Aleppo wewe merged to assume the functions of a Parliament.

1928.05.09

The Syrian Constituent Assembly met in Damascus (election in April) and elected Hashim Atassi to preside over it. The drafting Committee was led by Ibrahim Hananu. The Assembly was prorogued sine die on 5 Feb 1929.

1930.05.14

Founding Constitution of the Syrian Republic under the French Mandate was promulgated, providing a single chamber Assembly of Deputies. The Constituent Assembly thus dissolved.

1930.05.14?

The Alawite State was renamed as the Government of Latakia.

1932.01.04

Parliamentary Election held between 20 Dec 1931 and 4 Jan 1932.

1932.06.07

The Parliament opened for a one-week session, elected Subhi Barakat as Presiednt of the Chamber (June 7), and Ali Abed as President of the Republic (June 11). President Abed appointed Haqqi al-Azem as Prime Miniser on June 15.

1933.11.18

The Chamber opened and Barakat reelected President of the Chamber. Thre Chamber was susupended by the French High Commissioner for the rest of the session on Nov 24.

1934.03.16

Sheigh Taj al-Din al-Hasani formed a new government replacing Haqqi Bey al-Azm.

1934.11.02

The Chamber of Deputies was suspended sine die by the Frehch Hign Commissioner.

1936.09.09

Franco-Syrian Treaty of Independence signed in Paris.

1936.11.30

Parliamentary election held on Nov 14 and Nov 20.

1936.12.05

The Alawite State was incorporated into Syrian Republic.

1936.12.02

The Jabel Druze State was incorporated into Syrian Republic.

1936.12.21

The Chamber of Deputies met in Damascus. The eldest parliamentarian Muhammad Yahya al-adali occupied the Speaker’s chair until Faris al-Khuri elected Speaker. Hashim Atassi elected next President of the Republic, who appointed Jamil Mardam Bay as Prime Minsiter.

1938.07.05

Turkish military entered into the Sanjak of Alexandretta and the Sanjak Assembly based on people registration on July 22 favoured Turkey. On Sep 2, 1938 the Sanjak Assembly proclaimed the State of Hatay, which was officially set on on Sept 7. A referendum on June 29, 1939 voted to join Turkey which was turned into Hatay Province of Turkey de jure on July 7, and de facto on July 23, 1939.

1938.12.14

The French Parliament refused to ratify the Franco-Syrian Treaty.

1939.02.18

Jamil Mardam Bay resigned as Prime Minister.

1939.02.23

Lufti al-Haffar succeeded Jamil Mardam Bay as Prime Minister, but it lasted barely a month and was forced to resign on March 16.

1939.04.06

A non-party Ministry under Nasuhi al-Bukhari was formed and it resigned on May 15, while keep in office before a new nominations.

1939.07.07

The French High Commissioner issued autonomy to the Druze and Alawite regions. President Atasi immdediately resigned from his position.

1939.07.10

The French Hign Commissioner published a decree suspending the Syrian Constitution, dissolving the Chamber, and appointed a Council of Departmental Directors-General under Bahij al-Khatib.

1941.03.15

Bahij al-Khatib resigned from his position.

1941.04.04

A Cabinet of Khalid al-Azm formed. A Council of State charged with the preparation of new legislation was placed under Abd al-Qadir al-Azm.

1941.07.14

The Vichy government's control of Lebanon and Syria ended with an armistice signed in Acre.

1941.09.17

Sheikh Tajeddine Al- Hasni was appointed Head of State. He asked Hassan al-Hakim to form a new government on Sept 20. Th e cabinet remained in offi ce until April 1942 and was replaced by one led by Hosni Barazi, which in turn was superseded in January 1943, days aft er the death of the head of state Tajeddine Al- Hasni, by a new government led by Jamil Al- Ulshi.

1941.09.27

General Catroux officially handed over to the Syrian Government, declaration of the independence of Syria.

1942.12.12

Druze and Alawite territories were reintegrated into Syria by France.

1943.03.25

The Constitution was restored by France, and an interim government led by Atta Ayubi was appointed, whose main duty was to prepare Syria for elections.

1943.07.26

Parliamentary election heled on July 10 and July 26.

1943.08.17

Parliament opened, Shukri Qwatli elecced President of the Republic and Fares Khouri President of the Chamber, and he appointed Saadallah Jabri as Prime Minister on August 19.

1944.10.12

Prime Minister Saadallah Jabri announced his resignation. On Oct 14, Fares Khouri was given the premiershop and Jabri was elected President of the Chamber.

1946.04.17

The last of French troops left Syria and Syria won its independence.

1948.04.17

The Constitution was revised and the Deputies of the Chamber reelected President Qwatli to a second term.

1948.12.01

Prime Minister Jamil MArdam resigned. He was replaced by Khaled al-Azzem on Dec 16, 1948.

1949.03.30

General Husni Al-Zaim, head of the General Staff, led the first coup d’état in Syria. He dissolved the Chamber and abolished the 1928 Constitution, and ousted President Qwatli.

SUMMARY OF THE FIRST SYRIAN REPUBLIC (1920-1949)
  1. The 1928 constituent assembly exercised its functions for several weeks before being suspended and then dissolved by the mandatory power.
  2. The legislative assembly elected in late 1931 and early 1932 operated normally for a few months and was then suspended by the high commissioner in 1933.
  3. After the 1936 negotiation and the signing of the Franco- Syrian treaty, the country was to experience for three years a bumpy political life that was marked especially by France abandoning the sanjak of Alexandretta to Turkey. In July 1939, the high commissioner dissolved parliament aft er the president’s resignation.
  4. Constitutional political life was restored by France in 1943, that is, three years before actual independence.
  5. The first coup in March 1949 dissolved the Parliament and abolished the 1928 Constitution.

1949.04.11

General Zaim announced by decree the dissolution of Parliament and the establishment of a Constitutional Committee entrusted to draft a new Constitution. The Committee was headed by Asad Kourani, and it submitted the draft Constitution on June 27, 2 days after the referendum which has changed the original drcree to draft constitution before the referendum. (a single chamber Assembly of Deputies was proposed) Thus a new Constitution Committee was appointed with Mohsen Barazi as lead, but the new committee did not have time to complete its work because of the new coup that overthrew the regime on 14 Aug 1949.

1949.04.17

Husni Al- Zaim formed a government, making himself prime minister and minister of defence.

1949.06.25

A referendum on presidential powers was held alongside a referendum on Husni al-Za'im's candidacy for the presidency. After winning the referendum, Zaim appointed Mohsen Barazi as Prime Minister.

1949.08.14

General Sami Hinnawi conducted a coup. Prsident Zaim and Prime Minister Barzai were executed.

1949.08.15

Sami Hinnawi invited former President Hashim Atassi to form a provisional cabinet to ensure the transition to a legitimately elected government.

1949.11.15

Constituent Assembly election.

1949.12.12

The Constituent Assembly held its first meeting and elected Rushdi Kikhyia Speaker. A provisional Constitution was passed on same day. Atassi was elected Head of State (Provisonal President) on Dec 14. On Dec 28 a Constitution Committee headed by Nazem Kudsi was appointed.

1949.12.19

Colonel Adib Shishakli led a new coup overthrew Hinnawi, but kept the Constituent Assembly and Head of State.

1949.12.24

Head of State Atassi tasked Nazem Kudsi with forming a new government, but he dissolved his cabinet the next day due to pressure from the general staff.

1949.12.27

President Atassi called on the moderate Khaled al-Azm to form a new government, which was finally approved on Jan 7, 1950.

1950.05.29

Prime Minister Khaled Azm resigned, and Nazem Kudsi was asked to form a government the next day.

1950.09.05

The 1950 Constitution was adopted by the Constituent Assembly (single- chamber approach Assembly of Deputies). Th e assembly then elected Hashim Atassi president under the new constitution, aft er which the assembly became the legislative assembly. Nazim Kudsi was again appointed Prime Minister.

1951.03.09

Prime Minister Nazim Kudsi presented his resignation, and he failed another bid to form a government on March 23 due to Shishakli’s veto. In protest, Rushdi al- Kikhiya resigned from the Assembly Speaker. Only on March 27, Khaled al-Azm formed a neutral government of independents.

1951.07.30

Prime Minister Khaled Azm dissolved his government and presented his resignation. On August 9 President asked Hassan al-Hakim to form a new government.

1951.10.24

Hassan Hakim presented his resignation to President Atassi but agreed to remain in office until Nov 10.

1951.11.28

Ma’aruf Dawalibi formed a government and he refused to change his cabinet per military requrst. In the early morning of Nov 29, Shishakli arrested the Prime Minsiter and his government. On Dec 1 Dawalibi officially resigned from office.

1951.12.02

President Atassi resigned and on the same day Adib Shishakli dissolved the Legislative Assembly by military decree. On December 3 Shishaki conferred full legislative and executive powers to Fawzi Selo, his second-hand military man, who assumed the authority of Head of State, Prime Minister and Misister of Defense.

1952.06.08

A Council of Ministers was created to assist the Head of State in the exercise of his executive and legislative functions. On June 9 Genebral Selo formed a traditional cabinet. On August 2 he created the position of deputy prime minister measure for Shishakli.

1953.06.21

The 1953 Constitution was published. A modern presidential constitution, with a single chamber Assembly of Deputies.

1953.07.10

The Constitution was approved and Shishakli was elected President by referendum. He formed his cabinet on July 15.

1953.10.09

Praliament Election.

1953.10.24

The Assembly met for the first time and elected Maamun Kuzbari as Speaker.

1954.02.25

President Shishakli resigned under pressure from military commanders and left Syria for Lebanon. Speaker Kuzbari declared himself interim president under Constitution, but he was aksed to resign which he complied on Feb 26. A consensus formed on the need to return to the 1950 constitution, to restore the parliament elected that year for the remainder of its legislature, and to restore President Hashim Atassi to office.

1954.03.01

Hashim Atassi returned to Damascus and resumed the functions as President. He officially accepted the resignation of Maaruf Dawalibi as Prime Misniter, and appointed Sabri al-Assali to form a new government.

1954.03.16

The 1949 Assembly dissolved by Shishaki was reconvened.

1954.06.11

Sabri al-Assali resigned and was succeed by Said al-Ghazi, who formed a non-partisan Government on June 19.

1954.10.05

Parliamentary election held on Sept 24-25 and a second round Oct 4-5.

1954.10.14

The new legislature met for the first time and Nazim al-Kudsi elected Speaker of the Assemly. President Atassi accepted the resignation of Said Ghazi, and Fares Khoury formed a cabinet on Oct 29.

1955.02.07

Fares Khoury government was brought down following the failure of the Cairo Arab Premier’s Conference and waves of unrest in Damascus by Nasserist elements.

1955.02.13

President called on Sabri al-Assali to form a new cabinet.

1955.08.18

Shukri al-Kuwatly won the presidential election, and he was sworn in on Sept 5, 1955.

1955.09.06

The government of Sabri al-Assali was dissolved following new President’s swearing-in. Said al-Ghazi formed a new government.

1956.06.03

Prime Minister Said al-Ghazi resigned following student demonstration. Sabri al-Assali formed a new government on June 14.

1958.02.01

United Arab Republic proclaimed.

1958.02.21

Referendum on the formation of the UAR and appointing Gamal Nasser as its President held in both Egypt and Syria. UAR formally inaugurated on Feb 22.

1958.03.05

The provisional constitution was promulgated, an abridged form of the Egyptian 1956 Constitution. The legislative power was vested in a National Assemblym which at least half of its members mustbe members of the Syrian Chamber of Deputies and the National Assembly of Egypt.

1958.03.06

President Nasir declared the nomination of four vice-presidents (Syrians Asali and Hourani and Egyptians Amir and Baghdadi) and appointed the government (eight-member federal cabinet and eleven-member each regional cabinets).

1958.04.01

A Presidential decree established the Executive Councils. Abd al-Latif Baghadadi nominated to head the Egyptian EC, and Hourani became head of the Syrian EC.

1958.10.07

President Nasir announced the reorganization of the UAR government. Chairman of the Egyptian EC was Nur al-Din Tarraf, and that of the Syrian EC Nur al0Din Kahalah.

1960.09.20

President Nasir announced the reshuffle of the central government and the Syrian Executive Council, and appointed Abdul Hamid Sarraj President of the Syrian EC.

1961.08.16

A Presidential decree dissolved the central government and two regional executive councils, replacing them with a unified central cabinet. The new government included seven vice-presidents, with two Syrians, Kahalah and Sarraj.

1961.09.28

A military coup in Damascus put the UAR to an end.

1961.09.29

The Supreme Arab Revolutionary Command of the Armed Forces (SARCAF) entrusted Maamun al-Kuzbari to form a government.

1961.11.15

A provisional constitution was promulgated, explicitly declared sovereign independence. All major followed 1950 Constitution, a Clnstituent and Legislative Assembly shall be elected to compose a new Constitution and after that the Constituent Assembly shall change into a Legislative Assembly.

1961.11.20

A government led by Izzat al-Nuss was appointed in preparation for the coming election.

1961.12.02

Parliamentary election held Dec 1-2.

1961.12.12

Maamun Kuzbari was elected Speaker. On Dec 14, Nazem Kudsi was elected President and he appointed Maaruf Dawalibi as Prime Minister on Dec 22.

1962.03.25

Prime Minister Dawalibi resigned under pressure from the army.

1962.03.28

Colonel Adb al-Karim al-Nahlawi carried out his second coup, had the President and the Prime Minister arrested, and dissoved the Assembly. Geneal Abdel-Karim Zahr El-Din was confirmed as Commander-in-Chief by SARCAF, and de facto leader of the country.

On March 31, an insurrection was led by commander-in-chief of the central region Colonel Badr Alassar in Homes. General Zahr El-Din convened an army congress in Homs on April 1, and it was decided to have Colonel Nehlawi removed from Syria, and .to restore the constitutional life He left on the next day.

1962.04.13

Nazim Kudsi restored as President. A new cabinet headed by Ahmad Bashir al-Azmah was formed on April 16, 1962.

1962.09.11

The dissolved Assembly was convened at Khaled al-Azzem’s home, and it was chaired by then Deputy Speaker Rafik Bashur. The Assembly voted for 1950 Cosntitution to be in effect with amendments suggested by Azzem.

1962.09.13

The Assembly passed the Constituion amendements, it then ceased to be a Constituent Assembly and became a Legislative Assembly. Khaled Al- Azzem was approved in a vote of confi dence to form a new government, and the Assemply elected Fawzi Ghazi to succeed Kuzbari as speaker. Azzem’s cabinet formed on Sept 17.

1963.03.08

A coup, leb by Commander of the Syrian-Israeli front Ziad Hariri, established National Revolutionary Command Council, with Luay Atassi as its Chairman. The Council gave itself executive, legislative and judicial powers. Hariri replaced Zahr El-Din as Chief of Staff. Salah al-Bitar was appointed Prime Minister on March 9.

1963.05.11

The first cabinet of Salah al-Bitar, a Ba'athist-Nasserite coalition government, was dissolved. He presented a new cabinet on May 13.

1963.06.23

The Military Committee demoted Ziad Hariri to become Syris’s military attaché in Washington. After all struggle in vain, Zaid left for France and resigned from all his posts on July 8.

1963.07.18

A coup attempt by Nasserist officiers was crashed by Ba'athists. Luay Atassi was removed as National Revolutionary Command Council Chairman on July 27 and replaced by Amin al-Hafez.

1963.08.04

Salah al-Bitar formed a new cabinet full of Ba'athists and unionist independents.

1963.11.11

Salah al-Bitar cabinet was resolved. Amin al-Hafez succeeded him as Prime Minister on November 12.

1964.04.14

Amin Hafez’s government resigned after harshly quelled disorder throughtout the county.

1964.04.25

The Provisional Constitution was promulgated by a presidential decree. The National Revolutionary Council (NRC), previously known as the National Council of Revolutionary Command (NCRC), became the state’s legislative body. It was also to elect the members of the Presidential Council including its president and vice president. The NRC was also responsible for revising the provisional constitution and had to prepare the draft for the permanent constitution.

1964.05.04

The new National Revolutionary Council elected a Presidential Council of five members (Amin Hafez as President, Salah Jadid, Mohammad Umran, Nuredin Atassi and Yusef Zuayin). This Council was dissolved the next day and replaced with following members (Amin Hafez as President, Salah Bitar as Vice-President, Umran, Shibli Aysami and Mansur Atrash).

1964.05.23

Salah al-Bitar formed a new government, ushered in a more liberal period.

1964.10.04

Amin Hafez replaced Bitar as Prime Minister, with a more radical government.

1965.09.01

The National Revolutionary Council met for the first time, Mansur al-Atrash was elected its President.

1965.09.23

The Yusef Zuayin governemtn was formed afrer the creation of the National Revolutionary Council.

1965.12.21

The Regional Command dissolved the Regional Command and dismissed the Zuayin cabinet. Salah Bitar formed a new government on Jan 1, 1966.

1966.02.23

The ruling Ba'th National Command was removed by a coup led by Ba’th Provisional Regional Command (PRC). It announced the suspension of the 1964 provisional constitution, the dissolution of the NRC and the Presidential Council.

1966.02.25

The PRC appointed Nuredin Atassi as Head of State. It also decied legislative power was to be exercised by the council of ministers via legislative decrees that were to be approved by an absolute majority.

1966.03.01

The PRC tasked Yusef Zuayin with forming the new government.

1969.05.01

The 1968 Provisional Constitution was promiulgated, and Ba'ath rule was formalized for the first time. It was decided to elect a People’s Assembly to exercise legislative power and draw up a permanent constitution.

1970.10.18

In the face of the revived rivalry between Salah Jadid and Hafez Assad, Nuredin Atassi submitted his resignation as head of state.

1970.11.16

Asad’s Corrective Movement announced a provisional Ba'ath Provisional Regional Command (PRC) and promised a People’s Assembly and a permanent Constitution within 90 days.

1970.11.18

Ahmed Khatib was appointed Head of State and Hafez Asad Prime Minister.

1971.02.16

The PRC appointed a People’s Assembly. On Feb 17, the PRC amended the 1969 Provisional Constitution, reintroduced the position of President of the Republic, and it also provided a People’s Assembly to be elected that served as the parliament.

1971.02.22

The Peoples’ Assembly met for the first time, and Head of State Ahmed Khatib resigned as Head of State and was elected President of the Assembly.

1971.03.12

Hafez Asad was elected President of the Republic and he took office in March 14.

1971.04.03

A new cabinet was formed with Abd al-Rahman Khulayfawi as Prime Minister.

1971.12.26

Ahmed Khatib resigned as Speaker to become Prime Minister of the Federation of Arab Republics, and he was replaced by Fehmi el-Yusefi, who supervised the preparatory work for the permanent constitution by a special commission directed by Mazhar al-Anbari.

1973.03.12

The 1973 Constitution was adopted by a referendum and it was promulgated by the President the next day. It kept the one chamber legislative People’s Assembly.

2011.10.15

President Bashar Assad established a National Committee headed by Mazhar al-Anbari to draft a new Constitution.

2012.02.26

The 2012 Constitution passed in a referendum and it was put into effect the next day.

也门 Yemen

[北]也门 [Northern] Yemen (Sana)

卡西姆（约1905年起称也门）原为奥斯曼附庸国，1918年10月获得独立。1926年9月改称也门穆塔瓦基利亚王国。1962年9月废除君主制，建立共和政体，成立阿拉伯也门共和国。此后保皇派与共和派发生内战，直至1970年。1969年3月成立国务委员会，1970年12月通过宪法，1971 年2月成立协商议会，1974年6月哈马迪政变上台后被废止。1977年10月加什米上台后逐步恢复民主，组建了制宪议会。在他于1978年6月遇刺身亡后，制宪议会改称人民议会，1988年7月依照1970年宪法，协商议会得以恢复。1990年5月南北门合并为也门共和国。

1918.10.30

The Ottoman Turkish army concluded the Armistice of Mudros, and it withdrew from Hijaz, Asir and Yemen.

1924.08.06

Treaty of Lausanne (signed 23 Aug 1923) took into effect and formally freed Yemen from the Turks.

1926.09.02

Mutawakkilite Kingdom of Yemen internationally recognized.

1948.02.17

Imam Yahya was assassinated and Abdullah bin Ahmed a-Wazir seized the throne. The new Imam claimed a Shura Council on Feb 20, with Saif al-Haq Ibrahim (Yahya’s eighth son) as Shura Chairman, Ali al-Wazir Prime Minister of his new Council of Ministers. He was defeated by elderest son og Yahya, Ahmed, and was executed on April 8. (His Prime Minister also killed on June 30)

1962.09.19

Imam Ahmad was reported dead.

1962.09.26

New Imam al-Badr was overthrown by Abdullah al-Sallal. On Sept 28 Sallal formed a cabinet with himself as Prime Minister and Army Commander-in-Chief. Meanwhile a Revolutionary Council headed by Sallal and a Presidential Council headed by Mohammed Alo Osman.

1962.10.31

A Provisional Constitution was published, the country would be ruled by a National Council, who would promulgate a law for election to first Parliament. Abdullah al-Sallal became President while keeping the title of Prime Minister, Abdul Rahman al-Baidani Vice President. (Baidani was dismissed all positions on Feb 18, 1963, and Hassan al-Amri replaced him as Vice President. ).

1963.04.13

President Sallal promulgated a Provisional Constitution, provided a Presidential Council (with President as the Chairman) to determine state policies, a Executive Council responsible to the Presidential Council, and suggested a Parliament of 25 sheikhs representing the principal tribes. On April 26 the Presidential Council was elected and the Executive Council appointed with Abdul Latif Dhaifallah as Chairman (Prime Minister).

1963.10.05

President Sallal appointed two more Vice Presidents, Mohammad Ali Osman and Abdul Rahman al-Iryani. Iryani was also Chairman of the Executive Council.

1964.01.07

Presideny Sallal issued a decree to establish a Political Bureau to be the highest authority for political and legislative affairs, which superceded and de facto replaced the Presidential Council. The PB was presided by the President.

1964.04.28

A new Constitution was proclaimed, abolished the Political Bureau and the Executive Council. It envisaged the creatio of a Consultative Assembly entrused the legialative power and election the President of the Republic. On April 29 Hamoud al-Jaifi was Appointed Prime Minister and Ahmed Muhammad Numan Chairman of the Consultative Council. Hasan al-Amri named Vice President under the new Constitution.

1964.12.12

Chairman of the Consultative Council Ahmed Muhammad Numan resigned in protest to the government’s peace talk policies. Also resigned Vice Prime Ministers Abdul Rahman al-Iryani and Muhammad Mahmoud al-Zubairi.

1965.01.05

Preme Minister Hamoud al-Jaifi was replaced by pro-Sallal Hassan al-Amri, and the new cabinet formed on Jan 6.

1965.04.20

After Muhammad Mahmoud al-Zubairi’s assassination on April 1, President Sallal was under pressure.

Hassan al-Amri was foced to resign as Prime Minister, Ahmed Muhammad Numan was appointed to form a new government and his cabinet announced on April 24.

1965.05.08

President Sallal was obliged to announce a new interim Constitution, which provides for a parliamentary democracy and an independent judiciary. The President was now subject to a Republican Council (al-Madjlis al-Djumhuri) with himself as Chairman and a Consultative Assembly (Madjlis al-Shura).

1965.05.28

President formed a Supreme Defense Council (with Hamoud al-Jaifi as Chairman and Prime Minister and several other ministers as members), and a Commttee for tribal affairs (headed by Husayn al-Difai), which he didn’t consult with the Prime Minister.

1965.07.01

Prime Minsiter Numan and his cabinet resigned, but he was asked to remain in power pending the negotiation with the UAR. On July 6 President Sallal appointed himself as Prime Minsiter, but he revoked this order on July 11, allegedly under pressure from Egyptian President Nassir. He appointed Hassan al-Amri to form a new government on July 18, and the new cabinet announced on July 20.

1966.09.16

Prime Minister Hassan al-Amri’s resignation was announced, and President Sallal became the new Prime Minister as a new cabinet was announded on Sept 18. There’s rumor that Amri has been arrested by UAR and this was confirmed by Sallal on Sept 30.

1967.10.12

President Sallal reshuffled the cabinet and he kept the posts of Prime Minister and Foreign Minister.

1967.11.05

President Sallal was ousted by a bloodless military copu. A 3-members Republican Council headed by Abdul Rahman al-Iryani, members are Ahmad Muhammad Numan and Muhammad Ali Osman. Mohsin al-Aini was named new Prime Minister.

1967.12.18

The cabinet of Mohsin al-Aini resigned. Hassan al-Amri became the new Prime Minister, and he named his cabinet on December 23.

1968.09.15

Hassan al-Amri formed a new cabinet.

1968.09.25

The President issued a decree and decied the formation of the Provisional National Council.

1969.03.15

The Republican Council and the Cabinet resigned so that the new National Council could make necessary eletions.

1969.03.17

The National Council held its first meeting. On March 21 the Presidential Council was elected and composed of Iryani, Amri and Osman. Amri formed a new cabinet by April 3.

1969.07.08

Prime Minister Hassan al-Amri resigned for medical reasons. Deputy Prime Minister Abdul Salam Sabrah was appointed acting Prime Minister.

1969.09.02

Abdullah Kurshumi was named new Prime Minister.

1970.02.01

Presidnt Iryani accepted the resignation of Prime Minister Abdullah Kurshumi. He named Mohsin al-Aini as Prime Minister on Feb 5.

1970.12.28

First permanent Constitution was announced, providing a Consultative Council (Majlis al-Shura) to be elected and it would choose a Presidential Council.

1971.02.25

Prime Minister Mohsin al-Aini presented his government’s resignation in preparation for the election. Deputy Prime Minister Abdul Salam Sabrah was appointed acting Prime Minister.

1971.03.10

Parliamentary election.

1971.04.19

The Consultative Council met for the first time and elected Shaykh Abdallah al-Ahmar Speaker. On April 26 the new Republican Council was elected with Iryani as President. A new cabinet headed by Ahmad Muhammad Numan was announced on May 3.

1971.07.20

Prime Minister Ahmad Muhammad Numan resigned. Hassan al-Amri was appointed Prime Minister on August 20, and his cabinet formed on August 24.

1971.09.04

It was announced that Prime Minister al-Amri resigned all his posts, Prime Minister, Commander-in-Chief, and membership in Republican Council. Abdul Salam Sabrah acted as Prime Minister. It was later reported Amri was forced to resign by President Iryani after Amri killed a shipkeeper who unknowingly insulted him. (his membership in the Republican Council was replaced by Adballah al-Hajari on June 13, 1972)

1971.09.18

A new cabinet was announced with Mohsin al-Aini as Prime Minister.

1972.12.28

Mohsin al-Aini resigned as Prime Minsiter. Qadi Abdullah al-Hajri formed a cabinet on Dec 30.

1974.02.10

Prime Minister Qadi Abdullah al-Hajri resigned. Hassan Muhammad Makki became acting Prime Minister, and he named a new cabinet on March 3.

1974.06.13

Yemeni military seized power in a bloodless coup. A seven members Command Council was set up with Ibrahim Muhammad al-Hamadi as Chairman. The Constitution suspended the legislature dissolved.

1974.06.22

A new cabinet with Mohsin al-Aini as Prime Minister was formed.

1974.10.22

The ruling Command Council issued a Constitutional Declaration making the Chairman of the Command Council as Head of State during the transition period.

1975.01.16

Chairman Hamadi dismissed Prime Minister Mohsin al-Aini. Abdul Aziz Abdul Ghani was named on Jan 23, and he formed a cabinet on Jan 25.

1977.10.11

Chairman Hamadi assassinated. Ahmad al-Ghashmi became new Command Council Chairman.

1978.02.06

The Command Council issued a proclamation setting up a Constituent People’s Assembly, which opened on Feb 25 and elected Abd al-Karim al-Arashi as Speaker.

1978.04.22

Chairman Ghashmi was elected President of the Republic. Abdul Ghani formed a new cabnie on May 30.

1978.06.24

President Ghashmi was killed by a bomb exploded when he met with a South Yemen envoy. A new Presidential Council was formed, with Abd al-Karim al-Arashi as Chairman.

1978.07.17

Ali Abdullah Saleh was elected President by the People’s Assembly.

1980.10.15

Abd al-Karim al-Irtani formed a new cabinet.

1983.05.22

Ali Abdullah Saleh was reelected President by the People’s Assembly.

1983.11.13

Abdul Ghani formed a new cabinet.

1988.07.05

Parliamentary election. It inaugurated on July 17, and Saleh reelected President. Abdul Ghani was reappointed as Prime Minsiter on July 28 and he formed a new cabinet on July 31.

1988.07 – 1990.05

Majlis Alshoora

Consultative Council

*协商议会

[南]也门 [Southern] Yemen (Aden)

  1. 亚丁1839年1月19日被英国东印度公司侵占，成为英属印度孟买管辖区（Bombay Presidency）属下的亚丁定居地（Aden Settlement），1932年成为首席专员省（Chief Commissioner's Province of Aden），1937年4月1日脱离英属印度成为独立的直辖殖民地（Aden Colony）。
  2. 亚丁被侵占后，英国的势力逐渐从东西两面渗透内陆地区，最终1874年建立亚丁保护国。1917年，亚丁保护国的控制权由英属印度政府转移至英国外交部。行政上，非正式划分为东部保护国（Eastern Protectorate）与西部保护国（Western Protectorate）。
  3. 1959年2月11日，原属于亚丁保护国的六个苏丹国、酋长国和教长国组建了南阿拉伯酋长国联邦（Federation of the Arab Emirates of the South）；伺候又有九个苏丹国和酋长国加入联邦，1962年4月4日更名为南阿拉伯联邦（Federation of South Arabia）。
  4. 1963年1月18日，亚丁直辖殖民地重组为亚丁国（State of Aden），加入南阿拉伯联邦；同时，亚丁保护国中拒绝加入南阿拉伯联邦的4个邦组建了南阿拉伯保护国（Protectorate of South Arabia），就此亚丁保护国不再存在。
  5. 1967年11月30日，英军撤离，民族解放阵线随即占领亚丁，南也门人民共和国（People's Republic of South Yemen）宣告成立，南阿拉伯联邦和南阿拉伯保护国宣告终结。

1947年不列颠在亚丁殖民地设立立法会议（Legislative Council），1月6日召开首次会议。1955年起立法会议开始有选举成员，

1967年11月南也门独立，称南也门人民共和国，1970年11月改称也门人民民主共和国。1970年成立最高人民委员会，主席团主席为国家元首（自1978年起）。1990年5月南北门合并为也门共和国。

1947.01.06

Opening meeting of Aden’s first Legislative Council.

1958.11.18

Aden Colony (Amendment) Order, 1958 came into force. The Legislative Council to be consisted of 12 elected, 4 ex-officio and 6 nominated members with an impartial Speaker appointed by the Governor.

Arthur Eber Sydney Charles (b. 6.1.1910 – d. 1.9.1965) was appointed the first Speaker in Jan 1959. He was assassinated on Sept 1, 1965 on this post.

1959.02.11

The Federation of Arab Emirates of the South was formed. The constitution established a Council of six Ministers (known as Supreme Federal Council) with executive authority which chairman on a rotating basis, and a Federal Council of six representatives from each State as legislative authority. The name of the entity was changed to Federation of South Arabia on April 4, 1962.

1962.09.26

Aden’s Legislative Council voted to join the Federation. With this, a new Constitution was introduced on Oct 2, four more members of the LC will be elected, and a Chief Minister should be appointed by the Governor and the Executive Council renamed Council of Ministers, and the title of Governor changed to High Commissioner.

1963.01.18

Aden joined the Federation of South Arabia, and the Federal Constitution was amended to accommodate Aden. The legislature was called the Federal Council and the executive organ is the Federal Supreme Council.

1965.09.25

Britain suspended the Constitution of Aden after a series of terrorist attacks.

1967.11.30

People’s Republic of South Yemen proclaimed after agreement between Britain and the NLF. Qahtan al-Shaabi was proclaimed President of the Republic for 2 years, and the 13-men Hign Command of the NLF will serve as a legislature until a constitution is drawn up. On Dec 1 al-Shaabi formed the first cabinet with himself as head of the government.

1967.04.06

The NLF General Command ended a week’s meeting announcing Faysal Abd al-Latif al-Shaabi as Prime Minister.

1969.06.22

The NLA High Command announced the resignation of President al-Shaabi, and named a five-man Presidential Council. On Jun 23, Salem Rubayyi Ali was named Chairman of the Presidential Council and Muhammad Ali Haitham Prime Minister.

1969.12.30

The NLF General Command announced the dismissal of the NLF members including forer President al-Shaabi and former Prime Minister Faysal Abd al-Latif al-Shaabi. Also the Presidential Council was reduced to three members (President, Prime Minister, Secretary General of NLF).

1970.11.30

The government announced a new Costitution which would transfer the legislative ower from the NLF General Command to a Supreme People’s Assembly. The name of the State was changed to People’s Democratic Republic of Yemen.

1971.08.02

The People’s Supreme Assembly met and elected a new Presidential Council with Salem Rubayyi Ali as Chairman, Ali Nasir Muhammad was named Prime Minister.

1978.06.26

Salem Rubayyi Ali was killed in a military coup. Ali Nasir Muhammad was new Chairman of the Presidential Council. The new Presidential Council was elected on July 1.

1978.10.31

The Supreme People’s Assembly extraordinary session passed an amended Constitution. The Presidential Council was abolished, and it was replaced by the Presidium of the Supreme People’s Council.

1978.12.18

Parliamentary election.

1978.12.27

First session of the first elected Supreme People’s Council, Secretary General of the newly formed Yemen Socialist Party Abdul Fattah Ismail was elected Chairman of the Presidium of the Supreme People’s Council (Head of States), Ali Nasir Muhammad remained Prime Minister.

1980.04.21

Abdul Fattah Ismail resigned as Secretary General of the Yemen Socialist Party and Chairman of the Presidium of the Supreme People’s Council. He was replaced by Prime Minister Ali Nasir Muhammad.

1985.02.14

Ali Nasir Muhammad resigned as Prime Minister, and he was replaced by Haidar Abu Bakt al-Attas.

1986.01.13

Abdul Fattah Ismail was killed in a cival war with Ali Nasir Muhammad.

1986.01.25

It was announced Prime Minister Haidar Abu Bakt al-Attas now interim Head of State. Ali Nasir Muhammad was put into exile.

1986.02.06

The Central Committee of Yemen Socialist Party elected Ali Salem al-Beedh as new Secretary General. On Feb 8 Attas was approved as Chairman of the Presidium of the Supreme People’s Council, and Yasin Said Numan as new Prime Minister.

1986.10.30

Parliamentary Election held Oct 28-30. It opened on November 6, and Haidar Abu Bakt al-Attas reelected Chairman of the Presidium, Yasin Said Numan reelected Prime Minister.

1970.08 – 1990.05

Supreme People's Council

*最高人民委员会

也门 Yemen

1990年5月南北门合并为也门共和国，成立统一的代表会议。1993年4月举行首次议会选举。萨利赫总统于1997年5月颁布总统令，宣布成立也门协商会议。

PRELUDE TO UNIFICATION

Proposals for a merger between the two states were first made in October 1972 and were revived in October 1979. An agreement on further cooperation and co-ordination, signed in Aden on Dec. 2, 1981, provided inter alia for the creation of a Yemen Council comprising the two countries’ Presidents, a joint ministerial committee and a six-member secretariat.

The Yemen Council held its first meeting in Sana’a (Yemen Arab Republic) on Aug. 15–20, 1983, and set up a Yemen unity special committee, which set about increasing trade and abolishing customs duties between the two countries. The unification of the Yemen Arab Republic (North Yemen, with its capital at San’aa) and the People’s Democratic Republic of Yemen (South

Yemen, with its capital at Aden) was proclaimed at midday on May 22, 1990, after ratification the previous day by both parliaments.

1989.11.30

Yemen Arab Republic (YAR) President Abdallah Saleh and Secretary General Ali Salim al-Baidh of the Yemeni Socialist Party of the People’s Democratic Republic of Yemen (PDRY) signed a draft constitution of their proposed unification.

  • The House of Representatives (Majlis al-Nuwab) contains all members of the Shura Council (YAR) and the the Supreme People’s Council (PDRY), plus 31 members appointed by Presidential Council.
  • The five-member Presidential Council shall be elected by a joint session of the offices of the Presidency of the Supreme People’s Council and the Shura Council.
  • The Presidential Council shall elect a President and a Vice-President.
  • The Presidential Council shall appoint the Advisory Council and form tha government.

1990.05.21

The dradt constitution was adopted by the two Yemeni legislatures separately.

1990.05.22

Yemen Unified. Saleh is President, Baidh is Vice President, and the Presidential Council also included Salem Saleh Mohammed, a southerner who is Mr. Baidh’s former deputy, and two northerners – Abdel-Karim al-Arshi, former speaker of Yemen’s Parliament, and Abdel-Aziz Abdulghani, Sana’s former Prime Minister. Former PFRY President Haidar Abu Bakr al-Attas was named Prime Minister and his cabinet named on May 24. Former PDRY Prime Minister Yasin Said Numan was elected Speaker of the House of Representatives on May 26.

1991.05.16

Constitutional referendum held on May 15-16.

1993.04.27

Parliamentary election.

1993.05.15

Sheikh Abdullah al-Ahmar was elected Speaker of the newly elected House of Representatives and, on 30 May, a coalition Government was formed with Haider Abu Bakr al-Attas reelected Prime Minister.

1993.10.12

The House of Representatives elected a Presidential Council: Ali Abdallah Salih, secretary general of the General People's Congress (GPC) and president of the republic; Abd al-Aziz Abd al-Ghani, assistant secretary general of the GPC; Ali Salim al-Bidh, secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist Party (YSP) and vice president of the republic; Salim Salih Muhammad, YSP assistant secretary general; Abd al-Majid al-Zandani, member of the Islamic Reform Grouping.

1994.09.29

Constitutional amendment: The Presidential Council was abolished, and the President was to be elected by the House of Representatives.

1997.04.27

Parliamentary Election. The newly elected House held its first session on May 18.

1997.05.19

The President appointed a Consultative Council (Majlis al-Shura) with Abd al-Aziz Abd al-Ghani as Chairman.

1999.09.23

First Direct Presidentail election.

2001.02.20

Constitutional amendment: Shura Council defined in and expanded. A new Shura Council was appointed by the President on April 28.

2014.09.21

Houthi forces stormed into capital Sana'a.

2015.02.06

The Houthis declared parliament to be dissolved and installed a Revolutionary Committee as the interim authority, although they agreed to keep the House of Representatives in place on Feb 20 as part of a power-sharing agreement, to establish a People’s Transitional Council. This never happened as President Hadi managed to flee to Aden where he declared he was still president under the Yemeni constitution and condemned what he called Hothi “the coup”.

2019.04.13

The first session of House of Representatives was held in Seiyun, in Hadi controlled territories.

伊拉克 Iraq

伊拉克1920年11月沦为不列颠委任统治地，1921年8月建立费萨尔王朝，1932年10月获得完全独立。1924年7月，伊拉克王国制宪会议制定了第一部宪法，1925年7月经国王颁布实施。，实行宪政，议会由参众两院组成。1958年7月，费萨尔王朝被推翻，伊拉克共和国成立，原议会被终止。但此后先后由军人和阿拉伯复兴社会党实行独裁统治，长期不设议会。1968年7月，复兴党发动政变成立革命指挥委员会，1968年9月公布临时宪法，革命指挥委员会是国家最高权力机关，下辖政府和国民议会。1980年3月颁布《国民议会法》，始重新设立国民议会。2003年4月萨达姆被推翻，美英对伊拉克实行军事统治，国民议会被解散。2003年7月，美国占领当局任命组成伊拉克临时管理委员会。2004年3月临时管理委员会签署临时宪法，据此2005年1月组织了过渡国民议会选举，组织了过渡政府，并于2005年10月经全民公决通过了新宪法。根据新宪法，未来伊拉克议会将由国民议会和地方事务委员会共同组成。2005年12月，伊拉克举行国民议会选举，2006年3月正式召开。地方事务委员会具体组织形式尚未确定。

伊朗 Iran

18世纪末恺加王朝开始统治波斯，在俄国1905年革命的影响下，1905年12月伊朗爆发革命，要求改革内政、召开议会制订宪法。在压力下，1906年8月国王穆扎法-厄丁宣布同意实行宪政，10月国民议会召开，制订了伊朗历史上第一部宪法，限制王权，规定议会为最高权力机关，由参议院和国民议会组成。新王穆罕默德-阿里即位后，1908年6月议会被解散，但随即引发护宪起义。1909年7月革命军攻占德黑兰，16日召开非常议会，宣布恢复宪法，废黜国王，另立新国王阿赫德。1911年12月国王派在英俄支持下反动力量攻占议会大厦，解散议会。1914年12月才得以恢复。1925年10月巴列维王朝建立。1979年1月伊斯兰革命废除君主制，建立共和政府。12月颁布第一部宪法，规定伊实行政教合一制度，神权统治高于一切；伊斯兰议会是最高国家立法机构，实行一院制，1980年5月举行首次选举；宪法监护委员会审议和确认议会通过的议案，裁定是否与伊斯兰教义和宪法相抵触，1980年7月成立；1988年3月成立确定国家利益委员会，当议会和宪法监护委员会就议案发生分歧时进行仲裁。此外，伊朗专家会议是选举伊朗领袖的最高权力机构，成立于1982年12月。

网址：http://majlis.ir/

以色列 Israel

巴勒斯坦地区(包括今约旦、以色列和巴勒斯坦)原为不列颠委任统治地，1947年11月29日，联合国大会通过决议，决定在巴勒斯坦分别建立阿拉伯国和犹太国。1948年5月14日，以色列国正式宣告成立，临时国务委员会代行立法权，直至制宪议会选举产生。1949年1月选举产生制宪议会，同年2月通过过渡法，制宪议会改称议会。迄今以色列没有正式的成文宪法，仅有一些基本法。

网址：http://www.knesset.gov.il/

约旦 Jordan

外约旦原为巴勒斯坦一部分，1921年4月成立王国，为不列颠之委任统治地。1928年4月颁布组织法，1929年4月举行首次选举成立立法会议。1946年5月获独立。1949年4月改国名为约旦。1952年1月1日宪法颁布生效，规定议会由参众两院组成。1974年10月拉巴特峰会上巴勒斯坦解放组织获得承认，并被宣布为西岸维系合法代表，11月约旦暂时解散了众议院，以防止东岸单独选举会造成约旦河西岸事实上的分离，1976年2月正式解散议会。1978年4月国王侯赛因任命全国协商委员会，代行众议院部分职权。1984年1月侯赛因宣布重新召开众议院会议，修改宪法，规定约旦河东岸议员缺额补选产生，而西岸议员可由国民议会任命。1988年7月，侯赛因国王宣布中断同约旦河西岸地区的“法律和行政联系”。1989年11月举行1967年以来首次大选。

网址：http://www.parliament.gov.jo/
