非洲地区

埃塞俄比亚 Ethiopia

1931.07.16

The first written Constitution promulgated, composed by Tekle Hawariat Tekle Mariyam. It provisioned for the establishment of a parliament of two houses, the Senate (Yaheg Mawossena Meker-beth) and the Chamber of Deputies (Yaheg Mamria Meker-beth). The Senate was appointed by the Emperor and the Chamber nominated by nobility and local chiefs (until the people are capable of electing them themselves). Known Senate Presidents (1946, Mangasha Wube; Lorenzo Taezaz, 1943.07-1944.09)

1931.11.03

The parliament met for the first time. It was suspended at the beginning of the Italian invasion.

1941.03.09

A Proclaimation established the method of indirect election for the Chamber of Deputies.

1942.11.03

The parliament reopened after restoration.

1955.11.04

A revised Constitution was issued, with legislative composed the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies. The Senate remained appointed and and the Chamber now being elected.

1957.10.10

Ethiopia’s first general election held from Sept 12 to Oct 10.

1957.11.01

The Chamber of Deputies met for the forst time. And on the same day Emperor Haile Selassie appointed 35 members to the Senate. Former Prime Minister Makonnen Endakatchew served as President of the Senate (1957-61), and then followed by Asrate Kassa (1961-64), Abiye Abebe (1964-1974).

1961.06.17-07.12

General Election

1965.06.23-07.12

General Election

1969

General Election

1973.06.23-07.07

General Election

1974.09.12

The Emperor was deposed, Parliament dissolved, and the Constitution suspended.

1986.02.15

A degree promulgated by the Derg announced the establishment of a Constitutional Commission to draft a new Constitution, chaired by Mengistu.

1987.02.01

Referendum on new Constitution

1987.02.22

The new Constitution took effect. The People's Democratic Republic of Ethiopia was declared and the supreme organ of state power was the National Shengo (National Assembly).

1987.06.13

Election to the National Shengo

1987.09.09

The National Shengo convened its first session. The election of President, Vice President, Council of State, Council of Ministers, Supreme Court, Precurator General took on Sept 10, and The People's Democratic Republic of Ethiopia took into effect.

The Council of State is the standing body of the Shengo and the President of the Republic is President of the Council of State.

1990.07.26

Mengistu announced that Ethiopia has abandoned communism.

1991.04.19

Mengistu offered to resign. On April 26, Tesfaye Gebre Kidan was appointed Vice President replacing Fisseha Desta, and Tesfaye Dinka appointed Prime Minister.

1991.05.21

Mengistu fled Ethiopia, and Kidan became acting president.

1991.05.28

Forces of the EPRDF entered Addis Ababa and Meles Zenawi was proclaimed interim President.

1991.06.0

Tamrat Layne was appointed acting Prime Minister of an interim government.

1991.07.01

The EPRDF called a national Democracy Conference that culminated in the adoption of a Transitional Period Charter to function as an interim Constitution. The charter took effect upon publication on Negarit Gazetta on July 22. There shall be established a Transitional Government consisting a Council of Representatives and a Council of Ministers, to exercise legislative and executive responsibilities respectively. The Chairperson of the Council of Representatives shall also be the Head of State, and he shall appoint the Prime Minister, whose appointment shall be approved by the Council of Representatives, as well as the Prime Minister’s nomination of the members of the Council of Ministers.

1991.07.22

The Council of Representatives unanimously elected Meles Zenawi Chairman of the Transitional Council and Head of State.

1991.07.29

Tamrat Layne was elected Prime Minister by the Council of Representatives. His cabinet was formed on August 10.

1992.08.18

A constitutional Drafting Commission was established by a Council of Representatives proclamation, with Ato Kifle Wodajo as its Chairman.

1994.04.08

A draft handiwork was delivered to the Council of Representatives and got approved with minor modification.

1994.06.05

Election to the Constituent Assembly.

1994.10.28

The Constituent Assembly convened to begin work, and it elected Negasso Gidada as its Chairman.

1994.12.08

The Constituent Assembly ratified the new Constitution to create Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia. The Federal Houses contained the House of Peoples' Representatives and the House of the Federation

1995.05.07

General elections held on 7 and 18 May 1995 for seats in its House of People's Representatives.

1995.08.21

The House of the Federation convened its first regular session and Almaz Meko was elected its speaker. On same day the House of the People's Representatives also convened and Dawit Yohannes was elcted its Speaker.

1995.08.22

Negasso Gidada was elected President, and current President Meles Zenawi was elected Prime Minister on August 23. Zenawi announced the make-up of the new Council of Ministers on August 24. According to the new Cosntitutuion, the Prime Minsiter held real executive power and President now played a fingurehead role.

2000.10.09

The newly elected House of People's Representatives was inaugurated and it reelected Ato Dawit Yohannes as the Speaker.

2001.08.17

It is announced that Almaz Meko has resigned from her position as speaker of the House of Federation and defected to the Oromo Liberation Front.

2002.10.10

Mulatu Teshome was elected speaker of the House of Federation.

2005.10.10

The newly elected House of People's Representatives convened first session and elected Teshome Toga as the new Speaker. On same day, the newly indirectly elected House of Federation elected Degife Bula as new Speaker.

2010.10.04

The newly elected House of People's Representatives convened first session and elected Abadula Gemeda Dego as the new Speaker. On same day, the House of Federation elected Kassa Tekeleberihan Gebrehiwot as new Speaker.

2015.10.05

The newly elected House of People's Representatives convened first session and reelected Abadula Gemeda Dego as the new Speaker. On same day, the House of Federation elected Yalew Abate as new Speaker.

2017.10.08

Speaker of House of People's Representatives Abadula Gemeda Dego resigned, but he rescinded the resignation on Dec. 29.

2018.04.19

Muferiat Kamil was elected and sworn in as Speaker of House of People's Representatives.

2018.04.30

Keria Ibrahim was elected new Speaker of House of Federation.

2018.10.16

Speaker of House of People's Representatives Muferiat Kamil resigned to take role as Misnter of Peace. Tagesse Chafo was elected Speaker on October 18.

2020.06.08

Speaker of House of Federation Keria Ibrahim resigned to protest the postponement of planned elections over the coronavirus. Aden Farah was elected Speaker on June 10.

1931年7月埃塞俄比亚颁布宪法，实行宪政，参照日本模式成立议会，由贵族院和众议院组成，二者均为咨询机构。1936年5月意大利侵占埃塞俄比亚，1941年11月埃塞俄比亚重获独立。1955年11月修改宪法，扩大民主权，内阁对议会负责，但总体上仍是国王拥有最高权力。1974年9月塞拉西被废，1975年3月废除君主制，建立共和政府，临时军事行政委员会拥有最高权力，长期不设议会。1987年8月根据新宪法设置国民议会，同时结束军事统治，成立埃塞俄比亚人民民主共和国。1991年5月门格斯图政权被推翻，7月成立过渡政府。1994年6月选举产生制宪议会，12月通过新宪法，议会实行人民代表院和联邦院两院制。1995年5月举行首次多党选举。

安哥拉 Angola

1973.03.27

Legislative Assembly election took place between 19 and 27 March, per May 2, 1972 Portuguese National Assembly Organic Law for the Overseas Territories, which provided for greater autonomy for overseas territories. A Legislative Assembly was set up with the Governor-General as the President.

1975.11.11

Angola gained independence. MPLA (Movimento Popular de Libertação de Angola) Government promulgated the first Constitution on Nov 10. It subordinated the government to the ruling party, and the Council of the Revolution performed both executive and legislative functions, with President Agostinho Neto as its president. This Constitution was enacted by a resolution of the Central Committee of MPLA.

1975.11.14

The new government of the People’s Republic of Angola led by Lopo do Nascimento sworn in.

1977.08.07

The MPLA Central Committee passed a Constitution Amendment to tramsfer the power to appoint the Prime Misniter and any ministers from the legislatve Council of the Revolution to the President.

1978.12.09

It was officially announced that Lopo do Nascimento has been dismissed from the post of Prime Minister following a MPLA Central Committee meeting held on Dec 6-9, 1978.

1978.12.10

President Agostinho Neto announced that the posts of Prime Minister and Deputy Prime Minister abolished in a speech to mark the MPLA 22nd anniversary.

1979.09.11

President Agostinho Neto died in Moscow.

1979.09.20

José Eduardo dos Santos was elected by MPLA as new President and he sworn in on Sept 21.

1980.09.23

The MPLA Central Committee passed a Constitution Amendment to replace the Council of the Revolution by a People’s Assembly indirectly elected by provincial People’s Assemblies.

1980.11.11

The People’s Assembly was installed officially. President José Eduardo dos Santos was also the President of the People’s Assembly. The election started from August 23.

1987.01.30

The new People’s Assembly took office. This round of election started from Dec 9, 1986.

1991.03.06

Law No. 12/91 passed allowing the creation of new political parties.

1991.07.19

President José Eduardo dos Santos appointed Fernando José de França Dias Van-Dúnem as Prime Minister, filling the position for the first time in 13 years.

1992.08.26

A Constitution amendment provided for a presidentially appointed prime minister to head a transitional government, and the People’s Assembly renamed as National Assembly.

1992.09.29

General elections were held on 29 and 30 September 1992 to elect a President and National Assembly, the first time free and multi-party elections. José Eduardo dos Santos was elected President.

1992.11.26

The new National Assembly convened for first time. Outgoing Prime Minister Fernando José de França Dias Van-Dúnem was elected Speaker.

1992.12.02

President dos Santos announced a new Government headed by new Prime Minister Marcolino Moco.

1996.06.03

President José Eduardo dos Santos fires Prime Minister Marcolino Moco and replaces him with Fernando José de França Dias Van-Dúnem, who current was Speaker of the National Assembly.

1996.06.13

A new Speaker of the National Assembly, Roberto António Victor Francisco de Almeida, was elected.

2008.09.05

Legislative elections were held in Angola on 5 and 6 September 2008.

2008.09.30

The National Assembly held first session and outgoing prime minister Fernando da Piedade Dias dos Santos was elected new Speaker.

2010.01.21

The National Assembly passed a new Cosntitution and it was promulgated on Feb 5. The constitution abolished the direct election of President, and again the post of Prime Minsiter abolished. Speaker of the Natiomal Assembly Fernando da Piedade Dias dos Santos was the new post of Vice President.

2010.02.09

Former Prime Minister Paulo Kassoma was elected Speaker of the National Assembly.

2012.08.31

Legislative elections were held in Angola.

2012.09.27

The National Assembly held first session and Fernando da Piedade Dias dos Santos was elected Speaker.

2017.08.23

Legislative elections were held in Angola.

2017.09.28

The National Assembly held first session and Fernando da Piedade Dias dos Santos was reelected Speaker.

安哥拉原为葡萄牙属地，在争取民族独立的斗争中，安哥拉人民解放运动（安人运）、安哥拉民族解放阵线（安解阵）和争取安哥拉彻底独立全国联盟（安盟 ）先后成立。1975年1月葡萄牙与三个组织达成关于安独立的协议，共同组织过渡政府。不久，安人运与安解阵、安盟发生武装冲突。1975年11月11日独立，安人运成立安哥拉人民共和国；安解阵和安盟则成立了安哥拉人民民主共和国。 同日，安两派三方武装冲突扩大为全面内战。1976年安人运击败安解阵，安人民民主共和国解体。1980年11月成立人民议会。1991年5月安政府与以萨文比为首的反对派安盟签署《比塞斯和平协议》。1992年8月议会第2次特别代表大会决定将国名安哥拉人民共和国改为安哥拉共和国，人民议会改称国民议会。9月，安举行首次多党制大选。安盟拒绝接受大选结果，安重陷内战。2002年2月萨文比被政府军击毙，4月，安政府与安盟签署停火协议，结束长达27年的内战。

网址：http://www.parlamento.ao/

贝宁 Benin

1959.02.28

Constitution: A parliamentary system with a Prime Minister holding executive powers and a Legislative Assembly with legislative powers.

1959.04.02

Legislative Assembly election

1959.04.23

The Lsgislative Assembly elected Justin Ahomadégbé as its President, and the assembly took office on April 24.

1960.11.26

Constitution for Independence: A Presidential system with a President assisted by a Vice-President, neither of whom responsible to a National Assembly.

1960.12.11

Hubert Maga was elected President, and Sourou Migan Apithy Vice President. They took office Dec 31.

1960.12.15

The first legislature opened first session, and Valentin Djibodé Akplogan elected Speaker on Dec 17.

1963.10.27

A three-man Provisional Government formed after military Chief of Staff Christophe Soglo announced the existing National Assembly had been dissolved. The three men were President Hubert Maga, Vice President Sourou Migan Apithy, and former President og the Dahomey Democratic Union Justin Ahomadegbé.

1963.10.28

Coup led by Chief of Staff of the Armed Forces Christophe Soglo seized control of the country one day after the three-men Provisonal Governement met more protests. He announced his own Provisional Government on Oct 29 with same three-men.

1964.01.05

Constitutional referendum. The new Constitution: Two headed executive with a President as Head of State and a Vice-President who countersigned all presidential acts as Head of Government. Also a National Assembly with restricted powers. It was promulgated on Jan 11.

1964.01.19

Parliamentary elections, Sourou Migan Apithy elected President, Justin Ahomadegbé Vice President and Prime Minister. They took office on Jan 25.

1964.01.24

The new Parliament convened and Tahirou Congakou was new Speaker.

1965.11.27

The National Assembly deposed PRsident Sourou Migan Apithy and replaced him with Vice President and Prime Minister Justin Ahomadegbé, followed by a struggle of these two.

1965.11.29

Chief of Staff of the Armed Forces Christophe Soglo led a coup to dismiss both President Apithy and Vice President Ahomadégbé, and form a new government headed by President of the Nationasl Assembly Tahirou Congacou.

1965.12.22

Soglo withdrew Congacou’s mandate to form a coalition government and assumed full power of himself. On Dec 24 Soglo set up an advisory civilian Committee for National Renewal (Comité de Rénovation Nationale, CRN), and it was dissolved on April 6, 1967 and a all-miliary Committee of Military Vigilance (comité militaire de vigilance) was established with Major Benoit Sinzogan as Preident and Maurice Kouandété as Vice President.

1967.12.17

Coup led by Maurice Kouandété. Kouandété formed a Provisional government on Dec 18 with himself as Head of Government. Soglo was officially dismissed his function as President of the Republic on Dec 19, and Jean-Baptiste Hachème was the President the Military Revolutionary Committee (Comité militaire révolutionnaire). On Dec 20 it is announced Maurice Kouandété as Head of State, however due to France’s refuse to recognition, the Revolutionary Military Committee decided on Dec 21 to appoint Alphonese Alley as Head of State, while Kouandété became Prime Minister.

1968.03.31

A national referendum on the constitution was held.

1968.05.05

Presidential election was won by Basile Adjou. But the result was voided by the Military Regime due to insufficient voter turnout on May 12.

1968.06.28

Émile Zinsou was appointed by the Revolutionary Military Committee as next president, and he sworn in on July 17.

1968.07.28

A referendum on Émile Zinsou’s presidency was held.

1968.08.

Constitution: Military imposed presidential system with wide powers and an Economic and Social Council (Conseil Economique et Social) with recommendatory powers.

1968.08.29

The Economic and Social Council (Conseil Economique et Social) was established. It met for first time on Oct 12, with Tahirou Congacou as President.

1969.12.10

Chief of Staff Maurice Kouandété conducted another coup, toppled President Zinsou. A Military Directorate was set up on Dec 13, composed of Kouandété, Head of Gendarmerie Benoit Sinzogan and Head of Department of National Defense Paul-Émile de Souza, under the chairmanshop of the most senior of the three, de Souza.

1970.03.09

Presidential and legislative election began and it was suspended on March 28. And finally the Military Directorate annulled the election on April 3.

1970.04.30

It is announced a Presidential Council (Conseil Présidentiel) to be created composing Hubert Maga, Justin Ahomadégbé and Sourou Migan Apithy. Hubert Maga take first totate on May 7.

1970.05.

Constitution: Rotating two-year chairmanship of Presidential Council (Conseil Présidentiel), and a Consultative Assembly (Assemblée Consultative Nationale) divided into social, economic and general policy sections.

1972.01.19

Paul Darboux was appointed President of the National Consultative Assembly, but the Assembly only erected in July, and terminated same October after the coup.

1972.10.26

Mathieu Kérékou coup toppled Presidential Council, and he was named President and Defence Minister on Oct 27. A National Revolutionary Council (Conseil national de la revolution, CNR) created with Mathieu Kérékou as its Chairman.

1974.11.30

President Mathieu Kérékou announced Dahomey pursued a Marxist-Leninist policy.

1977.08.29

Constitution: The Loi Fondamentale set up a National Revolutionary Assembly (Assemblée Nationale Révolutionnaire, ANR), which in turn elected the President of the Republic.

1979.11.20

National Revolutionary Assembly election. It convened and replaced the CNR on Feb 4, 1980, with Ignace Adjo Boco elected as Speaker (titled President of the Standing Committee). Mathieu Kérékou was elected President by the Assembly on Feb 6.

1982.10.17

Speaker of the National Revolutionary Assembly Ignace Adjo Boco died.

1984.06.10

National Revolutionary Assembly election. It convened on July 27, Romain Vilon Guezo reelected Speaker, and Mathieu Kérékou reelected as President on July 31.

1989.06.18

National Revolutionary Assembly election. It convened on July 31 and Romain Vilon Guezo reelected Speaker on August 1. It also reelected Mathieu Kérékou as President on August 2.

1989.12.08

President Mathieu Kérékou announced Benin abandoned Marxism-Leninism, its ideology for the last 15 years.

1990.02.19

A National Conference (Conférence nationale des Forces Vivies) held between Feb 19 to 28. With original purpose to discuss economic issues, but turned into countries’s democratization. Robert Dossou was Chairman of the Organizing Committee.

1990.02.21

The Conference declared its sovereignty with the power to set up a commission to draft a new constitution, dismiss the existing national assembly and appoint an interim Prime Minister. President Kérékou was forced to accept it

1990.02.27

The National Conference appointed Nicéphore Soglo as Prime Minister.

1990.03.01

A Republic High Council (Haut Conseil de la République) was setup by the National Conference. Also, a Constitutional Commission (Commission Constitutionnelle) was set up with Maurice Glèlè-Ahanhanzo as Chairman.

1990.03.09

Republic High Council (Haut Conseil de la République) officially opened, with Isidore de Souza as its Chairman.

1990.03.12

Nicéphore Soglo took office as Prime Minister, and his cabinet took office on March 27.

1990.12.02

Constitution Referendum: A presidential system with a unicameral National Assembly (Assemblée nationale). It was promulgated by the President on Dec 11.

1991.02.17

National Assembly election.

1991.03.10

First round of presidential election.

1991.03.26

Second round of presidential election, won by Nicéphore Soglo. He took office on April 4.

1991.04.01

The National Assembly convened for first time and Adrien Houngbédji was elected President of the National Assembly.

1995.03.28

Parliamentary election.

"Les ministres du Dahomey et du Bénin"

Les Gouvernements du Dahomey et du Bénin : 1957-2005

达荷美原为法兰西属地，1946年法兰西在达荷美设立总议会(1952年改称议会)。1958年达荷美成为法兰西之自治共和国，1960年8月1日独立。1963年10月马加总统被推翻，议会被终止。1964年1月通过新宪法，选举产生新的民选政府，1965年12月再次被废止。1972年10月克雷库政变上台，实行一党制。1975年11月改国名为贝宁人民共和国。根据1977年5月宪法，1979年6月选举、1980年2月设立全国革命代表大会。1990年2月实行多党制，同时成立共和国最高委员会，取代原来的革命代表大会，3 月改国名为贝宁共和国。1991年2月选举产生新的国民议会。

布基纳法索 Burkina Faso

上沃尔特原为法国属地，1948年3月年法国在上沃尔特设立总议会(1952年2月改称议会)。1958年12月上沃尔特成为法兰西之自治共和国，1960年8月5日独立，设立国民议会。独立后政局动荡，曾发生多次政变，议会多次被解散。1966年1月亚梅奥果被推翻，军队接管政权，中指宪法，解散议会。1970年6月通过新宪法，1974年2月总统拉米扎纳解散议会，1977年12月通过新宪法，1978年4月选举产生新的国民议会。1980年11月泽博发动政变后，国家长期由军人统治，无议会。1984年8月改国名为布基纳法索。1991年6月通过新宪法，议会由国民议会和代表院（上院）组成，1992年5月举行首次选举,1995年12月代表院证实成型。2002年1月，布国民议会修改宪法，撤消代表院，将议会两院制改为一院制。

布隆迪 Burundi

乌隆迪原为比利时委任统治地，1946年12月联合国将布交由比利时托管，1947年比利时在乌隆迪设立总参议会(1957年改为全体会议，1959年又改为立法会议) 。1962年7月1日乌隆迪独立，实行宪政。宪法规定设立两院制，参议员和代表院。1966年11米孔贝罗发动政变废除君主制，改国名为布隆迪共和国，并解散国民议会。1966 - 1982年间长期由军人统治，无议会。1982年巴加扎重建国民议会，1987年9月布约亚政变上台就任总统，成立第三共和国。1993年6月举行立法选举，1996年7月由图西族控制的军队发动政变，废黜恩蒂班通加尼亚，推举前总统布约亚为总统。1998年6月通过了《布隆迪共和国过渡时期宪法》，9月恢复议会活动。2001年10月，布颁布实施《过渡时期宪法》，决定实行两院制，即由国民议会和参议院组成，过渡期国民议会和参议院分别于2002年1月和2月成立。2005年3月颁布实施《后过渡时期宪法》，2005年8月组成新的国民议会和参议院。

  • 8 juillet – 28 août 1991 : Conférence nationale souveraine du Togo

法属多哥原为法兰西属地，1946年10月法兰西在法属多哥设立领地议会。1956年8月法属多哥成为法兰西之自治共和国，称多哥共和国，领地议会改称领地立法议会，1958年4月改称代表院。1960年4月27日独立，1961年4月宪法规定国会为一院制，称国民议会。1967年1月埃亚德马发动政变，解散议会，废除宪法。1967 - 1980年间长期由军人统治，无议会。1979年12月全国公民投票通过宪法，1980年1月成立国民议会。1990年10月埃亚德马宣布接受多党制，1991年8月全国大会后成立共和国最高委员会，1992年9月公民投票通过第四共和国宪法。1994年2月举行立法选举，组成新的国民议会。2002年12月修改宪法规定，议会实行两院制，由国民议会和参议院组成。迄今参议院尚未选出。

厄立特里亚 Eritrea

1950.12.02

UN General Assembly approved a resolution calling for the federation of Ethiopia and the British-administered UN Trust Territory of Eritrea.

1950.12.14

Edwardo Anzi Matienzo of Bolivia was appointed UN Commissioner in Eritrea.

1952.01.28

British Administration issued a decree to establish the Eritrean Representative Assembly (Proclamation No. 121)

1952.03.25

Eritrean Representative Assembly election held March 25-26, 1952.

1952.04.28

The Eritrean Assembly convened first meeting. On April 29 Tedla Bairu was elected its Chairman.

1952.07.09

The Assembly transformed itself into Eriteria’s legislature.

1952.07.10

UN drafted constitution adopted by the Eritrean Assembly. The Constitution was approved by the UN Commissioner on August 6 and ratified by the Ethiopian Emperor on August 11.

1952.08.28

The Eritrean Assembly elected Tedla Bairu Chief Executive of the Eritrean Government.

1952.09.08

Tedla Bairu resigned as Chairman of the Assembly and Sheikh Ali Mohamed Musa Radai was elected Chairman.

1952.09.11

The Ethiopian Emperor ratified the Federal Act and proclaimed the emergence of the Federation.

1952.09.15

The Ethio-Eriteriean Federation took effect, and the British Administration came to a formal end by handing over power to the Ethiopian authorities and the new Eritrean Government. The Eritrean Assembly took over the legislative function.

1955.07.06

The Eritrean Assembly passed a vote of no confidence on both Chief Executive Tedla Bairu and President of the Assembly Sheikh Ali Mohamed Musa Radai.

1956.07.28

Idris Mohamed Adem replaced Sheikh Ali Mohamed Musa Radai as President of the Assembly.

1956.08.03

Chief Executive Tedla Bairu’s resignation letter dated July 28 was read to the Assembly.

1955.08.08

Asfaha Woldemikael was elected by the Assembly to be the new Chief Executive and he took oath of office on August 9.

1956.06.13

Idris Mohamed Adem was ousted as President of the Assembly and replaced by Sheikh Hamid Ferej Hamid.

1956.09.05

Assembly election held Sept 5-6, 1956.

1956.09.12

The second Assembly convened and reelected Sheikh Hamid Ferej Hamid as its President.

1960.05.17

The Assembly voted unanimously the Flaf, Seal and Arms Act 1960, and it changed the name "Eritrean Government" to "Eritrean Administration", and the word Merah Menghisty (Chief Executive) in Tigrinya be amended to read Teklal Ammahadaray (Chief Administrator).

1960.07.14

Second Eritrean Assembly officially came to an end, with the major pillars of Eritrean autonomy severely diminished.

1960.09.05

Assembly election held Sept 5-7, 1960.

1960.09.12

On first meeting of the Assembly Sheikh Hamid Ferej Hamid was elected Chairman of the Assembly.

1962.11.15

Ethiopian annexation of Eriteria accepted by Eritrean Assembly without a vote, and thr Assembly ceased to exist.

厄立特里亚原为意大利殖民地，1941年，意军战败，厄成为英国托管地。1950年12月，联合国决议将厄作为一个自治体同埃塞俄比亚结成联邦。1962年，埃皇塞拉西强行取消联邦制，将厄合并为埃的一个州，成为埃塞俄比亚一部分，引发了厄人民长达近30年的武装独立斗争。1991年5月埃塞俄比亚门格斯图政权被推翻，厄立特里亚人民解放阵线（厄人阵）解放厄全境，成立临时政府，建立政权。1993年4月在联合国的监督下举行全民公决以99.8%的绝对多数决定与埃分离。埃过渡政府接受公决结果，承认厄独立。5月24日，厄正式宣告独立。1997年1月组成制宪议会，1997年5月通过新宪法并正式颁布实施，成立国民议会。迄今未组织过正式选举。

刚果共和国 Congo, Republic of

  • 25 février – 10 juin 1991 : Conférence nationale du Congo

Les délégués déclarent la souveraineté de la conférence et destituent le Président Denis Sassou-Nguesso. Ils choisissent André Milongo, ancien officiel administratif de la Banque africaine de développement, Premier ministre du gouvernement de transition, et préparent pour des élections multipartites.

法属刚果原为法兰西属地，1946年法兰西在法属刚果成立总议会(1952年改称议会)。1958年11月法属刚果成为法兰西之自治共和国，1960年8月15日独立，称[西]刚果共和国。独立后曾发生多次政治动乱，议会被多次解散。1963年8月八月革命尤卢总统被推翻，议会被解散。1963年12月通过第二部宪法，成立国民议会。1968年8月，马桑巴-代巴总统被推翻后，宪法被废除，议会解散。1969年12月改国名为刚果人民共和国，但是通过的新宪法没有对议会作任何规定，1973年6月设立全国人民议会，1977年3月恩古瓦比总统遇刺身亡，宪法被中止，国家政权由刚果劳动党军事委员会行使，直至1979年7月通过新宪法，全国人民议会得以恢复。1990年9月劳动党同意实行多党制，1991年2至6月，刚果举行全国协商大会，通过了新的临时宪法，恢复独立时的国名“刚果共和国”，同时规定由它成立的共和国最高委员会是为期12个月的过渡时期的最高决策机构，并拥有一切权力（欧内斯特·孔博主教为最高委员会主席），从而剥夺了萨苏的一切权力，使之成了“挂名总统”。议会由国民议会和参议院共同组成，据此1992年6-7月举行了新议会的选举。新总统利苏巴于同年11月解散了国民议会，并于1993年5-10月举行了新的选举。1997年6月刚果总统选举前夕爆发内战，萨苏推翻利苏巴重新夺回权位。1998年1月，召开“全国和解、团结、民主和重建论坛”，确定3年弹性过渡期后举行总统大选；会议选举产生过渡时期全国委员会作为临时议会。2002年1月全民公投通过新宪法，议会仍由国民议会和参议院组成；同年5-7月举行首次立法选举。

刚果民主共和国 Congo, Democratic Republic of

  • 7 août 1991 – 17 mars 1993 : Conférence nationale souveraine du Zaïre

La conférence est suspendue à la suite des plaintes de l’opposition, accusant le Président Mobutu de contrôler la procédure, mais elle reprend le 12 décembre 1991. L’archevêque Monsengwo Pasinya est élu président de la conférence. Puis, Mobutu suspend la conférence jusqu’à avril 1992, mais elle recommence sous la pression des pays donateurs et du Vatican. La conférence se déclare souveraine, conserve Mobutu à la tête de l’État pendant la période de transition, et élit Étienne Tshisekedi Premier ministre. Mobutu continue à enfreindre les décisions de la conférence, et le 17 mars 1993 il nomme Faustin Birindwa Premier ministre, créant deux gouvernements contestant.

比属刚果原为比利时属地，1960年仿照比利时建立了两院制议会。同年6月30日独立，称[东]刚果民主共和国，1964年8月改国名为刚果民主共和国。1965年11月蒙博托夺取政权后，1967年5月20日组建人民革命运动（Mouvement Populaire de la Révolution (MPR)），并于同年6月24日通过新宪法，宣布人革运为国内唯一的国家机构、唯一的执政党，所有公民均为其成员，立法委员会为其组成机构之一（初称国民议会，后1972年10月改称立法委员会）。1971年10月改国名为扎伊尔。1990年4月实行多党制，1992年5月，主权国民会议conférence Nationale Souveraine召开，12月2日，主权国民会议建立了一个由453名议员组成的共和国高级委员会，其权力是通过并执行新宪法。1993年1月，共和国高级委员会判处蒙博托腐败叛国的罪名。作为回击，蒙博托于1993年4月任命了他自己的新总理，并重新召集了以前的国民立法委员会，以削弱共和国高级委员会的力量。为了避免动乱，主权国民会议与蒙博托达成妥协，解散了国民立法委员会和共和国高级委员会，在原国民立法委员会、共和国高级委员会的基础上，于1994年1月26日建立了新的过渡性议会：共和国最高委员会-过渡议会，作为过渡时期的立法机构。1997年5月解盟夺取政权后恢复“刚果民主共和国”国名，卡比拉取消了蒙博托时期的“共和国最高委员会-过渡议会”，1997年10月，刚果（金）成立宪法委员会，其主要职能是讨论宪法草案和相关事宜，但因1998年8月邻国入侵，战争爆发，宪法委员会中止了工作。2000年8月，洛·卡比拉总统宣布成立制宪立法议会（过渡议会）。2003年8月22日，刚过渡议会宣告正式成立，实行两院制。2006年2月新宪法正式实施后，两院相继举行了选举，正式宣告成立。

网址：http://www.parlement-rdc.org/

吉布提 Djibouti

法属索马里兰原为法国属地，1946年法国在法属索马里兰设立总议会(1952年改称议会)。1977年成立国民议会。同年6月27日法属索马里兰独立，改国名为吉布提共和国，国民议会为一院制，是国家最高权力机构。

网址：http://www.assemblee-nationale.dj/

几内亚 Guinea

法属几内亚原为法兰西属地，1946年法兰西在法属几内亚设立总议会(1952年改称议会)。1958年10月2日法属几内亚独立，建立几内亚共和国，成立国民议会。1979年3月改称全国人民议会。1984年3月杜尔总统病逝，4月孔戴发动政变接管政权，成立国家复兴军事委员会，解散议会，终止宪法。1990年12月公民投票通过新宪法，1991年1月解散国家复兴军事委员会，成立新的最高权力机构“全国复兴过渡委员会”。1992年4月，几内亚宣布开放党禁，实行多党制。1995年6月首次有多党参加的立法选举，国民议会得以恢复。

几内亚比绍 Guinea-Bissau

葡属几内亚原为葡萄牙属地，1951年被定为葡海外省，1973年9月24日在解放区宣告成立几内亚比绍共和国，并颁布宪法，成立全国人民议会。1974年9月10日葡予以承认并正式撤军，几比获得正式独立。1980年11月部长会议主席维埃拉发动“调整运动”，推翻卡布拉尔政府，成立革命委员会，暂时中止宪法。1984年5月恢复。1991年5月，几比全国人民议会特别会议通过了建立多党制的法律。1994年7-8月举行首次多党选举。

加纳 Ghana

黄金海岸原为不列颠属地，1874年不列颠在黄金海岸设立立法会议(1954年改组为立法议会)。1957年3月6日黄金海岸独立，改国名为加纳。1960年7月1日成立共和国，议会改称国民议会。1966年2月政变恩克努玛被推翻后，议会被解散。1969年8月恢复选举，1972年1月再次被政变推翻。1979年6月，曾发动军事政变未遂的罗林斯再次发动军事政变，推翻阿库福政权，出任武装部队革命委员会主席。9月，将政权移交给民选的利曼政府；1981年12月，罗林斯第三次发动军事政变，推翻利曼政府。1992年4月通过新宪法恢复议会。

网址：http://www.parliament.gh/

加蓬 Gabon

  • 1er mars – 19 avril 1990 : Conférence nationale du Gabon

Le Président Bongo organise une conférence nationale, suivant le modèle du Bénin. Il introduit le multipartisme en avril, mais la conférence ne devient pas souveraine, et Bongo le contrôle. Les élections sont prévues pour octobre 1990.

加蓬原为法兰西属地，1946年法兰西在加蓬设立总议会(1952年改称议会)。1958年11月28日加蓬成为法兰西之自治共和国，1960年8月17俄i独立，设立国民议会。1968年邦戈创建加蓬民主党，实行一党制。1990年3月改行多党制，10月举行多党立法选举。1991年3月通过新宪法，1994年3月，国民议会通过宪法修正案规定议会由国民议会和参议院组成，二者共同行使立法权。参议院1997年1月选举后正式成立。

网址

国民议会：http://www.assemblee.ga/

参议院：http://www.senatgabon.net/

津巴布韦 Zimbabwe

南罗得西亚原为不列颠属地，1923年不列颠在南罗得西亚(1964年改称罗德西亚)设立立法会议。1965年11月11日罗德西亚殖民政府单方面宣布独立，实行白人种族主义统治。1970年3月罗得西亚宣布成立共和国，设立议会，由参众两院组成。1979年6月1日改国名为津巴布韦-罗德西亚，同年12月12日取消独立，复为不列颠属地。1980年4月18日正式独立，改国名为津巴布韦，议会仍由参众两院组成。1989年根据宪法修正案取消参议院，2005年11月再度设立。

网址：http://www.parlzim.gov.zw/

喀麦隆 Cameroon

喀麦隆原为德国殖民地，一战期间,喀东、西部分别被法、英军队占领；1922年国际联盟将东、西喀麦隆分交法、英“委任统治”。二战后,联合国将东、西喀分交法、英“托管”。东部法兰西属地，1946年12月设立总议会(1952年3月改称议会，1957年3月再改称立法议会)。 1959年东喀麦隆成为法兰西之自治共和国，称喀麦隆共和国。1960年1月1日独立，成立国民议会。1961年2月，喀英托管区北部和南部分别举行公民投票，6月1日北部并入尼日利亚，10月1日南部与喀麦隆共和国合并，组成喀麦隆联邦共和国，据此1962年议会改成联邦议会。1972年5月公民投票通过新宪法，取消联邦制，成立中央集权的喀麦隆联合共和国，议会改称国民议会，1973年5月举行首次选举。根据1996年1月宪法修正案，立法权由国民议会和参议院组成的两院制议会行使。目前,参议院尚未成立。

网址：http://www.cm.refer.org/assnat-cm/

科摩罗 Comoros

科摩罗群岛原为法兰西属地，1956年法兰西在科摩罗群岛设立议会。1975年7月6日科摩罗独立，阿卜杜拉出任总统。独立后政局动荡，8月3日即发生政变，议会被解散，亲法的阿里·萨利赫执掌政权。1978年5月萨利赫政权被推翻，阿卜杜拉又当选总统，同年改国名为科摩罗伊斯兰联邦共和国，成立联邦议会。1999年4月科军参谋长阿扎利上校发动军事政变，解散议会。2001年12月科摩罗通过独立以来第四部宪法，决定在维护国家统一和领土完整基础上成立由大科摩罗、昂儒昂、莫埃利和马约特四岛组成的科摩罗联盟。国民议会为联盟立法机构，2004年6月正式组建。

科特迪瓦 Côte d'Ivoire

科特迪瓦原为法兰西属地，1946年10月法兰西在科特迪瓦设立总议会(1952年2月6日改称领地议会)。1958年12月4日科特迪瓦成为法兰西之自治共和国，领地议会改称制宪会议，1959年3月通过新宪法。1960年8月7日获得正式独立，称象牙海岸。同年10月31日通过独立后的宪法，11月举行了首次议会选举。1985年10月改称科特迪瓦。1999年12月24日罗贝尔·盖伊宣布推翻贝迪埃总统，中止宪法，解散政府和议会。2000年1月宣布成立宪法和选举法协商委员会，7月23～24日举行全民公决，通过了新宪法。新议会于2001年1月选举产生。

网址：http://www.anci.ci/

肯尼亚 Kenya

肯尼亚原为不列颠属地，1907年8月不列颠在肯尼亚设立立法委员会。1963年改组为国民议会，由参众两院组成，同年12月12日肯尼亚独立，一年后成为共和国。1966年12月宪法修正案决定国民议会改为一院制。1982年6月，修宪确立实行一党制，1991年12月改行多党制，1992年举行首次多党议会选举。

网址：http://www.ski-pix.com/parliament/index.php

莱索托 Lesotho

巴苏陀原为不列颠保护领，1910年不列颠在巴苏陀设立巴苏陀会议(1960年改组为国民会议)。1966年10月4日莱索托独立，实行宪政，议会由参众两院组成。1970年1月举行独立后首次大选，巴苏陀兰大会党获胜。巴索托国民党政府宣布选举结果无效，并实行紧急状态，取缔反对党。1973年4月设立临时国民议会。1985年9月恢复议会，举行选举。1986年1月武装部队司令莱哈尼耶少将发动军事政变，接管政权并禁止政党活动。1993年3月，军政府还政于民，举行莱第二次大选。

网址：http://www.parliament.ls/

利比里亚 Liberia

利比里亚原为美国属地，1847年7月26日独立，成立国会，由参众两院组成。1980年4月12日多伊军士长发动政变，结束美国黑人移民后裔的统治，建立军政府，解散国会。1984年7月多伊设立临时国民议会，1985年10月举产生了第二共和国第一届国民大会。1989年12月查尔斯•泰勒率全国爱国阵线武装攻入利境，内战爆发，国民大会停止行使其职责。1991年4月，成立了代表国家大多数主要政治组织的临时议会。1994年3月，临时议会被一个由35名经任命产生的成员组成的过渡期立法会议代替，过渡期立法会议任期6个月，后来又被几次延长，直至1997年7月新一届国民大会选举。泰勒执政后，利国内局势一直动荡不安。2003年8月泰勒总统流亡尼日利亚，布拉政府与利民联、利民运和各政党社团共同签署《阿克拉和平协定》，并于10月中旬组建全国过渡政府，同时成立全国过渡立法会议。2005年10月，利举行新总统和议会选举，2006年1月正式就职。

卢旺达 Rwanda

卢安达原为比利时属地，1947年比利时在卢安达设立总参议会(1957年改为全体会议，1959年又改为立法会议) 。1961年1月28日废除君主制，改国名为卢旺达，为比利时之自治共和国。1962年7月1日正式独立。1973年7月5日，朱韦纳尔·哈比亚利马纳发动军事政变，解散国民议会，成立第二共和国并自任总统。1982年1月设立国民发展议会 。1991年6月卢实行多党制。1994年４月哈比亚利马纳因飞机失事遇难身亡后，内战再度爆发。7月卢旺达爱国阵线取得军事胜利，宣布实行5年过渡期，实行爱阵主导、多党参政和禁止党派活动的政治管理模式，设立过渡国民议会。2003年5月，卢全民公决通过新宪法，国会由众参两院组成，8月举行1994年以来首次多党总统大选，9月举行议会参众两院选举。

网址：http://www.rwandaparliament.gov.rw/

马达加斯加 Madagascar

马达加斯加岛原为法兰西属地，1946年法兰西在马达加斯加岛成立总议会(1952年改称议会)。1958年10月14日成为法兰西之自治共和国，称马尔加什共和国，同时成立制宪议会。1960年6月26日正式独立，议会由国民议会和参议院共同组成。1972年5月军方接管权力后，解散议会。1975年12月30日全民公决通过新宪法，改国名为马达加斯加，依此设立全国人民议会，同时取消参议院。1990年实行多党民主，1992年8月通过第三共和国宪法，实行两院制，由国民议会和参议院组成。

1978.12.04-08 Internal elections are held with the exclusion of SWAPO, the NNF and SWAPO-D. The DTA wins 82,1% of the seats, ACTUR 11,9%, the NCDP 2,8%, the HNP 1,8% and the Rehoboth Liberation Front (LF) 1,4%.

1978.12.20 The newly-elected Constituent Assembly meets and elects Johannes Skrywer as its first President

1979.05.21 The National Assembly is formally opened

1980.07.01 The National Assembly receives executive powers when the Minister’s Council is established to replace the (governing/advisory) Council of the Administrator-General, Dirk Mudge becomes Chairman of the Council of Ministers.

1983.01.18 Dirk Mudge decides to give up his position as Chairman of the Council of Ministers.

1983.01.19 The National Assembly is summarily and unceremoniously dissolved by South Africa.

1983.07. Administrator General Van Niekerk initiates the setting up of a State Council comprising 50 representatives to be drawn from the internal parties and private sector. The Council would act in an advisory capacity and formulate a new constitution which would be submitted to the electorate in a referendum. But, the State Council is effectively dead and buried two months later when the new Multi-Party Conference (MPC) takes its place in September.

1985.06.17 Transitional Government of National Unity is installed after SA agrees to the MPC proposals. The TGNU is granted legislative and executive powers under SA Proclamation R101 but always subject to South Africa’s authority.

1989.02.28 The TGNU dissolves itself, Administrator-General Louis Pienaar assumes control over governmental affairs in Namibia.

1989.11.07-11 Elections for the Constituent Assembly take place.

1989.11.21 Sam Nujoma opens the Constituent Assembly exactly one week after the elections being certified.

1989.12.21 Sam Nujoma announces his Shadow Cabinet for the first freely-elected Government of the Republic of Namibia.

1990.02.09 The Constituent Assembly unanimously adopts a new Constitution.

1990.03.21 Namibia gains independence, National Assembly of the Republic of Namibia is sworn in with Mosé Penaani Tjitendero as Speaker of the lower house of Parliament.

1992.08.31 The Regional Councils Act, the Regional Authorities Act and the Electoral Act are promulgated by the National Assembly and create the basis for the establishment for the second house of Parliament, the National Council.

1993.05.11 The second house of Parliament, the National Council commences his work. First Chairman of the House becomes Kandy Nehova.

塞内加尔 Senegal

Sénégal. Conseil general

En 1840 fut institué à Saint-Louis un conseil général. Ce conseil fut dissous en 1848. Le conseil général fut rétabli en 1879, puis dissous en 1920, il fut remplacé par le conseil colonial qui existera jusqu'en 1946. Le conseil général du Sénégal vit le jour en 1946 et fut remplacé en 1952 par l'Assemblée territoriale

俄罗斯 Russia

莫斯科早于1472年便设立杜马Duma，作为咨询机构。1547年改国名为俄罗斯。1905年俄罗斯爆发革命，政府被迫推行宪政改革。1906年成立国家杜马。1907年恢复君主专制。1917年布尔什维克党发动革命，建立苏维埃政府。1922年俄罗斯与乌克兰、白俄罗斯和外高加索合并为苏联。1991年苏联解体，俄罗斯成为独立国家。

1917.02.27(03.12) Duma delegates received an order from his Majesty that he had decided to prorogue the Duma until April, leaving it with no legal authority to act, The Duma refused to obey, and decided to form a Provisional Committee of the State Duma as governing body (Mikhail Rodzianko as chairman)

2016.04.13 Asylbek Jeenbekov stepped down as Speaker of the Jogorku Kenesh of the Kyrgyz Republic, citing his brother Sooronbay Jeenbekov is nominated prime minister and waiting for parliament voting. Vice Speaker of Parliament Nurbek Alimbekov will hold the parliamentary sessions from now on

2016.04.27 Chynybay Tursunbekov is elected new speaker of the parliament

乌克兰 Ukraine

1. 拉达Rada政府

1654年乌克兰成立哥萨克Cossack大会，作为咨询机构。其后乌克兰分裂为右岸(即西乌克兰)和左岸(即东乌克兰)两部分，分别并归波兰和俄罗斯。1917年乌克兰民族主义者在东乌克兰成立中央拉达，同年宣布独立。1921 年为苏维埃政府所灭。

Time

Local Name

English Name

Chinese Name

1917.03.04(17) Central Council of Ukraine is founded in Kiev

1917.03.07(20) Mykhailo Hrushevsky is absentia elected chairman of the Rada, while he’s not in Kiev, Fyodor Krizhanіvskiy acts as chairman

1917.03.14(27) Mykhailo Hrushevsky is back from Moscow and officially takes office as chairman of Rada

1917.06.10(23) Ukrainian Central Council declared its autonomy as part of the Russian Republic by its First Universal at the All-Ukrainian Military Congress

1917.06.15(28) The committee of the Central Council of Ukraine approves the establishment of the General Secretariat and gives it executive authorities

1917.11.07(20) the III Universal of the Ukrainian People's Republic which declared Ukraine an autonomous part of the Russian state

1918.01.09(22) the Central Rada issued its Fourth Universal breaking ties with Bolshevik Russia and proclaiming a sovereign Ukrainian state. the General Secretariat is renamed Council of People's Ministers of the Ukrainian People's Republic

1918.04.29 The Germans arrested and disbanded the Rada, and replaced by the conservative government of Hetman Pavlo Skoropadsky, the Hetmanate, and the Ukrainian People's Republic by a "Ukrainian State" (Ukrayinska derzhava)

1918.04.29 The All-Ukrainian Agrarian Congress elects Pavlo Skoropadsky the Hetman of Ukraine

1918.11.13 during a session of the Ukrainian National Union in rebellion against Skoropadsky's regime, Directorate of Ukraine is formed, with Volodymyr Vynnychenko as Directory's chairman

1918.12.14 the Directorate of Ukraine received the state powers in Ukraine after the Hetman of Ukraine emigrated to Germany, and restoring Ukrainian People's Republic

1918.12.19 Directorate takes control of Kiev

1919.02.11 Symon Petliura assumes the position of the Directory's chairman

1920.11.10 Directorate of Ukraine is dissolved

1992.11.10 Arman Kirakosyan is appointed foreign minister

1995.07.05 New Constitution of the Republic of Armenia was approved in the referendum, thus renamed Suoreme Council to National Assembly

1995.07.24 President Ter-Petrossian reappointed MrHrand Bagratian as Prime Minister 

1995.07.27 National Assembly of the Republic of Armenia opened the first convocation, Babken Ararktsyan is elected as chairman

1998.02.03 President Levon Ter-Petrosyan and parliament chairman Babken Ararktsyan resign. Prime minister Robert Kocharyan is acting president, and Khosrov Arutyunyan is elected parliament chairman

1999.06.11 President Robert Kocharyan appoints Vazgen Sarkisian as prime minister, Karen Demirchian is elected parliament chairman

1999.10.27 Prime Minister Vazgen Sarkisyan and parliament chairman Karen Demirchyan are killed in a shooting in parliament

1999.11.03 President Robert Kocharyan appoints Aram Sarkisyan, brother of the assassinated Vazgen Sarkisyan, as prime minister. Armen Khachatryan is elected as new parliemt chairman at an extraordinary session

2003.06.12 Artur Baghdasarian is elected as parliament chairman after the new parliament election

2006.05.23 Artur Baghdasaryan resigns as parliament chairman

2006.06.01 Tigran Torosyan is elected as parliament chairman

2007.06.07 Tigran Torosyan is re-elected as parliament chairman after the new parliament election

2008.09.26 parliament speaker Tigran Torosyan’s resignation is accepted, vice speaker Hrayr Karapetyan is acting chairman till Sept 29 when Hovik Abrahamyan is elected new chairman

2011.11.21 parliament speaker Hovik Abrahamyan’s resignation is accepted, vice speaker Samvel Nikoyan is acting chairman till Dec. 6 when he is elected new chairman

2012.05.31 Hovik Abrahamyan is elected as parliament chairman after the new parliament election

2004.04.13 Hovik Abrahamyan is appointed prime minister, thus speaker’s post is vacant

2014.04.29 Galust Sahakyan is elected parliament chairman, replacing Hovik Abrahamyan who is appointed prime minister

欧洲地区

阿尔巴尼亚 Albania

阿尔巴尼亚原为奥斯曼属地，1912年独立，成立国民议会。1928年独裁者索古Zogu解散国会。1939年意大利侵占阿尔巴尼亚。1944年恢复独立，并废除君主制，建立共和政体，重新设立议会。

1912.11.28 – 1912.12.04

All Albanian Congress in Vlorë

1912.11.28

Declaration of Independence

1912.12.04

Provisional Government of Albania, with an Elderly Assembly set up as advisory body

1913.02.27 – 1913.03.06

Albanian Congress of Trieste. Hil Mosi was elected Chairman of the Congress. The congress recognized the provisional government.

1913.07.29

London Conference agreed to establish the Principality of Albania.

1913.10.16

The International Contral Commission (Komisioni Ndërkombëtar i Kontrollit) eatablished (first meeting) based on July 29 decision.

1914.02.21

The Princeipality was officially established with Prince William of Wied accepted the throne.

1914.03.07

Prince William arrived in Durrës and took the throne.

1914.04.10

The Basic Law of the Principality came into force. There should be a National Assembly partially elected and partially appointed, but it never came into realized.

1914.06.03

An Islamist group of rebels in Central Albania founded the First General Council (Këshilli i Parë i Përgjithshëm) with goal to make Albania a protectorate of the Ottoman Empire. The Council President was Mustafa Ndroqi, Xhenabi Adili Vice President and Qamil Musa Haxhi Feza as Geneal Military Commander.

1914.09.03

Prince William fled the country.

1914.09.06

The International Contral Commission ceased to exist. On same day the Central Albania rebels entered Durrës and Qamil Musa Haxhi Feza became head of the Administrative Committee. On Sept 11 Mustafa Ndroqi formed a government.

1914.10.02

Esat Pashë Toptani, with support of Serbian military, entered Durrës, and he formed a provisional government on Oct 5, with Mustafa Ndroqi as Vice President.

1916.02.24

Austro-Hungarian troops arrived in Durrës and Esat Toptani government ceased to exist.

1918.12.28

Congress of Durrës (1918.12.25-27) held with Mehmet Konica was Chairman of the Congress. Turhan Pashë Përmeti was appointed Head of State and Prime Minister.

1920.01.31

Congress of Lushnjë (1920.01.28-31) held with Aqif Elbasani as President of the Congress. The Statute of Lushnjë outlined that the new government consisted of the High Council (Albanian: Këshilli i Lartë) and the National Council (Albanian: Këshilli Kombëtar). Also, Tirana was designated as Capital of Albania. The congress declared the Durrës government invalid and formed a new cabinet under Sulejman Delvina. The High Council was composed of Aqif Pashë Biçaku (Bektashi), Abdi Bey Toptani (Suni Muslim), Bishop Luigj Bumçi (Catholic) and Doctor Mihal Turtulli (Orthodox).

1920.02.11

The high organs left Lushnjë and settled in Tirana.

1920.02.20

The provisional government in Durrës handed over the offices to the Government in Tirana.

1920.03.27

The National Council, the first Albanian parliament, opened its first session.

1920.11.14

Sulejman Delvina resigned as Chairman of the Government. Iliaz Bej Vrioni was appointed new Prime Minister on Nov 19.

1921.10.11

Iliaz Vrioni government was down in the parliament. A new governmend headed by Pandeli Evangjeli was formed on Oct 16.

1921.12.06

The High Council decreed the dismissal of the Pandeli Evangjeli government to against Amet Zogu. Qazim Koculi was approved as new Prime Minister but he resigned after holding office only 20 hours under pressure. Hasan Pristina was appointed and formed a new anti-Zogu cabinet on Dec 7, but also also forced to resign on Dec 10. Idhomene Kosturi formed a technician cabinet on Dec 12.

1921.12.14

Amed Zogu entered Tirana. Previously, Aqif Pashë Biçaku and Luigj Bumçi resigned from the High Council on Dec 22, and the other two also left in next 2 days. On Dec 24 a new High Council was formed (Omer Vrioni, Ndoc Pistulli, Sotir Peci and Refik Toptani) and Xhafer Ypi was appointed Prime Minister.

1922.01.22

Omer Vrioni and Ndoc Pistulli resigned from the High Council.

1922.12.02

Amet Zogu took over as Prime Minister himself. Xhafer Ypi and Gjon Çoba were appointed to the High Council. The new cabinet was formed on Dec 24.

1922.12.08

A full Constitution was adopted by the National Council, as an extension of The Statute of Lushnjë 1920.

1924.02.23

Amet Zogu survived an assassination attempt and he resigned his position as Prime Minister on next day. He asked the High Council to appoint his father-in-law Shefqet Vërlaci to the position and he took office on March 3.

1924.05.27/30

Shefqet Vërlaci Cabinet resigned and a new cabinet with Iliaz Vrioni as Prime Minister formed on same day.

1924.06.10

Anti-Zogu revolutionary forces entered Tirana and Amet Zogu fled to Yugoslavia.

1924.06.16

The democratic government was formed with Fan Noli as Prime Minister.

1924.12.24

Amet Zogu returned Tirana. Fan Noli fled to Italy on Dec 26 and Iliaz Vrioni resoted as Prime Misister.

1925.01.06

Amet Zogu became new Prime Minister.

1925.01.21

The Constituent Assembly proclaimed the Albanian Republic and on Jan 31 Amet Zogu was installed as President.

1925.03.02

The new Cosntitution was approved. The President was also head of the Council of Ministers and Commander-in-Chief of the army, and the legislative power was exercised by the Parliament composed of a Senate and a Chamber of Deputies.

1928.08.17

Cosntitutent Assebly election.

1928.09.01

Albania proclaimed a heritable Democratic and Parliamentary Kingdom.

1928.09.05

The first cabinet of monarchical Albania was formed with Koço Kota as Prime Minister.

1928.12.01

Fundamental Statute of the Kingdom of Albania promulgated. The legislation was unichamber Parliament.

1939.04.07

Italy invaded Alabania. Amet Zogu fled the country on April 8.

1939.04.12

A so-called Constituent Assembly proclaimed the union of Albania with Italy under the crown of Italian king-emperor Victor Emmanuel III. Shefqet Vërlaci was appointed new Prime Minister.

1939.06.03

The Statute of the Albanian Kingdom proclaimed and all executive and legislative power wer reserved to the King of Italy. Albanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs was also dissolved.

1941.12.03

Shefqet Vërlaci Resigned as Prime Minister, and Mustafa Merlika-Kruja was named to replace him.

1943.01.19

Mustafa Merlika-Kruja resigned as Prime Minister and was replaced by Eqrem Libohova.

1943.02.13

Maliq Bushati became new Prime Minister, replacing Eqrem Libohova.

1943.05.13

Eqrem Libohova again became Prime Minister.

1943.09.08

Italy’s armistice with the Allied Forces was made public. The Albanian government of Eqrem Libohova collapsed and German troops moved in to occupy Albania.

1943.09.14

Ibrahim Biçakçiu was appointed Chairman of the Provisional Executive Committee, the puppet government under German occupation. He declared so called independence of Kingdom of Albania.

1943.10.01

Constituent Assembly election.

1943.10.16

The National Assembly began to function, and on Oct 20 it elected a four-member High Regency Council (Këshilli i Lartë i Regjencës), composed by Mehdi Frashëri (Bektashi), Lef Nosi (Orthodox), Fuat Dibra (Sunni Muslim) and Father Anton Harapi (Catholics) to govern the country, with Frashëri as Chairman.

1943.11.04

A Government was set up with Rexhep Mitrovica as Prime Minister. The foreign Ministry was reinstated.

1944.02.22

Member of the Regency Fuat Dibra died. His position was replaced by Cafo Ulqini.

1944.06.16

Prime Minister Rexhep Mitrovica resigned citing health reason.

1944.07.18

Fiqri Dine was new Prime Minister, but he resigned on August 29.

1944.09.06

Fiqri Dine was replaced as Prime Minister by Ibrahim Biçakçiu.

1944.10.25

The High Regency Council and the Council of Ministers were forced to announce their resignation and interruption of all state activities after German High Command retreated from Tirana to Shkodër.

1944.11.17

Tirana liberated by National Liberation Army. Shkodër liberated on Nov 29.

1941.11.08

The Communist Party of Albania founded.

1942.09.16

The Conference of Pezë crated a common National Liberation Front with Mehdi Frashëri named as honorary president of the conference, and a National Liberation General Council with Kamber Qafmolla as its Chairman.

1943.07.10

The General Staff of the National Liberation Army was formed under the command of Spiro Moissiu and political commissar Enver Hoxha.

1943.09.04

The second National Libration Conference convened in Labinot (Sept 4-9).

1944.05.24

The Anti-Fascist National Libration Congress held in Përmet (May 24-28). It chose the Anti-Fascist National Libration Council as highest legislative and executive organ, with Omer Nishani as President. And the Council them appointed the Anti-Fascist National Libration Committee as a provisional government headed by Enver Hoxha.

1944.10.20

The second meeting of the Anti-Fascist National Libration Council held in Berat (Oct 20-24). On Oct 22, the Anti-Fascist National Libration Committee was transformed into the Democratic Government of Albania with Exver Hoxha as Prime Minister and Defence Minister.

1945.12.02

Constituent Assembly election.

1946.01.10

The Constituent Assembly convened. On Jan 11 the People’s Republic of Albania proclaimed, and on Jan 12 the Presidium of the Assembly was elected with Omer Nishani as Chairman of the Presidium.

1946.03.14

New constitution Statute of the People's Republic of Albania promulgated, and the Constituent Assembly was then turned into the People's Assembly.

1946.03.18

The People’s Assembly tasked Exver Hoxha to form a new government, which was apprived on March 22 and sworn in on March 24.

1953.08.01

Chairman of the Presidium of the People’s Assembly Omer Nishani resigned and was replaced by Haxhi Lleshi.

1954.07.20

Interior Minister Metmet Shehu replaced Enver Hoxha as Prime Minister.

1976.12.28

Constitution of the People's Socialist Republic of Albania promulgated.

1981.12.18

It was reported Prime Minister Mehmet Shehu committed suicide early today. First Deputy Prime Minister Adil Çarçani became acting Prime Minister, until formally nominated as Prime Minister on Jan 15, 1982.

1982.11.22

Remiz Alia was elected Chairman of the Presidium of the People’s Assembly (Head of State) in place of Haxhi Lleshi.

1985.04.11

Enver Hoxha died. Ramiz Alia was elected First Secretary of the Party on April 13.

1991.02.22

President Ramiz Alia appointed a caretaker government (temporary presidential council) headed by Fatos Nano.

1991.03.31

Parliament election.

1991.04.29

A major constitutional provision was promulgated with major changes to democracy. Ramiz Alia became President.

1991.05.09

Prime Minister Fatos Nano named his new cabinet after the election. Bow to the pressure of unrest, he resigned on June 4.

1991.06.05

Ylli Bufi was named new Prime Minister, and his coalition cabinet of national salvation was approved by Parliament on June 12.

1991.12.04

Democratic Party withdrew from the government. Prime Minister Ylli Bufi resigned on Dec 6. Vilson Ahmeti was named as Prime Minister on Dec 10, and his cabinet approved on Dec 18.

1992.03.22

Parliamentary Election. Second round on March 29.

1992.04.03

Ramiz Alia resigned as President. Sali Berisha was elected President by the Assembly on April 9.

1992.04.13

Aleksandër Meksi was appointed Prime Minister and his cabinet named on Dec 19.

1998.10.21

The Assembly passed the constitution and it passed referendum on Nov 22 and promulgated on Nov 28. It provided an Assembly as legislature.

爱尔兰 Ireland

爱尔兰原为英格兰属地，早于1297年英格兰便在爱尔兰设立议会，作为等级代表机关。1643年爱尔兰宣布独立，议会取得最高权力。1652年被并归英格兰、苏格兰和爱尔兰联合体。1660年复辟本政权。1801年与大不列颠联合王国合并为大不列颠和爱尔兰联合王国。1919年爱尔兰新芬党单方面宣布爱尔兰独立，并成立国民议会。 1922年[南]爱尔兰成为不列颠自治领。1931年取得独立。

1171.10.17

Henry II, King of England, landed in Ireland. This marked the Norman invasion of Ireland.

1175.10.06

Treaty of Windsor between King of England Henry II and High King of Ireland Rory O’Connor (Ruaidrí Ua Conchobair). Rory swore fealty to Henry.

1177.05.

Henry II declared his son John to be Lord of Ireland, thus created the Lordship of Ireland.

1264.06.18

The Parliament of Ireland met for first time in history.

1797

Elected representatives are first attested to the Parliament.

1541.06.18

Crown of Ireland Act. The title of King of Ireland created for King of England Henry III and his successors.

1641.10.23

The Irish Rebellion of 1641 began.

1642.05.10

Ireland’s Catholic clergies hled a synod at Kilkenny and drew up an Confederate Oath of Association, also asserted their loyalty to England King Charles I.

1642.10.24

The first Confederate General Assembly was held in Kilkenny where it set up two Houses, the Lords and the Commons, with Nicholas Plunkett acting as Chairman. The Gegenral Assembly met annually at Kilkenny and Nicholas Plunkett was Chairman for every year except 1648 when he’s absent abroad so Sir Richard Blake was Chairman.

1642.11.14?

The Confederate General Assembly elected an executive body Supreme Council, with Richard Butler, 3rd Viscount Mountgarrett as President.

1646.03.28

First Ormond Peace between England and pro-King lords in the Supreme Coucil. It is officially proclaimed on July 30. But with hardline Archbishop Giovanni Battista Rinuccini against, it was soon declared void. On 26 September, the clergy appointed a new Supreme Council, with Archbishop Rinuccini as its president.

1647.03.17

After Archbishop Rinuccini renounced his presidency of the Supreme Council, Randal MacDonnell, 1st Marquis of Antrim was elected new President. He held this position till Novermber when Richard Butler, 3rd Viscount Mountgarrett was back as President

1649.01.17

Second Ormond Peace secured an alliance between the Royalists and the Confederates. The Confederate was formally dissolved.

1649.08.15

Oliver Cromwell landed on Ireland and started the brutal conquest of Ireland.

1652.06.28

The Marquis of Clanricarde surrendered to Commonwealth forces, marking the full conquest of Ireland by Cromwell.

1652.08.12

The Act for the Settlement of Ireland imposed penalties including death and land confiscation against participants and bystanders of the Irish Rebellion of 1641.

1652.06.01

The English, Scottish and Irish monarchies were all restored under King Charles II. Also, the Parliament restored.

1800.03.28

The terms of the Union with Kingdom of Great Britain were agreed by both houses of the Irish Parliament. The British Act of Union became law on July 2 and royal assern gave to the Irish Act of Union on August 1. The provisions of the Acts of Union came ito force on Jan 1, 1801.

1800.08.02

The Irish Parliament met for the last time.

1919.01.21

Members of Sinn Féin of UK Parliament founded a separate parliament in Dublin called Dáil Éireann. They declared Irish independence and passed a Dáil Constitution. The executive power was on the President of the Ministry, and the legislative power was on the Dáil Éireann. Cathal Brugha was as first President of the Dáil Éireann (head of the executive government Ministries)

1919.04.01

Eamon de Valera was elected as President of the Dáil Éireann.

1920.12.23

Government of Ireland 1920 provided two home rule Parliaments in separate parts of Ireland (Northern and Southern). Each had a bicameral parliament with a Senate and a House of Commons. This Act came into formce on May 3, 1921.

1921.05.10

The Dáil passed a resolution that the elections scheduled to take place later in the month in both parts of the country would be "regarded as elections to Dáil Éireann".

1921.05.24

Election to House of Commons of Northern Ireland and House of Commons of Southern Ireland.

1921.06.28

Sothern Ireland House of Commons and Senate forally assembled. Only the four Unionist MPs attended the Commons and Gerald Fitzgibbon elected Speaker; only fifteen members attented the Seante meeting, and by defauly the Lord Chancellor of Ireland Sir John Ross became President of the Senate.

1921.08.16

Sinn Féin members elected to both Houses of Commons of Northern Ireland and Southern Ireland convened the second Dáil Éireann. Eamon de Valera was reelected as President of the Dáil Éireann.

1921.12.06

The 1921 Anglo-Irish Treaty signed by British government and Irish Republic. It provided for the establishment of the Irish Free State with status same as Canada. The British parliament approved on Dec 16 Irish Free State (Agreement) Act 1922 and the Dáil Éireann approved on Jan 7, 1922. However, it required approval from the members elected to sit in the House of Commons of Southern Ireland, which was convened with only pro-Treaty members on Jan 14. The Treaty received royal assent on March 31, 1922.

1922.01.09

Against the Treaty, Eamon de Valera resigned as President of the Dáil Éireann. On Jan 10 his opponent Arthur Griffith elected new President.

1922.01.14

On the meeting of the members elected to the House of Commons of Southern Ireland, a provisional government was elected with Michael Collins appointed its Chairman. His government took office on Jan 16.

1922.05.27

The Parliament of Southern Ireland ceased to exist accorind to the Treaty.

1922.06.08

The second Dáil Éireann adjourned to June 30, 1922, and the new Assembly set to met on July 1. But the Irish Civil War began on June 29 and made this agenda never happen.

1922.06.16

General election in Southern Ireland under the 1921 Anglo-Irish Treaty tot elect a Constituent Assembly to draft a Constitution for the Irish Free State.

1922.08.12

President of the Dáil Éireann Arthur Griffith died. William Thomas Cosgrave took acting role.

1922.08.22

Chairman of the Provisional Government Michael Collins was ambushed and killed in action. William Thomas Cosgrave was elected on August 25 and his new cabinet formed on August 30.

1922.09.09

The third Dáil Éireann finally met, started the Cosntituent Assembly. William Thomas Cosgrave became President of the Dáil Éireann, and thus this government and the provisional government became identical.

1922.10.25

The third Dáil adopted the Constitution of the Irish Free State. The legislature consisted of two houses, with the Dáil Éireann as the lower house, and the Senate as the upper house. It received the royal assent on Dec 5.

1922.12.06

The Constitution of the Irish Free State came into force. The Third Dáil therefore functioned as a legislative lower house. Tim Healy became first Governor-General, and William Thomas Cosgrave became President of the Executive Council.

1922.12.11

The Senate met for first time.

1936.05.19

The Seante met for last time.

1936.05.29

The Senate was abolished by the Constitution (Amendment No. 24) Act 1936.

1937.06.14

The Constitution of Ireland was approved by the Dáil Éireann. It passed a plebiscite on July 1 and came into force on Dec 29. The legislature still composed of the Dáil Éireann and the Senate.

1938.04.27

The new Senate met for first time.

爱沙尼亚 Estonia

爱沙尼亚原为俄罗斯属地，1918年独立，成立国民会议。1940年并归苏联。1991年恢复独立。

1917.04.12

The Russian Provisional Government issued an order on the provisional autonomy of Estonia, with Jaan Poska as Provincial Commissioner.

1917.07.14

The Estonian Provincial Assembly met for first time.

1917.11.28

The Estonian Provincial Assembly proclaimed itself to be the only legally elected and constituted authority in Estonia.

1917.12.08

The Estonian Soviet Executive Committee announced the election of Constituent Assembly, and at the same time dissolved the Provincial Assembly.

1918.02.10

The Bolshevik suspended the Constituent Assembly election.

1918.02.19

The Provincial Assembly created the Salvation Committee, which was granted full decision-making powers to ensure the continued activity of the Provincial Assembly. Members of Salvation Committee were Konstantin Päts, Jüri Vilms and Konstantin Konik.

1918.02.24

The Salvation Committee publicly proclaimed Estonia an independent and democratic republic. And a Provisional Government was appointed led by Konstantin Päts.

1918.11.19

The Estonian Provisional Government took over the rule of Estonia from High Commussioner of the German Government.

1919.04.07

The Estonian Constituent Assembly election held April 5-7. It met for the first time on April 23.

1919.05.08

The first government headed by Otto Strandman was approved by the Constituent Assembly.

1919.06.04

A provisional Constitution was adopted by the Constituent Assembly, which outlined the authority of the Constituent Assembly. It came into force from July 9.

1920.06.15

The first Constitution was adopted, introduced a single chamber Riigikogu. It came into force on Dec 21.

1920.11.29

The election to the first Riigikogu took place Nov 27-29. It came into work from Dec 20.

1933.10.16

A constitutional refrrendum was held between 14 and 16 October 1933. The new constitution gave the Head of State (State Elder) broad powers while reducing that of the Riigikogu. The Constitution came into force from Jan 24, 1934.

1934.03.12

State Elder Konstantin Päts carried a self-coup and declared a state of emergency. This was approved and legitimated by the riigikogu on March 16.

1934.10.02

The Riigikogu was dissolved with no new election planned.

1936.02.25

A referendum on convening a National Assembly to draft a new Cosntitution was held between 23 and 25 Feb 1936. The National Assembly consisted of two chambers.

1936.12.14

The election to the First Chamber was held on Dec 12-14.

1937.02.18

The first sitting of the National Assembly was held. Jüri Uluots was elected the Speaker of the First Chamber and Mihkel Pung was elected the Speaker of the Second Chamber.

1937.07.28

The National Assembly adopted a new Costitution and it was promulgated on August 17. The Constitution came into effect on Jan 1, 1938. It introduced a a bicameral National Assembly consisting of the Chamber of Deputies and the National Council.

1938.02.25

The election to the new Riigikogu was held 24-25 Feb 1938.

1938.04.07

The term of office of the members of Riigikogu began. It convened for first time on April 21.

1938.04.24

Konstantin Päts was electd President.

1940.04.19

The last meeting of the regular session of both chambers of the Riigikogu.

1940.06.16

The Soviet Union invaded Estonia. It was occupied on June 17.

1940.07.15

The election to the People’s Riigikogu took place under Soviet occupation held on July 14-15.

1940.07.21

The Riigikogu declared the Estonian SSR and requested admission to the Soviet Union the following day. It was approved by the Soviet Union on August 6.

1940.08.25

The Riigikogu renamed itself to the Provisional Supreme Soviet of the Estonian SSR, and it became the Supreme Soviet of the Estonian SSR on April 7, 1941.

1990.02.24

The Congress of Estonia (a grassroot parliament as part of independence movement) election. Its first meeting held on March 11-12, chaired by Endel Lippmaa and Rein Tamme. It selected a Committee of Estonia as permanent standing committee with Tunne Kelam as Chairman.

1990.03.18

The 12th Supreme Soviet of the Estonian SSR election.

1990.03.29

The first meeting of the Supreme Soviet of the Estonian SSR elected Arnold Rüütel as Chairman of the Supreme Soviet and Ülo Nugis Speaker of the Supreme Soviet.

1990.05.08

The Supreme Council renamed the name to Republic of Estonia, and the Supreme Soviet renamed Supreme Council of the Republic of Estonia.

1991.08.20

The Estonian Supreme Council declared national independence of Estonia. It also decided to establish a Constitutional Assembly to draft the Constitution. Tõnu Anton was elected the Chairman of the Assembly.

1991.09.13

The Constitutional Assembly convened for the first time, and last sitting was held on April 10, 1992.

1992.06.28

A referendum of the new Cosntituion was held. It took into force on July 3. The constitution restored the unicameral legislature.

1992.09.20

The election of the new Riigikogu. Its mandate began on Sept 30 and first meeting convened Oct 5.

1992.09.26

The Congress of Estonia held its last meeting before the Riigikogu mandate.

1992.03.23 Foreign minister Lennart Meri resigns and Jaan Manitski is named to replace him.

安道尔 Andorra

安道尔原由法兰西国家元首和乌赫尔主教分别兼任之世俗亲王和教会亲王共同统治。1868年制定宪法，实行宪政，成立总委员会。

1419.02.11

The first parliament in Andorra established, as the Consell de la Terra.

1866.04.22

The New Reformation changed the name from Consell de la Terra to Consell General de les Valls, with a syndic.

1993.02.02

New Constituion adopted, and later gained assent by the referendum on March 14. It came into force with the publication on April 28.

奥地利 Austria

奥地利早于1396年便出现议会，作为等级代表机关。1848年爆发革命，颁布宪法，实行宪政。同年成立帝国议会。1849年革命失败。1861年重新召开帝国议会。1867年确立君主立宪制。1918年废除君主制，建立共和政体。1933年陶尔斐斯Dollfuss建立一党专政，解散议会。1938年德意志并吞奥地利。1945年奥地利恢复独立，重开议会。

1848.03.13

March Revoluion in Vienna, and Metternich resigned as State Chancellor.

1848.04.25

The Pollersdorf Constitution promulgated which introduced a two chamber system, the Senate (Senat) and the Chamber of Deputies (Kammer der Abgeordneten).

1848.05.16

The Pollersdorf Constitution was declared provisional.

1848.06.13

The Reichstag election in Austrian section of the Austrian Empire.

1848.07.22

The Imperial Diet met for the first time.

1848.10.22

The Diet moved to Kremsier, from where a constitution was drafted with the Reichstag composed of a People’s Chamber (Volkskammer) and a State Chamber (Länderkammer).

1849.03.07

The Imperial Diet was dissolved and a new Constitution introduced on March 4, with same chambers proposed but never implemented.

1851.12.31

The enforced constitution was formally suspended by Franz Joseph I with the New Year's Eve patent.

1860.10.20

The October Diploma was adopted. It created a non-elected Reichsrat with extended power over expire’s finances but no power over legislation.

1861.02.26

The February Patent promulgated, established a vicameral imperial parliament called still Reichsrat, with a House of Deputies (Abgeordnetenhaus) and a House of Lords (Herrenhaus).

1861.04.29

The new Ewichsrat met for the first time.

1867.05.29

The Austro-Hungarian Compromise ratified by the newly restored Hungarian Diet.

1918.10.21

The Provisional National Assembly for German Austria (Deutschösterreich) established. Three Presidents are elected: Franz Dinghofer of the German Nationalist Party, Jodok Fink of the Christian-Socialist Party, who was followed by Johann Hauser on Oct 30, and Karl Seitz of the Social-Democratic Party. Also on Octobre 30, an Executive Committee was set up with Karl Renner as head.

1918.10.30

The last meeting of the Herrenhaus.

1918.11.12

The Abgeordnetenhaus held its last meeting after Emperor proclamation for abdication.

1918.11.12

The Republic of German-Austria proclaimed by the Provisional National Assembly.

1919.02.16

The Constituent National Assembly election.

1919.03.04

The Constituent National Assembly convened its opening session, replacing the Provisional National Assembly.

1919.10.21

The Constituent National Assembly ratified Treaty of Saint-Germain-en-Laye, proclaimed Republic of Austria.

1920.10.01

The Constitution of Austria enacted. The parliament consists of two houses, the National Council and the Federal Council. It came into force on Nov 10.

1920.10.17

Parliament election.

1920.11.10

First meeting of the new Parliament.

1933.03.04

The President of the National Council resigned, Chancellor Engelbert Dollfuss stated that Parliament had eliminiated itself and that his government had the ahthoruty to rule b degree.

1934.04.30

A National Council without the Social Democratic members authorized the government to adopt a corporatist authoritarian constitution, whicl promulgated on May 1. Franz Hemala was President of the National Council for one day.

1945.04.27

The proclamation of independence of the Second Republic of Austria

1945.11.25

Parliamentary election to the restored National Council.

1945.12.19

First meeting of the new National Council.

1848.07.22-1849.03.07 Reichstag, first democratic representation of the people in Austria after the 1848 March Revolution.

1861-1918 Reichsrat (Imperial Diet), representation of the peoples of the kingdoms and countries of the Austrian part (Cisleithania) of the Austro-Hungarian monarchy (1865-1918)

consisted of the Herrenhaus (291 members appointed by the emperor (1914)) and of the Abgeordnetenhaus (516 members elected for 6 years (for the last time in 1911)).

Herrenhaus (House of Lords): The upper chamber in the former Austrian Reichsrat existed from 1861 to 1918;

Abgeordnetenhaus (House of Deputies / Austrian parliament): After the March Revolution of 1848 the Pillersdorf Constitution transferred legislative power to a Reichstag consisting of two houses (Abgeordnetenhaus and Senate).

The actual bicameral system (Abgeordnetenhaus and Herrenhaus (Upper Chamber)) was not introduced until 1861, when the February Patent (constitution written by A. Schmerling, approved by Emperor Franz Josef in 1861) went into effect.

Nationalversammlung, Provisorische (National Assembly, Provisional of the Independent German-Austrian State".), 1918.10.21-1919.02.16

Konstituierende Nationalversammlung (Constituent National Assembly), elected on February 16, 1919, ceased to exist after the elections of October 17, 1920.

Nationalrat (National Council), main legislative body of the Federal Republic (succeeded the Abgeordnetenhaus)

Presidents of the National Council of the Republic of Austria Karl Seitz*(SDAP) Oct. 21, 1918 - Feb. 16, 1919 Karl Seitz**(SDAP) March 5, 1919 - Nov. 9, 1920 Richard Weiskirchner (CS) Nov. 10, 1920 - Nov. 20, 1923 …

*President of Provisional National Assembly  **President of Constitutive National Assembly.

Bundesrat (Federal Council), second chamber of parliament,

Nationalrat and the Bundesrat together form the Bundesversammlung.( (Federal Assembly))

捷克斯洛伐克Czechoslovakia-捷克和斯洛伐克Czech and Slovakia

波希米亚和斯洛伐克原分属奥地利和匈牙利，14世纪波希米亚开始召开等级议会，作为等级代表机关。1918年波希米亚和斯洛伐克独立，合并成立捷克斯洛伐克，并成立临时国民议会。1939年德意志并吞捷克斯洛伐克。 1945年复国。1990年改国名为捷克和斯洛伐克。1993年最终分裂为捷克和斯洛伐克两国。

Bohemia

1848.03.11

The Committee of the Prague Citizenship (Výbor pražského měšťanstva, also named Výborem Svatováclavským) was elected with Vojtěch Deym as its president.

1848.04.13

National Committee (Národní výbor) formed as an expansion of the St. Wenceslas Committee joined by a special committee composed of Czech potilicans, with Rudolf Stadion as President. On April 15 Stadion was replace as President by Lev Thun-Hohenstein.

1848.06.26

The National Committee was dissolved. And thus, the planned Bohemia Diet was never met.

1861.04.06

The Bohemia Diet met for first time follow Austria’s February Patent.

1913.07.26

The Bohemia Diet was dissolved and replaced by the provincial administrative commission (nahrazen zemskou správní komisí/German Landesverwaltungskommission) chaired by Vojtěcha Schönborna.

Moravia

1848.05.31

A provisional Moravian Diet met between May 31 till Jan 24, 1849. The meetings were initially chaired by Hugo Salm and then followed by Jihann Koppel.

1861.04.07

The Moravian Diet was reinstated follow Austria’s February Patent.

1914.02.28

The last session of the Moravian Diet.

Silesia

1848.05.31

An enlarged Silesian Convention was elected, and it met for first time on June 20.

1849.12.30

The Austrian emperor issued a constitution to formalize the enlargement of the Diet.

1851.12.31

Austrian emperor repealed the 1849 Cosntituion, thus abolished the Diet.

1861.04.16?

The Silesian Diet was reinstated follow Austria’s February Patent.

Czechoslovakia

1916.11.18

National Committee formed, but it ceased to exist by July 1917.

1918.07.13

Czechoslovak National Committee established, with Karel Kramář as Chairman.

1918.10.28

Proclamation of Indepdendence of Czechoslovak State

1918.11.14

The Revolutionary National Assembly was formed as the highest legislative body, follow a provisional Constitution on previous day. The Chairman of the Assembly is František Tomášek.

1920.02.29

The Czechoslovak Constitution was adopted by the Revolutionary National Assembly and it was promulgated on March 6. The legislature National Assembly was bicameral, and it consisted of a Chamber of Deputies and a Senate.

1920.04.18

First election to the Chamber of Deputies

1920.04.25

First election to the Senate

1920.05.26

First meeting of the National Assembly. František Tomášek was President of the Chamber of Deputies and Cyril Horáček President of the Senate.

1920.07.13

Karel Prášek was President of the Senate.

1924.02.14

Václav Donát was President of the Senate.

1925.11.15

Parliamentary election.

1925.12.17

Jan Malypetr elected new President of the Chamber, and Václav Donát reelected President of Senate.

1926.02.18

Václav Klofáč elected President of Senate.

1926.11.30

Mořic Hruban elected President of Senate.

1929.10.27

Parliamentary election.

1929.12.12

Jan Malypetr reelected new President of the Chamber, and František Soukup elected President of Senate.

1932.10.29

Jan Malypetr resigned as President of the Chamber.

1932.11.03

František Staněk elected President of the Chamber of Deputies.

1935.05.19

Parliamentary election.

1935.06.18

Bohumír Bradáč elected new President of the Chamber, and František Soukup reelected President of Senate.

1935.10.20

Bohumír Bradáč died.

1935.11.06

Jan Malypetr reelected as President of Chamber of Deputies.

1938.12.16

The Chamber of Deputies met for last time. The Senate met for last time on Dec 17.

1939.03.16

Czechoslovakia annexed by Germany.

1945.08.25

Presidential drgree to establish the Interim National Assembly for the period until the National Assembly general election.

1945.10.28

The Interim National Assembly opened, and Josef David elected its President.

1946.05.16

Last session of the Interim National Assembly.

1946.05.26

Parliamentary elction to the Constituent Assembly.

1946.06.18

Constituent National Assembly opened, Antonín Zápotocký as President till July 18 when Josef David replaced him.

1948.05.09

The new Constitution of the Czechoslovak Republic was adopted by the Constituent National Assembly, and it took effect on June 9. This constitution provided a unicameral National Assembly.

1948.05.30

南斯拉夫Yugoslavia

塞尔维亚和蒙特尼格罗 Serbia and Montenegro

1918年塞尔维亚、蒙特尼格罗和斯洛文尼亚-克罗地亚-塞尔维亚国合并成立本政权。1920年成立制宪议会。 1929年改国名为南斯拉夫。1941年轴心国入侵并肢解南斯拉夫。1943年共产党重建南斯拉夫。1945年正式废除君主制。1991年起南斯拉夫陷入分裂，各加盟共和国相继独立。1992年余下两个加盟共和国塞尔维亚和蒙特尼格罗重组南斯拉夫。2003年改组为邦联式国家，改国名为塞尔维亚和蒙特尼格罗。2006年解体。

1848.09.15

西班牙 Spain

西班牙地区早于1188年便出现等级会议，作为等级代表机关。1516年正式形成西班牙王国。1808年法兰西入侵西班牙，西班牙各地掀起革命，1809年成立制宪议会。1812年制定宪法，实行宪政。1814年革命失败，恢复君主专制。此后西班牙曾经历多番政治变动。1931年废除君主制，建立共和政府。1939年佛朗哥Franco在全国建立法西斯专政。1975年恢复君主制，此后政局渐趋稳定，并逐渐确立议会民主制度。

希腊 Greece

希腊上古时代某些城邦(如雅典)曾实行奴隶主民主政治，出现五百人会议、公民大会等机关。其后希腊长期受外国统治。1832年独立。1843年颁布《根本法》，实行宪政。1844年成立议会。1936年起先后经历多次独裁政府上台和轴心国入侵，议会曾数度被解散。1974年废除君主制，建立共和政体，重新设立议会。

Time

Local Name

English Name

Chinese Name

*议会 1844 - 1926.1；1927 - 1936.8；1946.3 - 1967.4.21；1974.11 -

**上议院 1844 - 1864；1927 - 1936.8；1946.3 - 1967.4.21

**下议院 1844 - 1864；1927 - 1936.8；1946.3 - 1967.4.21

匈牙利 Hungary

匈牙利早于1222年便设立议会，作为等级代表机关。其后匈牙利成为奥地利附庸国。1848年爆发革命，政府被迫推行宪政，成立国民议会。1918年独立。1944年为德意志占领，1945年恢复独立。

1608

The Hungarian Parliament was officially divided into two panels, the House of Magnetes and the House of Deputies.

1848.04.11

The April Laws passed by Hungary Diet in March was signed by King Ferdinand I of Austria. It was a collection of laws legislated aimed of modernizing the Kingdom of Hungary, among them a parliament was set for bicameral with a ministry cabinet responsible to the parliament.

1848.07.05

First popular represented National Assembly opened.

1849.04.14

The National Assembly passed the Hungarian Declaration of Independence composed by Lajos Kossuth.

1849.08.11

Lajos Kossuth abdicated, and last seesion of the National Assembly held in Arad. His successor Artúr Görgey surrendered to Austrian troops on August 13. This ended the independence movement and its government and parliament.

1861.04.06

The Parliament was convoked by Emperor Francis Joseph after having proclaimed the Octobor Diploma.

1861.08.22

The Parliament was dissolved by the Emperor.

1865.12.14

The Hungarian Parliament reassembled.

1867.02.27

The Hungarian Parliament was restored based on 1848 April Laws, with a responsive cabinet led by Gyula gróf Andrássy already appointed on Feb 17.

1918.10.25

The Hungarian National Council was appointed with Mihály Károlyi as president.

1918.10.28

The Aster Revolution began and by October 31 Austrian Emperor Charles IV forced to accept the coup result with Mihály Károlyi as Prime Minsiter. János Hock was elected new President of the National Council on Nov 1.

1918.11.16

The Hungarian People's Republic proclaimed. The old House of Deputies dissolved itself and House of Magnates closed with not setting a new session date.

1919.03.21

A new government called Revolutionary Governing Council was set up which proclaimed Hungarian Soviet Republic. The legislature body for this Republic is the National Assembly of Soviets.

1919.06.14

The National Assembly of Soviets met for the first time after the local council election around April 7-8. Ignác Bogár was elected Chairman of the Assembly on June 15.

1919.08.01

The Hungarian Soviet Republic collapsed. A government led by Gyula Peidl lasted till August 6, when the National Assembly of Soviets ceased its function.

1919.08.06

István Friedrich seized power. Joseph August declared himself Regent of Hungary on August 7, which position he held until August 12 when he was forced to resign.

1920.01.26

Parliamentary election to the unicameral National Assembly. It officially opened on Feb 16.

1920.02.29

Law I of 1920 declared the restoration of the monarchical form of government and Kingdom of Hungary, and legislative power went to the National Assembly.

1920.03.01

Miklós Horthy was voted as Regent of the Kingdom of Hungary.

1926.11.15

Law XXII of 1926 restored the upper house to the National Assembly, and the lower house be the House of Representatives.

1944.10.15

Miklós Horthy issued a proclamation for an armistice with the Allies which triggered Hitler Operation Panzerfaust. Horthy was forced to appointed Ferenc Szálasi as Prime Minister on October 16.

1944.11.04

Ferenc Szálasi took oath as National Leader.

1944.12.21

A Hungarian Provisional National Assembly supported by Soviet Union met in Debrecen.

1945.11.04

National Assembly election.

1946.01.31

Law I of 1946 fornally ended the thousand-year monarchy and introduced a republican form of government.

1949.08.20

New Constitution confirmed a Communist controlled People’s Republic and National Assembly.

1989.10.23

The Constituion was amended to remove the Communist character, proclaimed Republic of Hungary and a new Parliament multi-party elected.

意大利 Italy

意大利在上古罗马共和国时代曾实行古代共和制度，出现百人团会议、平民会议、元老院等机关。在中古时代意大利长期陷入分裂状态。在部分意大利城市共和国（如威尼斯、佛罗伦萨等）曾出现议会组织的雏型。1861年意大利实现统一，成立议会。1946年废除君主制，建立共和政府。

英国 United Kingdom
